Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.00,0:00:07.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Downloaded from YTS.MX\N(字幕翻譯：Hardstick,校核：Hardstick，時間軸來自官譯版本）
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.00,0:00:13.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Official YIFY movies site: YTS.MX
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.00,0:02:11.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,倫敦，1890年代
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.32,0:02:28.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Get me a cab, will you?\N-Yes, sir.\N 請給我叫輛馬車？—是,先生
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.23,0:02:30.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The most brilliantly written play I've seen in years.\N它是這幾年中我看到最精彩的戲了.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.88,0:02:32.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The man's a born wit.\N這人真是天生奇才。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.19,0:02:33.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The whole play was tremendously exciting.\N整劇非常令人興奮。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.89,0:02:35.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hear he's writing a new one.\N聽說，他正在寫一部新劇。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.54,0:02:37.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can hardly wait to see it.\N我都等不住想看它了。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.46,0:02:39.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cab!\N馬車！
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.37,0:02:42.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, gentlemen, the English theater has just given birth to a genius.\N那是，先生們，英國戲劇界誕生了一個天才。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.51,0:02:44.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I feel sure Wilde would be the first to agree with you, Harry.\N我覺得，王爾德會首先贊同你，哈利。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.90,0:02:47.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wish I could approve of the playwright as much as I approve of his play.\N我會欣賞劇作家本人，就像我欣賞他的戲劇。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.60,0:02:50.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who cares about him as long as he continues to give us plays like this?\N只要他不斷給我們呈現這樣的作品，誰會在乎他本人那？
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.50,0:02:52.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,聖詹姆斯劇院隆重上演\N奧斯卡 王爾德 劇著\N《溫德米爾夫人的扇子》
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.94,0:03:25.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Oscar, how does it feel to be a success?\N那麼，奧斯卡，成功的感覺如何？
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.11,0:03:26.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you have any doubts, Robbie?\N羅比，你沒想到吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.12,0:03:35.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Congratulations, Oscar.Brilliant play! Brilliant!\N祝賀你，奧斯卡，精彩的戲！太精彩了！
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.99,0:03:38.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, there I've bound to agree with you,Lord Sonning.\N是的，我也這麼看，桑寧爵士。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.69,0:03:42.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My dear Mr. Wilde, I was simply delighted with your play.\N親愛的王爾德先生，我真為你的戲劇高興。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.83,0:03:43.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I even enjoyed the interval.\N我甚至更享受幕間休息。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.74,0:03:49.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dear Lady Sonning,she has the remains of a remarkable ugliness.\N親愛的桑寧夫人還是有著明顯丑陋的剩余物。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.31,0:03:52.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've always been a great admirer of your work, Mr. Wilde.\N王爾德先生，我一直對您的作品報以極大的敬意。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.14,0:03:54.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I've always been a great admirer of my work, Mr. Shaw.\N蕭先生，我也一直對我的作品報以敬意。\N（蕭伯納，英國現代傑出的現實主義戲劇作家）
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.49,0:03:56.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Frank!-Oscar!\N-弗蘭克！-奧斯卡！
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.88,0:03:58.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Wonderful play.-Thank you.\N精彩的戲。-謝謝你
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.28,0:03:59.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-My dear lady mother.-Oscar.\N-我親愛的母親大人。-奧斯卡
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.80,0:04:03.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My dear boy, a triumph. A magnificent triumph.\N我親愛的孩子，一場勝利。一場偉大的勝利。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.33,0:04:06.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ada, what are you going to say about my play in that woman's magazine you run?\N艾達，你將在你經營的婦女雜志上怎樣評價我的戲劇？
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.72,0:04:09.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I shall praise it as highly as you would yourself, Oscar.\N奧斯卡，我將會像你本人一樣給它很高的贊揚。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.11,0:04:10.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've always been the best critic of my work.\N你一直是我作品的最好評論家。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.59,0:04:12.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-But I never criticize your work.-Exactly.\N-但是我從未批評過你的作品。-沒錯。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.03,0:04:16.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so proud, Oscar.\N奧斯卡，我真為你驕傲。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.73,0:04:18.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I'm so proud of you.\N我也為你驕傲。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.91,0:04:20.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You look wonderful.\N你真可愛。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.95,0:04:22.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oscar, people are watching.\N奧斯卡，人們都在看著呢。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.34,0:04:23.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hardly think Oscar is the type of man\N我很難想象奧斯卡是那種
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.95,0:04:25.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to worry about his behavior in public.\N在公眾面前注重自己行為的男人。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.78,0:04:27.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And how did brother Willie\Nlike the play?\N怎麼威利兄弟也會喜歡戲劇？
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.57,0:04:28.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or couldn't you see it from the bar?\N你難道不是剛從從酒吧出來嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.83,0:04:30.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ooh, I've perfectly sober,thank you, Oscar.\N哦，謝謝，奧斯卡，我從未如此清醒。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.40,0:04:32.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've ordered a table at the Savoy.\N我在薩伏伊飯店訂了一張桌子。\N（它奠定了全球豪華酒店的最早標准）
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.18,0:04:33.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OSCAR: Get a cab, Robbie,there's a good chap.    -ROBBIE: Of course.\N奧斯卡：叫輛車，羅比，這是個好伙計   -羅比：當然了
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.96,0:04:35.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Constance, you don't mind not coming.\N康斯坦斯，你不想一起去嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.84,0:04:37.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-But you know,these supper parties.    -Very well, Oscar.\N- 你知道的，首演慶功晚餐。   -好的，奧斯卡\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.97,0:04:40.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Mother will take you.Now, won't you, Mother?   -Yes, of course.\N-媽媽會帶上你的，是吧？媽媽    -當然嘍。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.10,0:04:41.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Willie, get my wrap.  -Goodbye, my dear.\N-威利，拿上我的披風。   -再見，親愛的。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.80,0:04:42.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ada.\N艾達。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.28,0:04:44.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come along, Bosie.\N跟我來，波西。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.28,0:04:46.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good night, Mrs. Wilde.\N晚上好，王爾德夫人。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.02,0:04:48.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good night, Bosie.\N晚上好，波西。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.55,0:04:54.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A green carnation.How delightfully eccentric.\N綠色康乃馨，多逗的怪人。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.77,0:04:56.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damned ridiculous,if you ask me.\N要我看，那是可惡的荒唐。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.33,0:04:58.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But who's the handsome\Nyoung boy with him?\N跟著他的那位帥哥是誰？
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.34,0:05:00.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good heavens, Edith,you are out of touch.\N天哪，艾迪思，你一點都不曉得嗎
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.34,0:05:02.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why, the whole of London is talking about them.\N 難怪，全倫敦都在談論他們。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.17,0:05:04.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a damn disgrace the way the fellow is carrying on.\N這對同伴的行事方式令人詛咒和不齒。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.39,0:05:06.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These artistic fellows think they can get away with anything.\N這兩藝術伙伴以為他們可以拋開世人的一切。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.69,0:05:07.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But who is he? Well, you...\N他是誰？你。。。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.00,0:05:10.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's Lord Alfred Douglas.Queensberry's son.\N他是阿爾佛雷德 道格拉斯爵士。昆斯博裡大人的兒子。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.91,0:05:13.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I were Queensberry, I've...\N如果我是昆斯博裡，我會。。。\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.70,0:05:16.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've do what, sir?What would you do?\N你會做什麼？你要做什麼？
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.97,0:05:19.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What would you do?\N你要做什麼？
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.32,0:05:22.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.\N讓一下。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.45,0:05:26.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Alfred, you remember my daughter?\N阿爾弗雷德爵士，您還認識我女兒嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.50,0:05:28.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Oh, Mrs. Somers.How do you do?-Phyllis.\N-噢，索摩斯夫人，你好啊？-菲利斯
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.28,0:05:29.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Poor Mrs. Somers.\N可憐的索摩斯夫人
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.76,0:05:32.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still trying to get that daughter off her hands.\N還想著把她女兒推銷出去。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.24,0:05:34.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, she's wasting her time with him.\N對他來說，她是在白費力。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.11,0:05:35.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my lord.\N哦，我的大人。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.03,0:05:37.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You wicked man.\N你這個邪惡的人。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.34,0:05:45.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bosie!\N波西
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.91,0:05:48.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you even acknowledge me anymore?\N你不認我了嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.91,0:05:50.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want, Father?\N你想干什麼，父親？
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.43,0:05:53.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you any idea how sick it makes me\N你知道我有多惡心嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.09,0:05:55.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to watch you making a fool of yourself?\N看到你在對你自己做傻事
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.18,0:05:57.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A fine spectacle you are, sir,fawning and crawling round this fellow, Wilde,\N真夠丟人現眼的，一個勳爵，居然居然奉承巴結在這個王爾德身邊，
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.87,0:05:59.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,like some damn little lapdog.\N像一只可憐的哈巴狗。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.53,0:06:01.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are we going to have another one of your scenes, Father?\N我們能換個地點說這件事嗎？父親。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.18,0:06:03.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Scenes or no scenes, sir.I'd not tolerate this behavior.\N管它什麼場合，我不允許這種行為。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.45,0:06:06.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you sooner I went around with professional boxers and sporting gentry?\N你能待會兒嗎，等我去職業拳擊運動俱樂部？
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.27,0:06:07.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At least my friends behave like men.\N至少我的朋友們表現像男人一樣。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.80,0:06:09.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Father, I'm over 21...-Only just.\N-父親，我已經21歲了。。。-剛剛。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.80,0:06:11.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't see that I have to answer to you for my behavior,\N我就不明白了，為什麼你要管我的事
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.80,0:06:13.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,nor seek your permission for the choice of my friends.\N為什麼擇友還要得到你的許可。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.89,0:06:15.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are a disgrace to the name of Queensberry!\N你給昆斯博裡家族帶來恥辱
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.81,0:06:17.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I really don't have...Bosie, is the cab ready yet?\N我真的不想這樣。。。波西，叫馬車了嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.07,0:06:21.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oscar, this unpleasant little man is my father.\N奧斯卡，這個令人不快的人是我父親。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.38,0:06:22.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Lord Queensberry?-Yes.\N-昆斯博裡侯爵？-是的。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.51,0:06:23.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pleasure to meet you, sir.\N侯爵，很高興認識你。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.73,0:06:24.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The pleasure is entirely yours,Mr. Wilde.\N那是你高興，王爾德先生
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.81,0:06:26.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Oscar, let's go.-Just a minute.\N-奧斯卡，我們走吧。-等等
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.38,0:06:27.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-I have a few things to say to this gentleman.-Father!\N-我有一些話要向這位先生說。-父親！
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.90,0:06:29.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-You listen to me, sir.-Oh, really, Lord Queensberry.\N-你給我聽好了，先生。-哦，是的，昆斯博裡侯爵。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.60,0:06:31.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think the public have had enough play acting for one night.\N在晚上，每個人都都演自己的自由。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.34,0:06:33.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I demand to be heard!\N你給我聽著！
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.04,0:06:34.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are being heard, sir,by the entire theater.I should...\N聽著呢，侯爵，我想全劇院的人也都聽著那。。。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.30,0:06:35.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well done, Wilde.\N干不錯啊，王爾德。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.00,0:06:38.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Most entertaining.We both thought so,didn't we, my dear?\N太有趣了，我們都這麼認為，不是嗎？親愛的。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.00,0:06:40.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're very flattering,Your Royal Highness.\N您過獎了，殿下( 此時的威爾士親王，後來的愛德華七世國王）
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.66,0:06:42.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And Mrs. Langtry,you're very beautiful.\N蘭格夫人，您真漂亮。（演員，也是威爾士親王的情人）\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.61,0:06:45.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I adore flattery almost as much as you do, Oscar.\N奧斯卡，我和你一樣喜歡被過獎。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.44,0:06:47.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't know you were a patron of the arts, Queensberry.\N我還真不知道你也是一個藝術的熱心者，昆斯博裡。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.58,0:06:51.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought fist fighting was more in your line.\N我原以為你只會拳擊比賽。\N（第八代昆斯博裡侯爵是現代拳擊運動規則創始人）
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.19,0:06:53.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, thank you for a most enjoyable evening, Wilde.\N那麼，感謝你帶來的愉快夜晚，王爾德。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.58,0:06:55.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We shall look forward to the next play.\N我們期待你下一部大作。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.41,0:07:00.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good night, sir.\N再見，大人。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.11,0:07:01.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You coming, Bosie?\N你來嗎？波西。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.03,0:07:07.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me just say this, Father.You're been hounding me long enough.\N父親，我受夠了你像獵狗一樣追我。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.07,0:07:08.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you try and interfere with me again,\N如果你再試著這樣干涉我，
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.86,0:07:10.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or write anymore of your abusive letters,\N或者發出那些罵人的信件，
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.73,0:07:13.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I shall have no hesitation in seeking the protection of the law.\N我將不得不尋求法律的保護。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.47,0:07:16.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You may have the law on your hands much sooner than you think, my boy.\N制裁你的法律會來的比你想得要早，小子。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.12,0:07:50.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning, Edward.\N早上好，愛德華。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.47,0:07:52.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning, Mr. Wilde, sir.Lovely morning.\N早上好，王爾德先生，多好的早晨。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.77,0:07:54.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I think I'll walk a little. Follow.\N是的，我正打算走一段路，跟著我吧。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.04,0:07:59.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where to, sir?\N去哪裡？先生。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.30,0:08:01.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Cafe Royal.\N皇家咖啡館。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.17,0:08:03.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cafe Royal? Very good, sir.\N皇家咖啡館，好的，先生。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.62,0:08:13.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Wilde. Mr. Wilde, sir.\N王爾德先生，王爾德先生，先生。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.97,0:08:16.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Wilde, one thing my readers are anxious to learn.\N王爾德先生，有件事我的讀者們急切想知道。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.19,0:08:18.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-What paper do you write for, sir?-The Echo,sir.\N-你是哪家報社的？ -回聲報，先生。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.19,0:08:20.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, if your readers were anxious to learn anything,\N那麼，您的讀者想知道的任何事情
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.15,0:08:21.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they wouldn't take the Echo.\N無需通過回聲。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.93,0:08:25.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,May I ask you, sir,why do you always wear a green carnation?\N我能問您一下嗎？先生，為什麼您總戴一朵綠色康乃馨？
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.59,0:08:27.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,REPORTER: Mr. Wilde,your book Dorian Gray...\N記者：王爾德先生，您的書《道林 格雷的肖像》。。。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.15,0:08:28.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute. What did you say, sir?\N等一下，你說什麼？先生。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.37,0:08:29.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you always wear a green carnation?\N您為什麼總戴一朵綠色康乃馨？
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.94,0:08:31.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I consider nature to be quite inadequate.\N因為我認為我的自然天性總是不足。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.72,0:08:33.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why she never thought of a green carnation,I can't imagine.\N為什麼她從不考慮綠色康乃馨，我不能想象。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.86,0:08:35.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,REPORTER: Mr. Wilde.No doubt she will get around to it in time.\N記者：王爾德先生，無疑她是想及時繞開它。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.86,0:08:40.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Wilde, your book Dorian Grayhas been severely criticized.\N王爾德先生，您的作品《道林 格雷的肖像》已經被嚴肅地批評了。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.08,0:08:41.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not by me.\N不是被我。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.82,0:08:44.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but, many people do consider it immoral.\N是的，但是，許多人認為它不道德。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.21,0:08:48.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, now, sir.What is immorality? I consider that to conform\N告訴我，先生，什麼是不道德？難道一定要迎合
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.26,0:08:50.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to the narrow moral standards of this Victorian age\N維多利亞時代狹隘的道德規范
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.96,0:08:53.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the grossest form of immorality.\N來統稱什麼是不道德嗎
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.66,0:08:55.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but, you know,it is said, sir,\N是的，但是，您知道，大家都說\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.27,0:08:57.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that much of your writing and indeed your basic philosophy\N你寫的書和您本人基本哲學思想
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.88,0:08:59.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is fundamentally immoral.What have you to say to that?\N根本就是不道德，您對此有什麼好說的？
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.97,0:09:01.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I may have offended some people,\N我可能已經得罪了很多人，
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.54,0:09:03.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I'm sure that in 50 years,\N但我敢肯定，50年後，\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.63,0:09:05.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the works of Oscar Wilde\Nwill be standard literature\N奧斯卡王爾德的作品會是文學上的標桿
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.54,0:09:07.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for every fifth form schoolboy.\N對於每五年制小學生來說。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.54,0:09:08.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hear! Hear!\N有理！有理！
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.72,0:09:10.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My only regret is that I shan't be there\N我的遺憾是，那時我將不在人世了
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.59,0:09:12.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-to collect the royalties.\N-不能去收取版稅了。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.59,0:09:16.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I must say I hardly think a newspaperman\N我必須說，我不認為報紙記者
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.42,0:09:18.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is in a position to speak of immorality.\N具有評價是否道德的資格。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.38,0:09:20.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-What? -Indeed, Lord Alfred.\N-什麼？ -其實，阿爾弗雷德勳爵。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.34,0:09:22.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, what could be more immoral than a newspaper?\N看吧，還有什麼比報紙更不道德？
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.64,0:09:24.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It condemns gambling on the front page\N它們在頭版譴責賭博
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.60,0:09:26.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and prints racing tips on the back.\N卻在後版刊登賽馬提示。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.82,0:09:28.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Brilliant, Bosie. I wish I've said that.\N好極了，波西，我希望我也能說出你這樣的話。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.65,0:09:30.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You will, Oscar. You will.\N你會的，奧斯卡，你會的。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.52,0:09:35.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you go back to Oxford,you can say you outwitted Oscar Wilde.\N當你回到牛津，你就能說你以機制取勝了奧斯卡王爾德。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.22,0:09:37.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I ever go back,I certainly will.\N如果還能我回去，我當然會的。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.66,0:09:38.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?\N你什麼意思？
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.66,0:09:42.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, didn't you know? I've been sent down.\N我被勸退了。（牛津大學墨德琳學院）
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.58,0:09:44.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Congratulations!\N恭喜！
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.27,0:09:46.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All the best people are being sent down these days.\N這年頭，所有的好人都被勸退了。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.36,0:09:48.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you do, Bosie? Set fire to the dean's trousers?\N你做什麼了？把院長的褲子燒了？
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.76,0:09:50.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Waiter! Waiter! More champagne.\N侍者！侍者！再來瓶香檳。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.19,0:09:52.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Frankly I believe too much education's a bad thing.\N坦率地說，我相信教育有很多弊端。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.02,0:09:54.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you agree, Oscar?\N這你贊同吧，奧斯卡
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.20,0:09:55.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I certainly do.\N我當然贊同。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.89,0:09:58.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ignorance is a delicate blossom. Touch it and it has gone.\N愚昧無知是一朵嬌嫩的花朵，如你觸碰它一下，它就凋謝了。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.73,0:10:03.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't tell me that you've been sent down.\N你怎麼不告訴我，你被勸退了。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.21,0:10:06.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Didn't I? -No.\N-我沒有嗎？ -是的
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.47,0:10:09.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Oh. -Why?\N-噢。 -為什麼？
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.74,0:10:12.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was all rather tedious.\N它太沉悶乏味了。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.13,0:10:13.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tedious or not, I've like to hear about it.\N不管是否沉悶，我都想聽聽。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.44,0:10:21.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, there was some scandal over a boy in the town.\N好吧，有一些關於城裡男孩的丑聞。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.35,0:10:23.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know how provincial Oxford can be in some ways.\N你知道，牛津校方對這方面一直很野蠻偏見。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.40,0:10:26.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Frankly, I find the whole thing rather amusing,\N坦率地說，我認為整件事很好玩。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.80,0:10:30.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but unfortunately my father didn't.\N不幸的是，我父親不這麼看。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.36,0:10:33.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was so disgusted with his "so called son" as he put it,\N他厭惡他的“所謂的兒子”，於是
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.76,0:10:36.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that he's disowned me completely.\N他和我斷絕了關系。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.07,0:10:38.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So now, I haven't a penny in the world.\N現在，我在這個世界上就沒有一便士。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.33,0:10:39.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,MAN: Frank, you've drunk.\N男人：弗蘭克，你喝醉了。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.03,0:10:41.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,FRANK: Drunk? Who's drunk?\N弗蘭克：醉了？誰醉了？
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.94,0:10:45.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oscar, have you ever seen me when I had more than I could carry?\N奧斯卡，你以前看到過我喝下去這麼多嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.07,0:10:47.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, but I've seen you when you should have taken more than one trip.\N沒有，但是我看到你出去（方便）了不止一次。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.51,0:10:53.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you tell me about this before?\N為什麼你不告訴我這些？
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.13,0:10:54.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you were so busy, what, with your play and...\N你總是很忙，忙劇本，忙其他。。。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.74,0:10:58.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you've in any trouble, you only have to come to me.\N如果你有什麼困難，請來找我。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.61,0:11:00.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And if it's money you need,you needn't worry.\N你不要擔心錢的事情
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.14,0:11:05.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've very kind to me, Oscar.\N你對我太好了，奧斯卡。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.36,0:11:06.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm very fond of you.\N我非常喜歡你。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.79,0:11:10.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, what is friendship for?\N再說，友誼是用來做什麼的？
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.62,0:11:12.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Mr. Wilde, we're running out of conversation.\N來吧，王爾德先生，我們已經沒得好聊了。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.45,0:11:13.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as we've not running out of wine.\N只要我們還沒有喝完酒
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.76,0:11:17.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Waiter! Waiter!\N侍者！侍者！
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.45,0:11:19.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, gentlemen, in the past few years,\N先生們，在過去幾年中，
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.46,0:11:20.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've made a remarkable discovery.\N我有一個驚人的發現。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.89,0:11:22.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that, Oscar?\N什麼呀？奧斯卡。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.15,0:11:23.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alcohol, if taken in sufficient quantities,\N酒精，只要喝個夠
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.59,0:11:25.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,produces all the effects of intoxication.\N就能產生所有陶醉的效果。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.29,0:11:28.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gentlemen, I give you a toast.\N先生們，我提議干杯。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.77,0:11:31.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To youth.\N致青春。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.25,0:11:33.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,HARRIS: Oscar, you talk as if you're an old man.\N哈裡斯：奧斯卡，你說這話感覺你是一個老人。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.43,0:11:35.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am. I'll do anything to regain my lost youth\N我是，我將努力找回所逝去的青春
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.78,0:11:38.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,except take up exercise or get up early in the morning.\N除了鍛煉或早起
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.00,0:11:41.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Waiter! Waiter, where’s that champagne?\N侍者！侍者，我們點香檳呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.91,0:11:43.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,MAN: Ah, thank you. Here we are.\N男人：啊。謝謝你，我們在這。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.81,0:12:07.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Good evening, sir. -Hello, Arthur.\N-晚上好，先生。 -好。阿瑟。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.68,0:12:10.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oscar! You said you'll be in for lunch.\N奧斯卡，你說過午飯時回來的。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.60,0:12:13.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I had a meeting with my publisher.\N是的，我會見了我的出版人。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.82,0:12:15.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The children have been asking for you.\N孩子們一直在問你。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.34,0:12:16.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OSCAR: Oh.\N奧斯卡：哦。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.95,0:12:19.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They refuse to go to sleep until you tell them a story.\N你不回來給他們講故事，他們就不睡覺。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.26,0:12:21.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, very well.\N哦，好吧。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.56,0:12:26.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,BOYS: Daddy! Daddy!\N男孩們：爸爸！爸爸！
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.18,0:12:28.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, what's all this about your not sleeping?\N你們怎麼都不睡啊？
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.87,0:12:30.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We want you to tell us a story.\N我們想讓你講故事。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.22,0:12:32.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.\N我知道了，
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.92,0:12:34.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, now, what shall I tell you tonight about?\N那麼，今晚上講個什麼呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.62,0:12:35.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not too long, Oscar.\N別太長了，奧斯卡。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.79,0:12:38.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Giants or dragons?\N巨人或者怪龍？
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.19,0:12:41.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You told us the story about giants last night.\N您昨天晚上講的是巨人。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.76,0:12:45.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, have I told you the story about the Happy Prince?\N那麼，我給你們講過快樂王子的故事嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.24,0:12:46.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.\N不
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.46,0:12:50.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,High above the city on a tall column\N在城市聳立著高柱上
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.29,0:12:53.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,stood the statue of the Happy Prince.\N站著快樂王子的塑像。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.68,0:12:57.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was gilded all over with thin leaves of fine gold.\N他渾身鍍有薄薄一層精致的金箔。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.95,0:13:02.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For eyes he had two bright sapphires\N他有兩只像藍寶石一樣的眼睛
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.25,0:13:05.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and a large red ruby glowed on his sword hilt.\N他劍柄上鑲嵌的紅寶石閃閃發光。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.61,0:13:09.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was as beautiful as a weather cock.\N他像風向標一樣美麗。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.84,0:13:18.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir?\N您是？先生，
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.88,0:13:20.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Oscar Wilde?\N王爾德先生在家嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.66,0:13:22.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know that he's at home, sir.\N我不知道，先生
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.80,0:13:24.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah. My name is Wood.\N啊。我是伍德。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.45,0:13:25.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Wood, sir? -Yes.\N-您是伍德？  -是的
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.02,0:13:27.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a friend of Lord Alfred Douglas.\N我是阿爾弗雷德 道格拉斯爵士的朋友。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.89,0:13:30.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I see, sir. Would you step inside, sir?\N哦，我知道了，您請進屋吧，先生？
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.02,0:13:34.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll enquire if Mr. Wilde will see you, sir.\N我去問一下，王爾德能否見您，先生。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.16,0:13:36.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Dear little swallow," said the prince.\N“可愛的小麻雀”王子說。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.60,0:13:40.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"You tell me marvelous things,\N“請告訴我一些不可思議的事情，
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.43,0:13:44.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"but more marvelous than anything\N“最不可思議的事情是
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.82,0:13:47.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"is the suffering of men and women."\N“男人們和女人們正在受苦。”
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.61,0:13:55.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, sir.There's a person to see you, sir.\N對不起，有位先生來看您。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.66,0:13:56.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very well.\N好吧。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.36,0:14:08.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-He gave his name as Wood, sir.  -Wood?\N-他說他名叫伍德。 -伍德？
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.97,0:14:10.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Said he was a friend of Lord Alfred's , sir.\N並說他是阿爾弗雷德勳爵的朋友。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.98,0:14:11.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I see.\N哦，我知道了。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.02,0:14:13.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's in the front room, sir.\N他在客廳等候，先生。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.20,0:14:14.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Arthur.\N謝謝，阿瑟。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.59,0:14:18.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Wood?\N伍德先生？
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.38,0:14:22.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right, sir.\N正是，先生。\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.42,0:14:26.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh. Very delicate. Very delicate indeed.\N噢，太精致了，真的很精致。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.64,0:14:28.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand you are a friend of Lord Alfred's.\N您是阿爾弗雷德爵士的朋友？
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.95,0:14:32.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, well, I suppose you might say that, sir, yes.\N恩,我猜您會這麼說,先生,是的.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.04,0:14:34.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A very friendly gentleman, His Lordship, sir, very friendly.\N一個非常友善的人,爵士,他是非常友善的.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.69,0:14:36.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, he didn't mention you, Mr. Wood, but...\N伍德先生,他可沒有提及過您...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.78,0:14:38.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, Alfred Wood, sir.\N哈,阿爾弗雷德 伍德,先生
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.96,0:14:41.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Same name as His Lordship, sir.\N我和爵士同名
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.14,0:14:42.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm no lord, of course, sir,\N我當然沒有爵士頭銜,先生,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.83,0:14:45.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but as a poet like yourself might say, "What's in a name?"\N但正如您自己的詩句中所說“什麼是名頭？”
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.92,0:14:48.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cognac, Mr. Wood?\N白蘭地，伍德先生？
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.23,0:14:49.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, sir.\N謝謝您
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.06,0:14:51.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You knew Lord Alfred at Oxford?\N您知道阿爾弗雷德爵士在牛津的事情嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.89,0:14:54.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, not exactly at Oxford, sir.\N不是特別清楚，先生
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.71,0:14:56.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, sir, not in the way that you might mean.\N不，先生，不是你指的那方面的事。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.72,0:14:59.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I used to do odd jobs for His Lordship.\N我曾經給爵士做一些特別的工作
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.68,0:15:01.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, very kind he was to me, sir. Yes.\N他對我很好，先生，是的。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.81,0:15:04.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A gentleman like yourself, sir, in every particular.\N和您一樣的紳士，一模一樣。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.12,0:15:07.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, sir. Well, I'm very glad to meet any friend of Bosie's.\N謝謝，我很樂意見波西的朋友
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.08,0:15:08.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bosie?\N波西？
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.21,0:15:09.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.\N哦
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.38,0:15:11.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, of course, sir.\N當然了，先生
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.83,0:15:19.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your health, sir.\N祝你健康
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.70,0:15:31.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very fine brandy this, sir. Drives the cold from the bones.\N很好的白蘭地，先生，一下子暖和起來了。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.63,0:15:37.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I, uh...\N那麼，我，恩。。。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.02,0:15:40.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't beat about the bush, sir, as the saying goes.\N我就不兜圈子了，先生，正如您說的
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.38,0:15:50.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quite by accident, sir, I assure you, I a...\N非常偶然的，先生，我向您保證，我 一個。。。。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.38,0:15:54.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I came across that letter from you to Lord Alfred Douglas.\N我發現了一封您寫給道格拉斯爵士的信
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.04,0:15:58.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very beautiful letter, if I might say so, sir.\N一封非常漂亮的信，請允許我這麼說，先生。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.39,0:16:01.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only I think that perhaps\N我認為，可能其中
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.30,0:16:05.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there are parts that could be "misconstrued," I think is the word, sir.\N有些部分，在語句上會引起“誤會”，先生
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.35,0:16:07.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How did you come by this?\N你是怎麼得到它的？
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.57,0:16:09.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, yes, well, I used to...\N啊。是的，我曾經。。。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.18,0:16:11.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Used to press Lord Alfred's clothes.\N給阿爾弗雷德爵士熨燙衣物。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.23,0:16:13.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very particular about his clothes, sir.\N是那種非常特殊的衣物，先生。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.71,0:16:14.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As well you may know.\N您知道的。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.71,0:16:18.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I, uh, found it in one of his pockets.\N我，恩，我在他口袋裡發現它的
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.06,0:16:21.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you asking me to purchase my own work, Mr. Wood?\N伍德先生，你是想讓我贖回我自己的作品嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.41,0:16:24.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, sir, I... Come, sir, that's not very sound economics.\N那麼，先生，我。。。說吧，這也沒什麼不好意思的。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.67,0:16:28.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I've already been offered 60pound for it, sir.\N先生，我已經為它付了60英鎊。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.37,0:16:31.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I suggest that you sell it at once.\N那我建議你還是馬上把他賣給別人吧。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.46,0:16:34.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I myself have seldom been offered so much\N我自己不會花這麼多錢
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.16,0:16:36.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for a prose work of that length.\N為了這麼一篇小散文。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.08,0:16:39.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You take the letter, sir.\N那你還是把信拿回去吧。先生。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.86,0:16:42.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was stupid of me to try and rent you.\N我真愚蠢，和您討價還價。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.08,0:16:44.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The thing is, sir, that I'm desperate for money and...\N可事實上，我已經在經濟上很拮據了
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.96,0:16:47.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A hungry man gets driven to do stupid things.\N一個饑餓的人干出這樣的傻事。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.26,0:16:49.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, would you like a ham sandwich?\N哦，你需要一個火腿三明治嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.09,0:16:50.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now you've making fun of me, sir.\N先生，你拿我取笑了。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.44,0:16:52.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the contrary, Mr. Wood.\N相反，伍德先生。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.09,0:16:54.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've doing remarkably well yourself.\N你已經表現的非常好。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.49,0:16:55.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I think I'll be going now, sir.\N我想我該走了，先生。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.01,0:16:58.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no, no, no. Please stay and finish your drink.\N不不不，請再呆一會，喝完酒再走。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.84,0:16:59.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's very kind of you.\N您真是太好了。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.06,0:17:07.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're a very poor criminal, Mr. Wood, if I may say so.\N伍德先生，你是個可憐的罪犯，我能這麼說吧。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.20,0:17:12.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The fact is I came to London to look for some work.\N實際上，我是到倫敦找工作的。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.24,0:17:15.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, work, Mr. Wood, is the curse of the drinking classes.\N啊，伍德先生，工作，它是酒徒們的咒語。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.16,0:17:21.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The secret of maintaining youth\N保持青春的秘訣是
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.73,0:17:27.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is an inordinate passion for pleasure.\N盡情享受快樂。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.70,0:17:36.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,40pounds, sir?\N40英鎊,先生?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.53,0:17:39.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going out to dine in a moment. Perhaps you shoud not care to join me.\N我一會兒要去吃晚餐,也許你不介意和我一起.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.62,0:17:41.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that's very kind of you, sir.\N您真是太客氣了,先生.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.93,0:17:43.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a fascinating charm\N你的犯罪意識裡有一種
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.45,0:17:47.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,about your halfhearted criminal tendencies, Mr. Wood.\N不刻意的迷人的魅力,伍德先生.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.32,0:17:51.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I suspect that you lead a wonderfully wicked life.\N我猜想你一定過著非常的邪惡生活。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.41,0:17:53.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, well, there's good and bad in all of us, sir.\N啊，我們每個人都有好的一面和壞的一面。\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.72,0:17:55.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Wood, you're a born philosopher.\N伍德先生，您是一個天生的哲學家。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.46,0:17:57.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure we shall get along extremely well.\N我保證我們一定會聊得很投機。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.25,0:17:58.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your health, sir.\N祝您健康，先生。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.09,0:18:16.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shall I serve dinner, madam?\N夫人，需要我布置晚餐嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.18,0:18:20.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't understand it. I'm sure Mr. Wilde said\N我真不明白了，我肯定王爾德先生說過
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.27,0:18:22.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he would be in for dinner.\N他將回來吃晚餐
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.05,0:18:24.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, perhaps he's been detained on business, madam.\N也許他被生意上的事耽擱了，夫人。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.01,0:18:26.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.\N是的
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.27,0:18:27.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shall we wait?\N我們等他嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.19,0:18:30.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, Arthur, I'll dine alone.\N不了，阿瑟，我自己一個人吃吧。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.76,0:18:31.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very well, madam.\N好的，夫人。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.22,0:19:00.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bosie, you're nearly an hour late.\N波西，你晚了一個小時。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.05,0:19:00.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I know.\N我知道。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.14,0:19:03.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I know what that face means.\N噢，我知道你那張臉意味著什麼。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.75,0:19:06.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It usually heralds an unpleasant scene.\N一般來說，它意味著不高興的場景。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.31,0:19:08.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would be nice if it could be avoided.\N如果能避免將會好起來
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.19,0:19:10.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm in a singularly good mood.\N我的心情將會非常好起來。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.06,0:19:12.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Are you?  -I was.\N-你是嗎？  -我是。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.32,0:19:15.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No doubt, having entertained your friend at the Savoy last night.\N毫無疑問，你昨晚肯定在薩伏伊酒店讓你的朋友很高興。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.85,0:19:17.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean Mr. Wood?\N你是說伍德先生？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.80,0:19:20.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really, Oscar, have you no sense of propriety?\N真的，奧斯卡，你就不能說得體一點嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.24,0:19:21.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The man is a valet.\N那人是個男僕。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.46,0:19:23.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A very amusing valet.\N一個非常有趣的男僕。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.72,0:19:27.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank heavens, Bosie, I am not inhibited by your sense of class.\N天吶，波西，我受不了你的階級優越感。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.77,0:19:29.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So it seems.\N看來是的。\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.51,0:19:30.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, he was your friend.\N不管怎樣，他曾是你的朋友。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.77,0:19:33.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hardly knew the man.\N我幾乎不熟悉他。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.73,0:19:35.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not the impression that he gave to me.\N他沒有給我留下什麼印象。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.65,0:19:37.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,WAITER: Good morning, My Lord.\N侍者：上午好，大人。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.17,0:19:38.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did he want anyway?\N他到底想要什麼？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.87,0:19:40.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Money. What do the poor usually want?\N錢。窮人們都想要的？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.87,0:19:42.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you like to order now, My Lord?\N您想點餐嗎？大人。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.39,0:19:43.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you gave it to him?\N那你給他了？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.57,0:19:47.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For a valuable piece of property.\N一大筆錢。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.40,0:19:49.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A letter I wrote you at Oxford.\N你在牛津時我給你寫的信。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.79,0:19:51.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,WAITER: May I recommend the lobster, My Lord?\N侍者：大人。我能向您推薦龍蝦嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.80,0:19:55.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-I'll have the sole meuniere. -Very good.\N-我想要單獨裹面粉的。  -好的。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.06,0:19:58.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you mean he blackmailed you?\N你是說他敲詐你了？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.67,0:20:02.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leaving that letter around for anyone to find was not only careless of you,\N把那封信放到任何人可以得到它的地方，這不僅僅是你的粗心大意，
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.76,0:20:04.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but singularly lacking in respect\N而是非常缺乏尊重
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.85,0:20:08.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for something that I'd hoped was private and personal.\N那可是我希望保留的隱私
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.25,0:20:11.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Waiter, bring some champagne right away.\N侍者，來瓶香檳，快點。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.55,0:20:12.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very good, My Lord.\N好的，大人。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.56,0:20:17.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's seem, Bosie, that I am forever paying\N你看，波西，我一直為你的
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.04,0:20:20.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for your indiscretions and your extravagances.\N輕率和奢侈支付。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.56,0:20:22.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Money, is that all you ever think of?\N錢，這不是你以前一直想的嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.26,0:20:24.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, when I was young I thought money was everything.\N啊，在我年輕時，認為金錢萬能。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.96,0:20:26.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that I'm older I know that it is.\N現在我老了，還是這麼想。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.70,0:20:28.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My God, Oscar, you've never satisfied.\N上帝，奧斯卡，你從來沒有滿足過。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.83,0:20:29.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have a successful book out,\N你的書賣得很成功，
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.96,0:20:31.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a play running in the West End...\N一部在西區（倫敦富人區）劇院演出的劇作。。。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.18,0:20:33.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Playing to packed houses of creditors.\N可舞台下卻擠滿了我的債主。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.49,0:20:36.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you any idea how much money I've spent since we've been together?\N你知道，自從你我在一起，我花了多少錢嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.36,0:20:39.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you've kept an account.\N我想你有一個賬單。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.32,0:20:43.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Luncheon every day here, dinner at the Savoy, supper at...\N午餐在這裡，晚餐在薩伏伊，夜宵在。。。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.63,0:20:45.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Oh, look what you've done.  -I'm sorry, sir.\N-噢，你怎麼回事。 -對不起，大人。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.33,0:20:46.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Please.  -Oh, go away, stop fussing.\N-請。  -走開吧，別再添亂了。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.89,0:20:50.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And always the best champagne\N而且總是上等香檳
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.33,0:20:52.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because you have a very delicate palate.\N因為你的口味很刁。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.55,0:20:55.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bosie, you seem to think that you have a right to live at my expense\N波西，你有權靠我的花費過著
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.90,0:20:59.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in a profuse luxury to which you have never been accustomed.\N毫不吝惜的奢侈，那種你從未習慣的生活。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.86,0:21:03.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I pay your hotel bills, your tailor's bill,\N我付了你的旅館賬單，你的裁縫賬單，
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.34,0:21:04.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,your gambling debts.\N還有你的賭債。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.48,0:21:09.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You demand without grace and you receive without thanks.\N你不客氣地索取，卻對獲得毫無感激。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.40,0:21:12.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you finished?\N你有完沒完？
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.23,0:21:18.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now tell me honestly, Oscar. What did you expect, hmm?\N說真的，奧斯卡，你到底想要什麼？
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.18,0:21:20.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you think I was some common street Arab\N你是不是把我當成普通街頭的流浪兒
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.62,0:21:22.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to be bought with cheap trinkets\N可以被廉價的小玩意收買
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.28,0:21:25.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and an occasional supper in some Soho restaurant?\N或者感念你偶爾在蘇荷區（倫敦小吃街）的飯館請我幾頓晚餐？
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.54,0:21:27.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've given you my friendship for two years, Oscar.\N奧斯卡，兩年來，我付出了我的友誼。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.89,0:21:31.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've admired your genius, laughed at your jokes, flattered your vanity.\N我傾慕你的天才，會意你的笑話，迎合你的虛榮。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.37,0:21:34.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And now you question the price of such a friendship.\N而現在你卻質疑這種友誼的價錢。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.81,0:21:36.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It isn't worthy of you, Oscar.\N為你不值得，奧斯卡。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.05,0:21:50.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,給我的波西\N奧斯卡贈\N於1893年聖誕
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.90,0:22:21.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Good evening, Mr. Wilde.  -Evening, William.\N-晚上好，王爾德先生。  -好，威廉。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.29,0:22:23.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sydney.\N西德尼。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.12,0:22:25.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, sir.\N在，先生。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.43,0:22:27.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Good evening, Mr. Wilde. -Good evening.\N-晚上好，王爾德先生。  -好。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.52,0:22:31.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to take this to this address.\N我想讓你把它送到這個地址。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.43,0:22:33.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just around the corner.\N它離這不遠。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.13,0:22:37.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Straight away, hmm?  -Right away, sir.\N-直接去，好吧?  -馬上，先生。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.62,0:22:42.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, Robbie.\N你好，羅比。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.18,0:22:44.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, Oscar.\N你好，奧斯卡。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.97,0:22:46.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What will you have?\N喝點什麼？
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.19,0:22:48.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Brandy, and a large one.\N白蘭地，大杯的。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.71,0:22:50.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,John. A large brandy.\N約翰，大杯白蘭地。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.15,0:22:53.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give me a cigarette, there's a dear fellow.\N給我根煙吧，伙計。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.50,0:22:54.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I seem to have left mine at home.\N我好像把它落在家了。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.28,0:22:56.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-What?  -A cigarette.\N-什麼？  -來根煙。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.85,0:22:57.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yes, of course.\N哦，當然可以。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.42,0:23:00.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.\N謝謝
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.90,0:23:11.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Oscar?  Are you not well?\N怎麼了，奧斯卡，不舒服嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.65,0:23:13.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, just very tired, that's all.\N沒有，就是有點累。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.48,0:23:15.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your brandy, sir.\N您的白蘭地，先生。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.48,0:23:18.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.\N謝謝
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.48,0:23:25.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oscar, did you know that some of the club members\N奧斯卡，你知道嗎？俱樂部的一些會員
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.75,0:23:27.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,have approached the Committee to get you to resign?\N想讓委員會勸你退會？
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.92,0:23:29.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I hope not. I shall have to find somewhere else\N我可不希望，我還想找個地方
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.71,0:23:31.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to sleep in the afternoons.\N在下午睡一覺。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.45,0:23:33.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you any idea how much people are talking about you\N你知道別人都在談論你嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.45,0:23:34.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or what they are saying?\N想知道他們都說了些什麼嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.58,0:23:36.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I adore scandal about other people,\N我非常想知道別人的緋聞，
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.89,0:23:39.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but about myself I find it extremely dull.\N而我自己的，確是很枯燥的。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.54,0:23:41.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It hasn't the charm of novelty.\N它沒什麼新奇的魅力。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.55,0:23:44.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think you'll find this gossip dull.\N我不覺得這些謠言很無聊枯燥。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.94,0:23:47.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Robbie, are you being solicitous about my welfare?\N羅比，你能讓我清淨一會嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.73,0:23:49.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is very impertinent of you.\N你這樣很無理。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.51,0:23:50.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't mean to be.\N我不是這個意思。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.03,0:23:53.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oscar, I realize that much of your extravagant behavior\N奧斯卡，我覺得你有很多過份的舉動
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.04,0:23:56.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is done purely for effect. You've an artist.\N純粹是為了效果，因你是一個藝術家。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.30,0:23:58.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The public expects you to be different.\N但公眾希望你等夠表現不同。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.39,0:24:01.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you've no longer an ascetic young poet just down from Oxford.\N你已經不是一個從牛津來的，苦兮兮的年輕詩人。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.44,0:24:03.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Relax.  -You're a highly successful playwrighter\N-行了吧。  -你現在是一個很成功的作家
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.70,0:24:05.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,at the peak of your career.\N正處在事業頂峰。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.44,0:24:08.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You dine with royalty. You mix in the highest social circles.\N你和皇室一起用晚宴，你和社會上層圈子打交道。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.83,0:24:10.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah.\N啊
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.62,0:24:12.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're walking along a precipice, Oscar.\N你現在正走在懸崖邊上，奧斯卡。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.14,0:24:14.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just as long as you continue to play court jester,\N只要你繼續為宮廷提供娛樂，
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.75,0:24:16.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,society will accept you.\N（上流）社交界就會接受你。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.10,0:24:18.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But tax their tolerance too far\N但如果你向他們征收更多的容忍
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.71,0:24:20.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and they'll send you crashing from the heights\N那他們將把你從高處徹底擊碎
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.67,0:24:22.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-to the depths of obscurity.  -Oh, really.\N-把我打回默默無聞的深淵。  -哦，真的。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.72,0:24:25.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A halo doesn't have to fall very far, Oscar, to become a noose.\N光環不久就會變成套索落下，奧斯卡。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.55,0:24:27.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really, Robbie, this all very tedious.\N真的，羅比，這也太無聊了。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.33,0:24:29.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just tell me one thing.\N你只要告訴我一件事。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.46,0:24:32.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These stories I hear about you.\N那些我聽到的關於你的緋聞
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.77,0:24:34.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There isn't any truth in them, is there?\N沒有一點是真的，是不是？
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.56,0:24:35.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As I don't know what the stories are,\N我都不這道那些緋聞是什麼，
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.95,0:24:37.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm hardly in a position to answer you.\N我不知該如何回答你。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.30,0:24:39.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They say that you...\N他們說你。。。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.12,0:24:43.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're being blackmailed because of your association with Bosie.\N你因和波西交往而被人敲詐。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.43,0:24:48.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That you consort with criminals, stable boys.\N你和罪犯打交道，那個馬夫。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.96,0:24:54.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This sounds all very exciting and intriguing.\N這聽起來又刺激又有趣。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.27,0:24:55.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do go on.\N接著說。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.71,0:24:57.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just want to hear you tell me it isn't true.\N我只想聽你說這不是真的。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.10,0:25:02.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Robbie,\N羅比，
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.23,0:25:06.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm deeply hurt that you use our friendship to pry into my private life.\N你有我們的友誼來刺探我個人的生活，對此我感到很受傷。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.68,0:25:12.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you were a gentleman. I now see that you are not.\N我過去認為你是一個紳士，現在我不這麼認為。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.24,0:25:13.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just want to hear you deny it, Oscar.\N我只想聽你否認它，奧斯卡。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.03,0:25:16.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must think what you will, Robbie.\N你愛怎麼想就怎麼想，羅比。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.64,0:25:18.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Wood to see you, sir.\N先生，有位伍德先生想見您。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.86,0:25:19.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.\N謝謝你。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.30,0:25:30.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Robbie, because I'm very fond of you\N羅比，因為我很喜歡你
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.79,0:25:32.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I shall forget everything you've said tonight.\N我將忘掉剛才你跟我說的一切。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.61,0:25:34.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good night.\N晚安
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.35,0:25:36.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good night.\N晚安
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.06,0:25:41.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, Oscar.\N你好，奧斯卡。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.80,0:25:47.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lovely club you've got here.\N您的這個俱樂部很不錯啊。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.63,0:25:50.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-I like that.\N-我喜歡它。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.15,0:25:51.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like some champagne tonight.\N我今晚想喝點香檳。\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.39,0:26:11.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you shouldn't have bothered.\N哦，進來吧。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.70,0:26:14.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must eat something.\N你得吃點東西了。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.01,0:26:20.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right?\N好吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.79,0:26:22.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, I've eaten in all of the best restaurants in Europe\N你知道，我吃遍了全歐洲最好的餐館
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.40,0:26:24.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I've never tasted anything like your sweetbreads.\N沒有一家能做出你這樣好吃的甜面包。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.49,0:26:26.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's the wine?\N紅酒呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.58,0:26:28.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They didn't deliver any this week.\N這周酒商沒有送來。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.02,0:26:31.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For heaven's sake, why not?\N天吶，為什麼？
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.63,0:26:34.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps the fact that we owe the wine merchant 85 pounds\N事實上，我們已經欠了酒商85英鎊。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.63,0:26:36.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,might have something to do with it.\N這件事該認真對待了。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.89,0:26:39.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've living on credit, Oscar, and that can't go on much longer.\N我在靠信用過活，奧斯卡，再也不能這樣下去了。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.68,0:26:43.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, if I can finish this play, everything will be all right.\N等我這部戲寫完，一切都會解決的。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.42,0:26:47.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that's Bosie, tell him I'm not at home.\N如果是波西，告訴她我不在家。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.91,0:26:53.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,QUEENSBERRY: I wish to see Mr. Oscar Wilde.\N昆斯博裡：我希望見到奧斯卡 王爾德先生。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.56,0:26:55.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ARTHUR: I'm sorry, sir, but Mr. Wilde is not at home.\N阿瑟：對不起，先生，王爾德先生不在家。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.61,0:26:56.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'm sorry, but I demand to see him.\N那就對不起了，我必須要見到他。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.87,0:26:57.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't go in there, sir.\N先生，你不能進去。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.83,0:26:59.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you please, sir.\N客氣點，先生。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.22,0:27:00.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wilde, I want to have a word with you. Sit down. \N王爾德，我要跟你說幾句話，你坐下。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.79,0:27:05.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Lord Queensberry. It's all right, Arthur, you can go.\N好吧，昆斯博裡侯爵，可以，阿瑟，你們走吧。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.36,0:27:08.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems the peerage don't have a monopoly of good manners.\N看來，禮貌也並不是貴族的專利。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.40,0:27:10.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To hell with good manners, sir.\N讓禮貌見鬼去吧，先生
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.28,0:27:12.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What I have to say to you has very little to do with good manners.\N我不得不跟你說的，與禮貌毫無關系。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.97,0:27:15.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed? And I presume you've brought your ugly friend\N事實上，我猜你帶來的丑陋朋友
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.32,0:27:16.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to lend you moral support.\N已經給你帶來道義上的支持。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.02,0:27:19.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When it comes to morals, I have all the support I need,\N說到道義，我已經得到了我需要的各種支持，
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.24,0:27:21.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,thank you very much.\N非常感謝您。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.20,0:27:23.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've seldom come across anybody in whom the moral sense was dominant\N我很少對那些有明顯的
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.51,0:27:27.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who was not heartless, cruel, vindictive and completely lacking\N無情，殘忍，凶惡相貌的人產生道德感，並認為他們完全缺少
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.38,0:27:29.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in the smallest sense of humanity, Lord Queensberry.\N最起碼的人性，昆斯博裡侯爵。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.47,0:27:32.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Personally, I've sooner have 50 unnatural vices\N就個人而言，我將馬上擁有50個後天的惡習
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.78,0:27:34.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,than one unnatural virtue.\N而不是一個天生的美德。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.47,0:27:37.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I can well believe that. Now, you listen to me, sir.\N是的，我非常相信這點。現在，你給我聽好了，先生。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.65,0:27:39.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I presume you have come to make a speech.\N我猜你是來做一個演講的。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.30,0:27:41.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If so, I hope it's a short one because I have work to do.\N如果那樣，我希望您快點，因我還有工作要做。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.83,0:27:46.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wilde.\N王爾德。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.97,0:27:49.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wilde.\N王爾德。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.06,0:27:54.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've come here today to protest against\N我今天來這裡是向你抗議，反對
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.97,0:27:57.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,your disgusting relationship with my son.\N你和我兒子之間的令人作嘔的關系。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.76,0:28:06.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is a revolting and slanderous statement,\N這是令人厭惡和造謠中傷的陳述，
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.77,0:28:08.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I demand an apology.\N我要你道歉。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.59,0:28:10.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I refuse to apologize.\N我拒絕道歉。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.08,0:28:15.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I refuse to apologize for saying something which is common knowledge\N我拒絕道歉，因為我說的這些話會讓
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.30,0:28:17.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to every cab driver and messenger boy in London.\N倫敦任何一個馬車夫或送信童都有同感。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.78,0:28:19.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Queensberry, are you seriously suggesting that\N昆斯博裡侯爵，你難道不是認真地暗示
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.65,0:28:21.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there is improper conduct between your son and myself?\N你兒子和我之間有不正當的關系嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.78,0:28:25.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I do not say that you are.\N我沒有說你是這樣的。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.31,0:28:28.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I say that you look it, which is just as bad.\N我說你要看到，這會壞到什麼地步。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.31,0:28:29.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'll tell you this.\N但我要告訴你這些。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.70,0:28:33.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I catch you two again together,\N如果我再看到你兩人在一起，
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.23,0:28:37.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I shall take a whip to you, sir, and I shall thrash you to the ground.\N我將拿鞭子抽你，直到把你抽倒在地上。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.19,0:28:44.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see that when it comes to fighting,\N要打架就來吧，
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.50,0:28:47.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you choose to ignore the Queensberry rules.\N你可以選擇不顧及你的昆斯博裡規則（拳擊規則，倒地15秒認輸）
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.55,0:28:49.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Yes, well, I give you fair warning.  -And I give you fair warning.\N-是的，我給你公平的警告。  -我也要給你公平的警告。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.68,0:28:51.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you've not out of my house in two minutes, I shall throw you out.\N如果你兩分鍾內不離開我的房間，我將把你扔出去。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.77,0:28:53.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I refuse to leave until I've had my say.\N我不說完我不會離開的。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.29,0:28:55.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the contrary, sir, you are leaving now.\N正相反，先生，現在你就給我離開。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.29,0:28:57.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hit him! Hit him!\N揍他！揍他！
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.95,0:29:04.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Arthur, open the door! This gentleman is leaving.\N阿瑟，開門，這位先生要出去。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.35,0:29:05.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gladly, sir.\N好的，先生。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.74,0:29:09.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This, Arthur, is the Marquis of Queensberry.\N這位，阿瑟，是昆斯博裡第八代侯爵。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.96,0:29:12.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The most infamous brute in London and you've never to let him in my house again.\N這個倫敦最臭名昭著的畜生，你不能讓他再進我的家門。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.75,0:29:14.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Is that clear?   -Perfectly, sir.\N-明白了嗎？  -完全明白，先生。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.84,0:29:16.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now get out.\N現在滾吧。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.36,0:29:17.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very well.\N非常好。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.84,0:29:19.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you'll regret this, I promise you.\N我保證你會後悔的。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.93,0:29:21.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I promise you.\N我發誓
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.80,0:29:26.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go back to your room this instant.\N馬上會回你們的房間。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.67,0:29:29.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will that be all, sir?\N這就結束了吧？先生。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.41,0:29:30.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope so, Arthur.\N我希望是，阿瑟。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.21,0:29:45.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, this has got to stop.\N現在，該阻止這些事情再發生了。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.61,0:29:49.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are the only one who can stop it, Oscar.\N你是唯一能阻止這些事情的人，奧斯卡。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.48,0:29:51.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My God, am I not allowed to get on with my work in peace?\N上帝啊，我到底能不能安靜地工作?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.00,0:29:53.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What with creditors knocking at the door\N如果是債主敲門怎麼辦
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.66,0:29:55.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and Bosie dropping in as if this was some sort of club.\N如果是波西或者俱樂部其他人拜訪怎麼辦。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.57,0:29:58.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And now this coarse brute with his hired pugilists.\N而現在是那些粗鄙的惡棍和他所雇傭的打手。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.62,0:30:01.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can stand brute force, but brute reason is quite intolerable.\N我能抵抗畜生的力量，但是畜生的理智卻讓人不能忍受。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.71,0:30:02.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's like hitting below the intellect.\N就像打擊弱智的人。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.89,0:30:10.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oscar, I beg of you to give up this friendship with Bosie.\N奧斯卡，我希望你放棄和波西的友誼。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.02,0:30:14.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not for me, but for your own sake.\N不是為了我，而是為你自己。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.20,0:30:16.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He takes up too much of your time,\N他占用了你太多的時間，
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.24,0:30:18.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,demands too much of your emotions.\N剝奪了你太多的情感。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.33,0:30:20.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know.\N我知道。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.77,0:30:25.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The truth is the boy has a strange fascination for me\N事實上，這男孩對我有奇怪的幻想
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.21,0:30:28.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that I can't get free of.\N而我又不能拋棄他。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.39,0:30:34.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He needs you more than you need him.\N他對你的要求多於你對他的。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.61,0:30:37.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He needs you because he is weak and conceited.\N它需要你，因為他的脆弱和自負。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.61,0:30:40.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you give him a stature he could never acquire alone.\N而你給了他一個人永遠達不到的聲望。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.18,0:30:42.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And he will go on taking and taking until there's nothing left.\N他會一直拿走它，直到它什麼都沒剩下。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.92,0:30:44.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He'll destroy you, Oscar.\N他會毀了你，奧斯卡。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.36,0:30:48.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I married you,\N當我嫁給你時，
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.32,0:30:51.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't believe it was possible to love anybody more than I loved you.\N我不相信還有人比我更愛你。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.28,0:30:57.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I still love you, darling.\N我一直愛你，親愛的。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.94,0:31:01.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To me you are higher and greater than any man in the world.\N對我來說，你是世界上最高尚最偉大的男人。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.72,0:31:02.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Help me, Constance.\N幫幫我吧，康斯坦斯。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.60,0:31:04.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Help me.\N救我。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.73,0:31:10.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why not go away for a little while?\N為何不暫時離開這一切呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.69,0:31:13.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At least until you have finished your play.\N至少等到你寫完你的劇本。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.48,0:31:15.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it will give you a chance to think more clearly.\N也許，它會給你一個機會去想清楚這些。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.91,0:31:17.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I may.\N是的，我會的。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.18,0:31:22.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You always liked the sea. Why not go down to Brighton?\N你一直喜歡大海，為什麼不去一趟布萊頓（英格蘭西部港口）呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.48,0:31:24.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It should be very quiet at this time of year.\N它將是這年中非常平靜的時候。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.97,0:31:28.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a wonderful idea, Constance,\N好主意，康斯坦斯，
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.06,0:31:32.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but we've hardly enough money to pay the tradesmen, let alone hotel bills.\N但是我們幾乎沒有足夠錢來支付那些商人，更不用說旅館賬單。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.23,0:31:35.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't touched my father's allowance for some months.\N我已經有幾個月沒有動用過我父親給我的津貼。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.24,0:31:36.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-It isn't very much, I'm afraid.   -No, no, Constance.\N-它雖然不多，我恐怕。  -不，不，康斯坦斯。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.89,0:31:38.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please. Please.\N放心，放心。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.33,0:31:46.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I love you.\N我愛你。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.68,0:31:48.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I love you.\N我愛你。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.18,0:32:55.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Goodness Lordy, Mr. Wilde, wherever have you been?\N上帝啊，王爾德先生，你去哪裡了？
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.23,0:32:57.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been conversing with the elements, Mrs. Burgess.\N我去和大自然談了會兒話，伯傑斯夫人。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.54,0:32:59.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, goodness me, you've soaked to the skin.\N哦，天吶，您都濕透了。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.36,0:33:01.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listening to the wisdom of the sea, Mrs. B.\N我聽到了大海的智慧，伯傑斯夫人。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.98,0:33:03.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Out all night in weather like this.\N  這個天氣，你居然在外頭呆了一晚上
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.80,0:33:06.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, you come upstairs and we'll get those wet clothes off\N現在趕緊上樓，把濕衣服換下來
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.28,0:33:07.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-before you catch your death.   -It's all here.\N-在你將凍死之前。   -它都裝在這裡了。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.72,0:33:09.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Every word and every epigram, Mrs. Burgess.\N每一個單詞和每一個警句，伯傑斯夫人。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.46,0:33:11.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I'm very glad, Mr. Wilde, but do come on.\N哦，我很高興，王爾德先生，但要快點脫。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.16,0:33:12.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Every move and every curtain.\N每一次轉換和每一次啟幕。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.86,0:33:14.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all here.\N都裝在這裡了。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.20,0:33:16.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the important thing is who is Ernest.\N重要的是，誰是歐內斯特。\N(此時王爾德正在構思劇本《不可兒戲》，歐內斯特是劇中人物）
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.21,0:33:17.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yes, that will be nice.\N哦，是的，這就好了。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.34,0:33:18.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ernest and his little aunt...\N歐內斯特和他的小姑母。。。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.90,0:33:21.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But upstairs now, like a good boy, please, Mr. Wilde.\N快上樓，像個乖孩子，王爾德先生。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.91,0:33:26.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've very kind, Mrs. Burgess.\N您太善良了，伯傑斯夫人。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.65,0:33:30.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, if we can't show a little kindness on this earth,\N在這個世界上，如果我們再不表現出一點善良，
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.74,0:33:33.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we might as well not be here, that's the way I see it.\N那還是別在這裡生存下去了，這是就我明白的地方。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.97,0:33:37.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, you keep nice and warm.\N現在，你暖暖和和地睡個好覺。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.42,0:34:02.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure this is the right place, my dear chap?\N你能肯定是這個地方嗎？老伙計。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.43,0:34:04.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is where I brung him, sir. No mistaking him.\N是我帶他來這裡的，先生，不會有錯的。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.99,0:34:06.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Proper artistic gentleman he was.\N他就是那個風趣兒的紳士。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.91,0:34:07.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just wait here, will you?\N在這等一下吧
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.95,0:34:08.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, sir.\N行，先生。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.40,0:34:20.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning, madam.\N早上好，夫人。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.23,0:34:23.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it remotely possible you have a Mr. Oscar Wilde staying here?\N一個叫奧斯卡王爾德的先生會住在您這裡嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.93,0:34:24.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why, yes, sir.\N為什麼不會，是的，先生。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.93,0:34:27.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How extraordinary.\N太奇特了。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.63,0:34:29.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Ah, may I step inside? -Certainly, sir.\N-我能進屋嗎？  -當然，先生。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.80,0:34:32.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which is his room?\N他住哪間房？
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.02,0:34:34.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just at the top of the stairs.\N樓梯頂那間。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.59,0:34:36.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, but I'm rather you didn't disturb him, sir.\N我希望您別打擾他，先生。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.81,0:34:39.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You see, he was out all night and he's not at all well.\N你知道，他出去呆了一整夜，他現在不舒服。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.99,0:34:42.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed?\N真的？
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.73,0:34:45.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was wondering if I'd send for the doctor.\N我正在想是否送他去醫生那裡。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.56,0:34:47.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A doctor, madam, would probably prescribe\N醫生，夫人，會給他開的處方是
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.38,0:34:49.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a little less brandy in his soda.\N一小杯白蘭地加蘇打水。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.18,0:34:57.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well.\N好吧。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.79,0:35:01.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So this is where you've been hiding yourself, hmm?\N這就是你藏身的地方？
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.27,0:35:02.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bosie.\N波西。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.57,0:35:04.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really, Oscar, you are the most tedious person.\N真的，奧斯卡，你是個最乏味的人。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.23,0:35:05.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been all over Brighton.\N我找遍了布萊頓。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.75,0:35:07.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From one hotel to another,\N從一家旅館到另一家旅館，
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.10,0:35:09.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,tracking you down like some private detective.\N像私家偵探一樣搜尋你。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.54,0:35:10.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-What do you want?  -What?\N-你想干什麼？  -什麼
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.67,0:35:12.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do I want?\N我想干什麼？
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.89,0:35:15.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want a thing, I came to see you.\N我什麼都不想，我就是來看你。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.41,0:35:17.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good heavens, it's so dark in here.\N天吶，這裡也太暗了。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.38,0:35:23.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I must say you don't look any too good.\N我必須跟你說，你的氣色很不好。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.86,0:35:25.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah.\N哦。是的
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.07,0:35:26.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I've got a chill, I...\N我想我是著涼了，我。。。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.03,0:35:29.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must be out of your mind coming to a place like this.\N你必須拋開躲到這裡的想法。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.17,0:35:30.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't imagine what the food must be like.\N我不能想象你吃得這是什麼。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.65,0:35:32.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, as soon as I knew you were in Brighton,\N當然了，我一知道你到了布萊頓，
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.30,0:35:33.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I naturally went straight to The Grand.\N我就直奔大酒店。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.82,0:35:35.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally.\N自然的。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.00,0:35:38.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have a most delightful suite there overlooking the sea.\N我已經訂了一間能看到海景的最豪華的套房。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.78,0:35:42.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I shall get the bill, no doubt, in due course.\N毫無疑問，到時候，我就會收到賬單的。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.14,0:35:44.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously though, Os, I won't allow you to stay\N說正經的，我可不想讓你
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.88,0:35:47.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in this dreary little hovel another minute.\N在這種可憐的小旅館裡再多呆一分鍾。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.14,0:35:50.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, the most fascinating people are staying at The Grand.\N另外，一些奇妙的人物都呆在大酒店裡。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.28,0:35:55.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just look at this picture, really.\N看看這些畫吧，真逗。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.41,0:35:57.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bosie, can't you understand\N波西，你難道不明白
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.98,0:36:01.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that I came here to finish my play in peace and quiet?\N我來這裡是為了平和安靜地完成我的劇本（指《不可兒戲》）？
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.33,0:36:04.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was driven nearly frantic in London with you and your father.\N我在倫敦都快被你和你父親逼瘋了。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.55,0:36:07.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bosie, I've got to work.\N波西，我得工作。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.20,0:36:10.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the last person in the world to want to interfere with your work.\N我可是這個世界上最後一個想干預你的作品的人。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.12,0:36:11.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whether you mean it or not, you do.\N不論你說的是或不是，你都這樣干了。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.99,0:36:13.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you looking for?\N你在找什麼？
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.91,0:36:15.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm looking for my handkerchief. What do you think I'm looking for?\N我在找我的手帕，你以為我在找什麼？
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.30,0:36:17.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here it is, for heaven's sake.\N在這呢，天吶。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.69,0:36:19.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really, Oscar, when you are ill, you've singularly unamusing.\N真的，奧斯卡，當你病了的時候，你就更有魅力了。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.96,0:36:21.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't help being ill.\N我可不想生病。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.22,0:36:22.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you can help being a bore.\N但你卻能忍住令人厭煩。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.09,0:36:29.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this your new play?\N這就是你的新劇本？
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.66,0:36:30.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Importance of Being Earnest."\N“認真的重要性”\N（即《不可兒戲》）
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.92,0:36:35.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it's nearly finished.\N是的，它快完工了。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.28,0:36:39.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad to hear it. Poverty ill becomes you.\N我很高興聽到這些。貧窮疾病成就了你。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.58,0:36:43.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Frankly, I think you're being very unreasonable about this whole thing.\N坦率地說，我都不知道整件事情你是怎麼想的。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.33,0:36:46.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You disappear, leaving me in town without a penny piece.\N你去玩失蹤，我卻身無分文地被丟在城裡。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.85,0:36:48.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you trying to end this relationship, Oscar?\N你是想結束我倆的關系嗎？奧斯卡。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.85,0:36:50.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that what you want?\N這就是你要的？
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.51,0:36:53.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what I want. I just want to be left in peace.\N我不知道我要什麼。我只想一個人靜靜地待會兒。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.25,0:36:54.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Thank you for your company.\N“謝謝你的陪伴。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.77,0:36:56.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"It was charming while it lasted. Now kindly get out."\N“如果它能延續下去，那就太令人陶醉了。”
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.95,0:37:00.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bosie, can't you see that I'm ill and I hardly know what I'm doing?\N波西，難道你沒看到我病了，我都不知道我在干什麼？
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.74,0:37:01.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And what about me?\N那我呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.91,0:37:03.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care what you do,\N我不管你怎麼做，
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.35,0:37:04.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but as long as you go away and leave me alone.\N我只要你走開，讓我一個人待會兒。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.61,0:37:07.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean for good?\N你是說永遠嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.96,0:37:13.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It can't go on, your insane tantrums and your extravagances.\N再也不能這樣下去了，你的瘋狂暴怒和你的奢侈揮霍。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.01,0:37:16.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's got to stop, Bosie.\N這必須停止了，波西。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.49,0:37:19.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wouldn't my father be delighted to think\N這下我父親該高興了
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.80,0:37:21.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he'd finally broken up our friendship?\N他終於讓我們斷絕了關系
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.67,0:37:23.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My God, it is stuffy in here.\N上帝，這裡也太悶了。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.24,0:37:24.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know how you can breathe.\N我都不知道你在這裡怎麼呼吸。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.85,0:37:28.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once and for all, I'm sick to death of being a cat's-paw\N讓我一了百了地病死吧，我可不想成為
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.46,0:37:30.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in this terrible war between you and your father.\N你和你父親之間可怕戰爭的犧牲品。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.59,0:37:33.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And for heaven's sake, close the window.\N看在老天爺的份上，把窗戶關上吧。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.46,0:37:35.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Am I to be held responsible for the ravings of my lunatic father?\N我還需要為我那個失瘋的父親說過的瘋話負責嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.99,0:37:38.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I sometimes think there's very little difference between him and you.\N我有時覺得你和他之間沒什麼區別。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.12,0:37:39.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've both insane. Bosie, the window.\N你們都很瘋狂，波西，關窗。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.95,0:37:42.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My God, I've had just about had as much as I can stand of this.\N天吶，我已經受夠了我能忍受的。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.43,0:37:44.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Oh, my God.    -Is this the thanks I get\N-哦，上帝。  -這就是我的回報。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.08,0:37:45.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-for devoting myself to you these past two years?  -My God!\N-兩年來，我把我自己獻給了你。  -上帝啊！
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.65,0:37:46.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is happening to me?\N我這是怎麼了？
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.96,0:37:48.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How I ever came to think you were so marvelous...\N我曾認為你很非凡。。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.78,0:37:51.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Bosie, for God's sake, go away. -Oscar Wilde, the great genius,\N-波西，行行好，離開我。    -奧斯卡王爾德，這個偉大的天才，
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.09,0:37:52.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the great wit.\N偉大的智者。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.87,0:37:54.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Idol of society. And look at you sniveling like some kicked dog.\N社會的偶像，看看你現在像一只被踢開的狗一樣哭泣。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.75,0:37:58.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think I'm going to let you end this so easily, Oscar?\N你真的認為我會輕易地讓你結束這一切嗎？奧斯卡。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.10,0:37:59.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not going to throw me aside\N你別想把我拋到一邊
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.75,0:38:01.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because you've no further use for me.\N就因為以後我對你再也沒有用處了。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.23,0:38:02.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not my father!\N你不是我父親！
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.28,0:38:07.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bosie, are you insane?\N波西，你瘋了嗎?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.11,0:38:08.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you know? It runs in the family.\N你知道嗎？我們家都有這德性。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.54,0:38:09.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bosie, put it down.\N波西，放下刀。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.33,0:38:11.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bosie, please!\N波西，別！
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.86,0:38:23.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How insignificant you look when you're afraid, Oscar.\N當你害怕時，你看起來是多麼渺小，奧斯卡。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.39,0:38:27.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I never thought you'd be afraid of me.\N我從未想到你會怕我。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.61,0:38:39.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, this place depresses me.\N哦，著地地方太壓抑了。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.55,0:38:58.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, um...\N哦
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.90,0:39:02.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't suppose you could let me have some money to pay the cab, could you? I...\N我不認為你會讓我付馬車錢，你能？我身上。。。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.82,0:39:06.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, well.\N好吧
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.10,0:39:33.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait for me, will you?\N等我一下吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.50,0:39:34.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'鈥檃m.\N是的，夫人。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.77,0:39:47.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good afternoon, madam. Good afternoon, Arthur.\N-下午好，夫人。   -下午好，阿瑟
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.21,0:39:48.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is Mr. Wilde at home?\N王爾德先生在家嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.51,0:39:50.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, he's working at the moment, madam.\N是的，他這會兒在工作，夫人。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.21,0:39:52.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Mrs. Wilde is in the front room.\N王爾德夫人在前廳。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.35,0:39:58.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Mrs. Leverson, madam.  -CONSTANCE: Ada!\N-裡弗森夫人到，夫人。   -康斯坦斯：艾達！
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.61,0:40:00.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My dear, I hope you don't mind my just dropping in.\N親愛的，我希望你不介意我的拜訪。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.61,0:40:02.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not. Arthur, may we have some tea, please?\N當然不會，我們一起喝下午茶吧，請！
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.74,0:40:04.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Certainly, madam.\N遵命，夫人。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.22,0:40:05.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How nice to see you. Good heavens, you're freezing.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.01,0:40:07.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come and get warm by the fire.\N到爐子邊暖和一下。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.79,0:40:10.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was just embroidering my birthday present for Oscar.\N我正在給奧斯卡的生日禮物繡花。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.97,0:40:12.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think he's going to like it?\N你覺得他會喜歡這個嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.75,0:40:16.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I'm sure he will,it's most handsome.\N噢，我想他一定會喜歡的，真漂亮。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.23,0:40:19.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oscar has the most expensive tastes, even in the simplest things.\N奧斯卡一直都有很昂貴的品味，即使對最簡單的小物件。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.63,0:40:20.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How is Oscar?\N奧斯卡怎麼樣了？
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.72,0:40:22.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, much better.\N噢，他好多了。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.11,0:40:24.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He just needed looking after properly.\N他就是需要被很好的照顧
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.12,0:40:30.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about Bosie?\N波西呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.04,0:40:36.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's all over now, thank God.\N結束了，感謝上帝。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.65,0:40:39.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't tell you what it was like, Ada.\N我都不知道該怎麼向你說，艾達。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.82,0:40:41.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To have a woman come between yourself and your husband,\N就像有個女人在你和你丈夫之間，
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.91,0:40:43.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that's something a wife can understand.\N那是一個妻子能體會到的。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.48,0:40:46.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But another man.\N但是如有另一個男人。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.01,0:40:52.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OSCAR: Constance,is that Ada's voice I hear?\N奧斯卡：康斯坦斯，我聽到了艾達的聲音？
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.14,0:40:53.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it is, dearest.\N是的，她來了，老公。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.71,0:40:56.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I must hide this, I don't want to spoil the surprise.\N我必須把這個收起來，不想讓他失去驚喜。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.49,0:40:59.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ada, my dear.\N艾達，我親愛的。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.23,0:41:00.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're looking wonderful, Oscar.\N你看起來氣色不錯，奧斯卡。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.80,0:41:03.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm, what a delicious hat!\NMm，多麼精致的帽子！
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.19,0:41:05.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Constance, where's that bottle of champagne I've been hoarding?\N康斯坦斯，我儲存的那瓶香檳酒呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.50,0:41:07.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oscar, you're not going to start drinking so early.\N奧斯卡，才那麼早你就要喝酒。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.63,0:41:09.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I am. This is a celebration.\N我當然要的，這值得慶祝一下。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.77,0:41:10.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You finished the play?\N你完成了你的劇作？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.99,0:41:12.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The curtain fell on the third act of\N大幕將在第三場後落下
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.60,0:41:14.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Importance of Being Earnest as the doorbell rang.\N《不可兒戲》的開場鈴響了。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.68,0:41:15.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll get the champagne.\N我去開香檳。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.86,0:41:17.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ada, your timing is impeccable.\N艾達，你來的時機真好。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.25,0:41:19.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Is it a good play?    -Quite extraordinary.\N-這是一部好戲嗎？  -那是相當的精彩。\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.25,0:41:21.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ada, I'm happier than I've been for years.\N艾達，這幾年來，我現在最高興了。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.34,0:41:23.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm working. I'm seeing more of the children.\N我樂於工作，我樂於和孩子們在一起。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.52,0:41:25.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Constance is a guardian angel.\N康斯坦斯真是一個守護天使。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.48,0:41:29.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In fact, I believe I'm getting dull and bourgeois and very old.\N實際上，我相信自己已經變得很沉悶，很市儈，也很老。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.83,0:41:35.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You miss him, don't you?\N你在想他，是不是？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.66,0:41:38.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.\N是。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.45,0:41:45.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes when I see the sunlight on an evening sky\N有時當我注視著落日余輝
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.06,0:41:49.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or wander by the river and watch the dark waters,\N或當我漫步在河邊，並注視著黯淡的河水，
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.59,0:41:54.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I seem to see him flitting by me in the darkness,\N仿佛看見他從我身邊掠過，又消失在黑暗中，
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.60,0:41:58.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and then I feel terribly alone.\N於是我又墜入可怕的孤獨中。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.91,0:42:06.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you seen this?\N這個你看了嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.35,0:42:13.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Couldn't find the champagne glasses.\N找不到喝香檳的杯子。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.00,0:42:16.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been such a long time since we used them.\N我們已經好久沒用它們了。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.79,0:42:19.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oscar, what on earth is it?\N奧斯卡，怎麼了？
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.36,0:42:24.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bosie's elder brother was killed yesterday in a hunting accident.\N波西的兄長在一次狩獵事故被殺\N（有傳說是自殺，因他也是同性戀，與當時英國首相羅斯伯理有染）
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.62,0:42:26.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, how terrible.\N哦，太可怕了。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.02,0:42:28.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That would be Francis,wouldn't it?\N他就是弗朗西斯，是吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.85,0:42:30.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bosie was very fond of him, wasn't he?\N波西很喜歡他，是他吧?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.98,0:42:32.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Arthur.  -Sir?\N-阿瑟。  -先生？
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.81,0:42:35.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to go to the post office presently and send a telegram.\N我要你親自去趟郵局，拍封電報。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.46,0:42:36.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very good, sir.\N好的，先生。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.20,0:42:38.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think he may need me.\N我想他可能需要我。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.69,0:42:49.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For as much as it has pleased Almighty God\N為了盡可能地讓萬能的上帝得到滿足
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.13,0:42:54.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to take unto himself the soul of our dear brother departed,\N請帶走我們死去的親愛兄弟的靈魂上天堂\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.26,0:42:57.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we therefore commit his body to the ground.\N我們現在埋葬他的身體於地下。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.33,0:44:00.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well...\N那麼。。。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.94,0:44:04.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would seem it takes a death to bring about\N看來只有死亡才能給
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.94,0:44:07.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a family reunion in this house.\N這個家族帶來凝聚。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.74,0:44:18.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're all very silent.\N你們都不說話。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.22,0:44:21.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've just lost a son.\N我已經失去一個兒子。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.52,0:44:23.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't that mean anything to any of you?\N你們這樣是不是太殘忍了？
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.53,0:44:26.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.71,0:44:34.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're his mother. Don't you weep for your son?\N你是他的母親，你不想為你的兒子哭泣嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.41,0:44:39.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only real male son you ever bore.\N你生下的唯一的有男子氣的兒子。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.28,0:44:42.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Really, Father...   -The only real man among the three of you!\N-事實上，父親。。。   -你們三個中唯一一個真正男人！
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.30,0:44:56.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye, Mother.\N再見，母親。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.51,0:44:57.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye, Bosie.\N再見，波西。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.08,0:44:58.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bosie!\N波西！
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.04,0:45:04.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where the devil do you think you're going?\N魔鬼將要帶你去哪裡？
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.96,0:45:08.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've buried my brother.\N我已經埋葬了我的兄弟
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.96,0:45:11.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing to keep me here any longer.\N沒有什麼事情讓我再在這裡呆下去了。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.49,0:45:13.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is your home, damn you!\N這是你的家，混蛋！
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.53,0:45:16.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You belong here!\N你屬於這裡！
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.97,0:45:20.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were born here!\N你生在這裡！
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.67,0:45:24.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kinmount has been the House of Douglas for more than 300 years.\N道格拉斯家族在金芒特已經有300年了。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.24,0:45:25.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Goodbye, Percy.  -Bosie!\N-再見，珀西。  -波西！
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.68,0:45:32.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bosie.\N波西
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.64,0:45:37.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't go, boy. Stay here.\N別走，小子，呆在這裡。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.03,0:45:39.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just for a few days, eh?\N只待幾天，好嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.82,0:45:45.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It gets so lonely here sometimes and...\N有時這裡會非常冷清，而且。。。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.22,0:45:49.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, just for a few days, eh, Son?\N那就，呆幾天，兒子?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.57,0:45:53.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You call me son?\N你叫我兒子？
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.44,0:45:56.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not your son.\N我不是你的兒子。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.75,0:45:59.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You disowned me, or had you forgotten?\N你否認過我，你忘了嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.75,0:46:01.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You disowned me just as you've disowned the whole family.\N你否認過我就像你否認過整個家庭。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.71,0:46:02.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You drove Mother out of this house\N你把母親趕出了這座房子
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.97,0:46:05.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,with your abuse and your immorality.\N用你的辱罵和你的惡行。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.02,0:46:08.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You persecuted me until I had to keep away from you\N你騷擾我，使我不得不離開你
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.98,0:46:11.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for fear of what I might do if I were here to lay hands on you.\N我害怕如果我在這裡再住下去，我會對你下什麼樣的狠手。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.68,0:46:16.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I tried to make a man out of you.\N我試著讓你變成一個男人。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.64,0:46:19.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I tried to protect you against yourself.\N我試著教你保護你自己。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.38,0:46:21.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's no more than any other self-respecting father would do.\N這只不過是任何一個自尊的父親都會這樣做的。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.30,0:46:24.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You lost your self respect the day you threw my mother out of this house\N你把我母親拋出這所房子那天你就失去了自尊
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.39,0:46:26.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and brought your mistress here to live with you.\N那天你還把你的情婦領進門和你同居。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.30,0:46:31.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Damn your insolence! -Please!\N-拿你的傲慢無禮去見鬼吧！  -別這樣！
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.00,0:46:34.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I ought to take a whip and thrash you to the ground.\N我就應該拿鞭子把你抽倒在地。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.13,0:46:35.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I would welcome the opportunity, believe me.\N我希望有這樣的機會，相信我
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.01,0:46:37.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You talk to me of the moral issue.\N你敢和我談道德。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.66,0:46:39.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-For heaven's sake,   -Father!\N-天吶，  -父親！
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.05,0:46:40.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, what about him and that damned Wilde fellow?\N那他自己又怎麼樣？還有他那該死的伙伴王爾德？
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.49,0:46:43.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank God I succeeded in putting an end to that.\N感謝上帝，我已經結束了他們的關系。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.84,0:46:46.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One of these days you'll get down on your knees\N總有一天，你會跪在地上
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.10,0:46:47.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and you'll thank me for it.\N感謝我為你做的這一切。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.98,0:46:51.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He sent me a telegram this morning.\N他今天早上還給我發了份吊唁電報。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.46,0:46:54.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At least he has more sympathy with my bereavement than you seem to have.\N至少他對我喪失親人的的同情比你多
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.02,0:46:57.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going back to London this afternoon, and I warn you,\N我今天下午會倫敦。我警告你
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.90,0:47:01.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if ever you try and interfere in my private affairs again,\N如果你再試著干涉我私人的事情，
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.42,0:47:05.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll buy myself a pistol and I'll hunt you down and kill you.\N我將買把手槍，追到你並殺了你。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.83,0:47:23.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bosie!\N波西！
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.49,0:47:30.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bosie!\N波西！
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.76,0:47:35.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bosie!\N波西！
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.63,0:47:37.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're no son of mine, do you hear?\N你再也不是我的兒子了，你聽到了嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.89,0:47:40.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not my son!\N你不是我的兒子！
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.94,0:47:42.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go back to your precious friend,\N滾回到你那珍愛的朋友身邊吧，
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.42,0:47:44.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but, I warn you, I haven't finished with you yet!\N但是，我警告你，我和你沒完！
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.60,0:47:46.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or him!\N和他也沒完！
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.42,0:47:48.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll see you both behind bars!\N我將把你們兩個送監！
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.08,0:47:50.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you hear?\N聽到了嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.12,0:47:52.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Behind bars!\N送監！
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.93,0:48:12.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have a great deal to make up to you for, Oscar.\N我有很多話要跟你說，奧斯卡。
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.97,0:48:15.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been perfectly horrible to you in the past.\N我過去完全對不住你了。
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.50,0:48:17.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, don't mention it anymore.\N不，別在提那些了。
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.46,0:48:20.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes it takes a good row to clear the air.\N有時，一次激烈的爭吵會消除誤會。
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.60,0:48:29.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are we going to do about your father?\N你打算怎麼對付你父親？
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.82,0:48:32.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Believe me, it's only because of you\N相信我，這都是為了你
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.51,0:48:35.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that I haven't taken some sort of legal action against him.\N我才沒有對他提起訴訟。
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.69,0:48:37.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And involve your whole family in a scandal?\N也是為了不讓整個家族陷入丑聞吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.61,0:48:39.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That wouldn't help anybody except perhaps the journalists.\N這對任何人沒有好處，只會便宜了那些狗仔記者。
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.00,0:48:41.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just so long as he leaves me alone, that's all.\N只要他不管我的事，僅此而已。
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.96,0:48:48.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good heavens, what are we talking about my father for?\N天吶，我們干嘛談我的父親？
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.09,0:48:50.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your new play opens on Saturday.\N你的新劇星期六上演。
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.18,0:48:51.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We should be drinking to its success.\N我們需要為成功干杯。
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.40,0:48:54.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Its success?\N成功了？
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.14,0:48:57.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My dear boy, you don't doubt it'll be a success, do you?\N哥們兒，你不認為它會成功嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.76,0:49:01.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To The Importance of Being Earnest.\N為《不可兒戲》干杯。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.46,0:49:05.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To the importance of friendship.\N為友誼干杯。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.04,0:49:18.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,倫敦聖詹姆斯劇院\N隆重上演\N《不可兒戲》
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.97,0:50:22.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Wait there.   -Yes, sir.\N在這裡等著。  -是的先生。
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.02,0:50:28.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Queensberry, sir?\N昆斯博裡侯爵大人？
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.98,0:50:31.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.\N是我。
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.07,0:50:33.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, sir, I've strict instructions not to let you into the theater.\N對不起，大人，我有嚴格的命令不允許你進入劇院。
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.42,0:50:37.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must be out of your senses.\N你一定是瘋了吧。
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.73,0:50:38.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, sir.\N對不起，先生。
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.77,0:50:41.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who the devil are you anyway?\N你他媽的是什麼人？
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.34,0:50:42.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a police officer, sir.\N我是一個警官，先生。
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.64,0:50:45.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you indeed?\N真的?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.78,0:50:47.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Police officer, are you?\N警官，你嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.91,0:50:49.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you?\N你是嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.31,0:51:00.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't forget the cripple, sir.\N可憐一下我這個瘸子吧，先生。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.14,0:51:02.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, sir.\N對不起，先生。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.84,0:51:04.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No unauthorized persons are permitted to enter the theater.\N沒有得到允許的人不許進入劇院。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.75,0:51:06.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you realize who you're talking to?\N你知道你在和誰講話嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.62,0:51:08.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I do indeed, Your Lordship.\N哦，我知道，侯爵大人。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.76,0:51:10.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now look here, My Lord, why don't you run along and forget the whole thing?\N您看啊，我的大人，您為什麼不離開這裡忘掉這一切呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.80,0:51:13.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't want to go in there and spoil everybody's enjoyment.\N你其實不想進入這裡去破環大家的雅興。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.24,0:51:14.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not completely without influence.\N我不是完全沒有影響力的人。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.76,0:51:16.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm quite sure you're not, My Lord.\N我知道你不是，我的大人。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.29,0:51:18.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I shall report you to your senior officer, sir.\N不，我將向你的上級控告你，警官。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.12,0:51:27.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bit loose in the upper story, wouldn't you say, sir?\N你會向上級通融一下吧，長官？
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.47,0:51:29.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.34,0:51:31.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, let's hope that's the last we've seen of him tonight.\N但願這是今晚我們最後一次看到他。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.32,0:51:51.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ladies and gentlemen, I have enjoyed this evening immensely.\N女士們先生們，今晚我非常的高興。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.84,0:51:57.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The actors have given a charming rendering of a delightful play.\N演員們的迷人表演使得這部劇非常令人愉快。
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.16,0:52:05.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And your appreciation has been most intelligent.\N而你們也表現出很智慧的欣賞力。
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.12,0:52:10.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I congratulate you on the success of your performance,\N我祝賀你們雙方的表現都取得了成功，
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.38,0:52:11.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which proves to me\N這向我證明了
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.86,0:52:15.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that you think almost as highly of the play as I do.\N你們對這部劇的思考有著和我一樣的高度。
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.60,0:52:52.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-That's quite a wit...   -Cab!\N-太有趣兒了。。。  -馬車！
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.73,0:52:54.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's Queensberry.\N那是昆斯博裡。
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.12,0:52:55.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Queensberry? What's he up to?\N昆斯博裡？他要干什麼？
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.30,0:52:56.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mad as ever, I suppose.\N我猜他像以往那樣要瘋。
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.78,0:53:00.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mad.\N發瘋。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.39,0:53:06.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,QUEENSBERRY: Excuse me! Excuse me!\N昆斯博裡：讓一下！讓一下！
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.75,0:53:18.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Wilde, may I present you with this, sir?\N王爾德先生，我能送你這個嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.54,0:53:22.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How charming.\N好迷人。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.85,0:53:25.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Every time I smell them, I shall think of you, Lord Queensberry.\N每當我聞見它們的味道，我就會想到您，昆斯博裡侯爵。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.62,0:53:56.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Albemarle Club.\N去阿爾比馬爾俱樂部（王爾德是會員）
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.45,0:54:04.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry. Hurry!\N快點，快點！
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.95,0:54:25.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can I help you, sir?\N我能幫你嗎，先生？
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.21,0:54:26.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give me a pen.\N給我一支筆。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.43,0:54:29.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, I want you\N現在，我要你
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.78,0:54:33.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to give this message\N把這便簽
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.83,0:54:37.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to Mr. Oscar Wilde.\N給奧斯卡王爾德先生。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.23,0:54:38.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very good, sir.\N尊辦，先生。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.38,0:54:45.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,致奧斯卡 王爾德:\N表演的像個雞奸者。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.01,0:55:21.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here you are, Edward.\N給你，愛德華。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.36,0:55:22.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Mr. Wilde, sir.\N謝謝，王爾德先生
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.58,0:55:24.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Good morning, Wilde.   -Congratulations!\N-早上好，王爾德。    -恭喜成功！
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.75,0:55:25.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Thank you.     -Cab!\N-謝了。   -馬車！
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.59,0:55:34.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wilde, my dear fellow.\N王爾德，我的老伙計。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.89,0:55:38.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Saw your play last night. Laughed myself sick.\N昨晚看了你的劇，把我笑慘了。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.16,0:55:40.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You seem to have made a remarkable recovery, Major.\N看來你已經有了顯著的恢復，少校
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.51,0:55:46.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Mr. Wilde. A gentleman left this for you last night, sir.\N哦，王爾德先生，一位紳士昨晚給您留下這個。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.21,0:55:48.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Oh.  -I hear your play was a big success, sir.\N-噢。   -我聽說你的演出很成功，先生。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.60,0:55:50.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Congratulations, if I may say so.\N祝賀您，先生
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.39,0:55:51.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Sydney.\N謝謝你，西德尼。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.23,0:56:08.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, old chap. Enjoyed your play...\N你好，老伙計，喜歡你的演出。。。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.80,0:56:19.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, there's no doubt, Mr. Wilde,\N王爾德先生，這無疑
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.28,0:56:21.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,on the basis of what is written on this card alone,\N基於這張卡片上所寫的，
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.59,0:56:23.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you have the strongest possible grounds\N您有足夠的理由
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.55,0:56:26.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for an action against Lord Queensberry for criminal libel.\N對昆斯博裡侯爵提起文字中傷的訴訟
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.47,0:56:29.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean, Sir Edward, that you will take the case?\N這就是說，愛德華爵士，您將接手這個案子？
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.34,0:56:31.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, the question is, of course,\N那麼，問題是，當然，
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.25,0:56:32.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,do you want to proceed with this action?\N您是否要進行訴訟？
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.34,0:56:34.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, of course!\N當然要！
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.47,0:56:37.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you ask that, Sir Edward?\N您為什麼要問這個？愛德華爵士。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.04,0:56:38.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, no doubt, Queensberry's defense\N那麼，毫無疑問，昆斯博裡的辯護
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.65,0:56:40.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,will be that the libelous statement complained of\N將會是他的文字誹謗的觀點的抱怨緣由
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.96,0:56:43.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was justified and in effect true.\N是否是合理公正的和有效真實的
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.74,0:56:45.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It most certainly isn't true.\N它顯然不是真實的
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.66,0:56:49.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nevertheless, the defense will make every effort to prove that it is,\N不過，他們的辯護將努力證明它是真實的，
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.05,0:56:51.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and that could be extremely embarrassing for Mr. Wilde.\N而這將使得王爾德先生很難堪。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.49,0:56:53.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I agree. Oscar, it simply isn't worth it.\N我同意，奧斯卡，這樣不值得。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.49,0:56:55.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Queensberry's obviously a lunatic.\N昆斯博裡顯然是個瘋子。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.23,0:56:57.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To take an action against him is exactly what he wants.\N對他進行訴訟正是他想要的。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.58,0:56:59.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why he left that card.\N這就是他為什麼要留下這張紙條。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.50,0:57:01.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if we let him get away with this,there'll be no holding him.\N但是，如果讓他這麼逃脫，那就沒什麼阻撓他下一步的了。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.02,0:57:05.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have to draw a line somewhere. It's a matter of principle.\N我們必須明確界限，這是原則問題。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.37,0:57:07.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm afraid Lord Alfred is right.\N我認為阿爾弗雷德爵士是對的。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.07,0:57:09.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The man must be stopped somewhere.\N必須得有什麼能夠阻止這個人。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.12,0:57:10.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then you wish to proceed with this action?\N那麼你將進行訴訟了？
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.99,0:57:13.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I do.\N我要。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.51,0:57:16.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can't wait to see my father's face when I go into the witness box.\N當我進入證人席，真想看看我父親是什麼狼狽相。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.21,0:57:17.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I tell...\N當我告訴。。。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.60,0:57:19.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not going into the witness box, Bosie.\N你不會進入證人席的，波西，
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.69,0:57:22.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you mad, Oscar?\N你瘋了嗎，奧斯卡？
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.70,0:57:24.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've only got to tell them how he's...\N只有我才能告訴大家他是。。。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.26,0:57:26.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How he's persecuted me these past two years,\N過去兩年中，他是怎麼迫害我的，
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.05,0:57:27.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,how he drove my mother out of the house with his insane ravings.\N怎麼用瘋話把我的母親趕出那座房子的。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.92,0:57:30.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not having you involved, Bosie.\N我不想讓你卷進來，波西。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.14,0:57:33.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm afraid, Mr. Wilde, that Lord Alfred is already involved.\N王爾德先生，我恐怕，阿仁弗雷德爵士已經卷進來了。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.58,0:57:35.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, of course I'm involved.\N那麼，當然，我也就卷進來了。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.36,0:57:37.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not having you exposed to more scandal than is necessary.\N不到萬不得已的時候，我不會讓你曝光更多的緋聞。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.84,0:57:39.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oscar, don't you realize...\N奧斯卡，難道你沒有意識到。。。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.63,0:57:41.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bosie, you're not going into the witness box and that is final.\N波西你不會進入證人席，就這麼定了。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.30,0:58:00.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll have to forgive Bosie. He's a little impulsive.\N你要原諒波西，他有點沖任性。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.34,0:58:03.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So it would seem.\N好象是的。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.30,0:58:05.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, you have a very strong case, Mr. Wilde.\N不管怎麼樣，王爾德先生，你將有一場很激烈的官司。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.22,0:58:08.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter, Robbie?\N誰在乎呢，羅比？
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.13,0:58:12.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you determined to bring about your own destruction, Oscar?\N你這個決定將給你自己帶來毀滅，奧斯卡？
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.31,0:58:13.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that what you've trying to do?\N這是你將要做的嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.57,0:58:14.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't understand.\N我不明白。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.92,0:58:15.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I used to think you had a mind of your own.\N我過去曾經認為你有自己的想法。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.88,0:58:17.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A great mind. Oh, really.\N很偉大的思想，哦，真的。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.49,0:58:19.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oscar, you mustn't let Bosie push you into this thing.\N奧斯卡，你不能讓波西把你推入這些事情。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.32,0:58:20.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-What's the alternative?    -Go abroad.\N-那該怎麼躲開呢？  -出國去。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.01,0:58:23.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let Queensberry and his son fight their quarrel without you.\N讓昆斯博裡父子互相斗爭，而你置身其外。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.19,0:58:24.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They've well-matched.\N他們倆旗鼓相當。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.32,0:58:27.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's too late, Robbie.\N這太晚了，羅比。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.11,0:58:28.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Sir Edward, I'm entirely at your disposal.\N好吧，愛德華爵士，我將隨時聽後你的吩咐。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.02,0:58:30.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Any further information you need?\N你還需要什麼更多的信息？
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.59,0:58:32.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is one question I feel compelled to ask.\N有一個問題，我不得不問。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.42,0:58:34.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please do.\N請講。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.72,0:58:37.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can only accept this brief, Mr. Wilde,\N我只接受這個簡要聲明，王爾德先生，
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.16,0:58:40.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if you assure me on your honor as an English gentleman\N如果你以一名英國紳士的名譽向我保證
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.12,0:58:42.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that there is no truth in the charges made against you.\N那就是，所有對你的指責都不是真實的。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.00,0:58:48.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I assure you as an Irish gentleman\N作為一個愛爾蘭紳士，我向您保證
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.91,0:58:52.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that there's no truth whatever in any of them.\N他對我的任何指責都是不真實的。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.09,0:58:54.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, then, shall we say here tomorrow morning at 10:30, Mr. Wilde?\N那麼，我們將在明天上午10：30這裡繼續談，王爾德先生？
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.74,0:58:58.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good. Mr. Humphries.\N好的，漢弗萊先生。
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.54,0:59:06.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Paper! Queensberry arrested!\N報紙！昆斯博裡被捕了！
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.02,0:59:10.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Paper! Paper! Special edition!\N報紙！報紙！報紙！號外！
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.15,0:59:11.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Queensberry arrested!\N昆斯博裡被捕！
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.67,0:59:14.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Paper! Paper, sir! Paper!\N報紙！報紙，先生！報紙！
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.74,0:59:36.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,COURT USHER: Silence!\N庭警：肅靜！
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.03,1:00:04.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's Edward Carson, defending Queensberry.\N那是愛德華 卡森，昆斯博裡的辯護律師。\N（卡森被譽為北愛爾蘭無冕之王，一戰時任海軍大臣和不管大臣，最終，當上英國上訴法院院長）
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.78,1:00:13.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We went to Trinity College together.\N我們一起在（牛津的）三一學院上過學
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.95,1:00:17.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No doubt he'll perform his task with all the added bitterness of an old friend.\N無疑，他將要完成給他老朋友增加痛苦的任務。
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.70,1:00:19.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,COURT USHER: Silence!\N庭警：肅靜！
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.00,1:00:21.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be upstanding in court.\N庭上諸位，起立。
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.01,1:00:25.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All persons who have anything to do\N所有庭審有關的人員
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.79,1:00:28.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,before My Lords, the Queen's justices of oyer and terminer\N面對效忠女王陛下的，中央刑事法庭的法官大人，\N（位於倫敦老區的老貝利街，如今對游客開放）
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.88,1:00:32.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and general gaol delivery for the jurisdiction of the Central Criminal Court,\N該大人擁有聽審權，終判權和收監權
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.58,1:00:36.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,draw near and give your attendance. God save the Queen.\N爾等趨近就席，專心聽詢作答。天佑吾王。
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.38,1:00:51.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Put up John Sholto Douglas, Marquis of Queensberry.\N帶約翰·肖托·道格拉斯，昆士貝裡侯爵 上庭
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.69,1:00:54.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,John Sholto Douglas, Marquis of Queensberry.\N約翰·肖托·道格拉斯，昆士貝裡侯爵
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.83,1:01:11.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you John Sholto Douglas, Marquis of Queensberry?\N你是約翰 肖爾特 道格拉斯，昆斯博裡侯爵？
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.66,1:01:14.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am, sir.\N正是我，大人。
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.40,1:01:18.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The jurors for Our Lady, the Queen, upon their oath present\N“女王陛下的陪審團，將依據他們所發的誓言，對以下起訴書列舉的：
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.37,1:01:22.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"that John Sholto Douglas, Marquis of Queensberry,\N針對約翰·肖托·道格拉斯，昆士貝裡侯爵
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.54,1:01:25.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"contriving and maliciously intending to injure one\N“所犯的圖謀惡意傷害
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.63,1:01:28.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Oscar Fingal O'Flahertie Wills Wilde,\N奧斯卡·芬達爾·奧弗萊赫蒂·威爾斯·王爾德，
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.81,1:01:31.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"and to excite him to commit a breach of peace,\N“並涉嫌激怒原告去擾亂治安
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.29,1:01:35.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"and to bring him into public contempt, scandal and disgrace,\N並在大庭廣眾下給原告帶來蔑視，丑聞和羞辱，\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:35.64,1:01:41.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"did on the 14th day of February in the year of our Lord 1895,\N時間是在1895年2月14日
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.17,1:01:43.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"and within the jurisdiction of this court\N“同時，本庭的訴法審判權還包括，對以下所列舉的
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.70,1:01:48.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"unlawfully, wickedly and maliciously write and publish\N"非法，惡意和蓄謀書寫和公布
Dialogue: 0,1:01:48.18,1:01:50.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"a false and scandalous,\N“一個虛構的和誹謗的
Dialogue: 0,1:01:50.48,1:01:55.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"malicious and defamatory libel, in the form of a card,\N“惡意的和破壞名譽的文字誹謗物，以一張便簽紙的形式，
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.62,1:02:00.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"directed to the said Oscar Fingal O'Flahertie Wills Wilde,\N直接用說話的形式交給，奧斯卡·芬達爾·奧弗萊赫蒂·威爾斯·王爾德，
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.10,1:02:02.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"on which were written the words,\N“在上面寫著如下字樣，
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.41,1:02:06.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"'To Oscar Wilde, posing as a sodomite.'”?\N“致奧斯卡 王爾德，表演地像個雞奸者”
Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.77,1:02:17.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,COURT USHER: Silence in court.\N庭警：肅靜。
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.77,1:02:21.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"To the great damage, scandal and disgrace\N“給原告造成了極大的傷害，丑聞和恥辱
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.30,1:02:24.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"of the said Oscar Fingal O'Flahertie Wills Wilde\N“即給奧斯卡·芬達爾·奧弗萊赫蒂·威爾斯·王爾德
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.39,1:02:30.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"and against the peace of our said Lady the Queen, her crown and dignity,\N“並且擾亂了在女王陛下的王權和尊嚴統治下的和平，
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.31,1:02:34.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"John Sholto Douglas, Marquis of Queensberry,\N“約翰·肖托·道格拉斯，昆士貝裡侯爵
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.83,1:02:37.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"upon the aforesaid indictment, how do you plead?"\N“基於以上起訴書所列舉的種種行為，你要怎麼申辯？”
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.31,1:02:40.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guilty or not guilty?\N有罪還是無罪？
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.27,1:02:41.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not guilty, My Lord.\N無罪，大人。
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.88,1:02:44.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it please you, My Lord,\N如果它能令您滿意，大人，
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.23,1:02:46.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it is my client's plea that the alleged libel\N這是我的委托人對所謂誹謗行為的申辯
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.02,1:02:49.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,according to the natural meaning of the words thereof\N按照字面上的原始意思
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.54,1:02:51.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is true in substance and in fact,\N在本質上和實際上都是真實的，
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.37,1:02:54.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and that it was for the public benefit and interest\N它是符合公眾的利益和興趣的
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.24,1:02:57.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that the matter contained in the alleged libel should be published.\N所以，這件所謂的文字誹謗物應該被公布。
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.29,1:03:00.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Such a plea has been filed with this court?\N這個的辯解庭上是否已經記錄在案？
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.29,1:03:01.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It has, My Lord.\N已經記錄了，我的大人。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.60,1:03:04.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Mr. Carson. Let the jury be sworn.\N謝謝你，卡森先生，讓陪審團宣誓吧。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.39,1:03:09.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take the Bible in your right hand and read from the card.\N右手持聖經，按照卡片上念誓詞。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.30,1:03:13.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I swear by Almighty God that I will well and truly..."\N“向全能的上帝發誓，我將很好地並真實地。。。”
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.13,1:03:14.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I put the card in an envelope,\N我把便簽放進一個信封，
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.70,1:03:16.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which I addressed to Mr. Oscar Wilde\N在上寫了：給奧斯卡 王爾德先生
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.83,1:03:18.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and when Mr. Wilde came into the club,\N當王爾德先生來到俱樂部，
Dialogue: 0,1:03:18.96,1:03:22.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I handed it to him saying that Lord Queensberry had asked me to give it to him.\N我把信封交給他，並說這是昆斯博裡侯爵要我把這個給他的。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.75,1:03:25.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And did you look at this card when Lord Queensberry gave it to you?\N當昆斯博裡侯爵給你便簽時，你是否看到了上面的文字？
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.36,1:03:26.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I did, sir.\N我看到了，大人。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.23,1:03:28.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Mr. Wright.\N謝謝，賴特先生
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.63,1:03:31.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no questions, My Lord.\N我沒有問題了，大人。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.15,1:03:33.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,COURT USHER: The witness may stand down.\N庭警：證人可以退席。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.90,1:03:40.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think there's any suggestion by the defense\N我不認為辨方律師有任何提示
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.46,1:03:43.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that Lord Queensberry did not leave this card at the Albemarle Club,\N能表明昆斯博裡侯爵沒有在阿貝馬勒俱樂部留下這張便簽
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.29,1:03:46.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,nor that he wrote upon it the words complained of by my client.\N也沒有寫下使得我的當事人抱怨的文字。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.38,1:03:49.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In his plea of justification\N在他的釋罪申辯中
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.39,1:03:52.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in which the defendant seeks to malign the character of Mr. Oscar Wilde,\N被告竭力詆毀奧斯卡王爾德先生的品格，
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.17,1:03:54.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the defendant put in evidence a letter\N被告把一封信作為物證
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.65,1:03:57.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,written by Mr. Oscar Wilde to Lord Alfred Douglas,\N這封信是由奧斯卡王爾德先生寫給阿爾弗雷德道格拉斯爵士，
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.92,1:03:59.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the son of the accused.\N也就是被告的兒子。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:59.70,1:04:02.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I now propose to read the letter to the court, My Lord.\N現在我打算把它讀給庭上，大人。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.49,1:04:06.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"My own boy, your sonnet is quite lovely,\N“我的寶貝男孩，你的十四行詩是如此的可愛，
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.53,1:04:10.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"and it is a marvel that those red rose leaf lips of yours\N“你的紅玫瑰花瓣般的嘴唇，令人驚奇地
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.19,1:04:14.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"should have been made no less for music of song than for madness of kisses.\N“奏出與瘋狂接吻一樣樂曲
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.98,1:04:18.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Your slim guilt soul walks between passion and poetry.\N“你的纖細負罪心靈行走在激情與詩歌之間。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.55,1:04:21.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I know Hyacinthus, whom Apollo loved so madly,\N“我知道，被阿波羅瘋狂愛戀著的雅辛托斯（希臘神話中的一個形象）
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.55,1:04:23.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"was you in Greek days.\N“就是在希臘是的你。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.59,1:04:27.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Always with undying love, yours, Oscar."\N“對你的愛致死不休，你的奧斯卡”
Dialogue: 0,1:04:29.51,1:04:32.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The words contained in that letter may appear somewhat extravagant\N在信中的詞句會顯得太過放縱
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.95,1:04:36.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for those normally engaged in the writing of commercial correspondence.\N這當然是對那些從事正常商業信函寫作的人來說。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.17,1:04:39.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Silence!\N肅靜！
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.17,1:04:41.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Mr. Wilde is a poet\N但是王爾德先生是一個詩人
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.35,1:04:44.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and that letter is considered by him to be a prose sonnet,\N而這封信經過他的深思熟慮，變成了一首散文詩。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.92,1:04:48.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and one in which he is no way ashamed.\N在其中他一點也沒有什麼值得羞愧的。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.44,1:04:51.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I now ask Mr. Oscar Wilde to go into the witness box.\N我現在要求奧斯卡王爾德先生入證人席。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.24,1:05:02.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take the Bible in your right hand and read from the card.\N右手持聖經，按照卡片上念誓詞。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.02,1:05:06.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I swear by Almighty God that the evidence I give to this court\N“我向全能的上帝發誓，我帶給法庭的證據
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.16,1:05:08.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"shall be the truth, the whole truth, and nothing but the truth,\N“將是真實的，且全部真實的，且沒有不真實的，
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.51,1:05:09.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"so help me God."\N“上帝保佑。”
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.60,1:05:17.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are Mr. Oscar Wilde and you are the prosecutor in this case.\N你是奧斯卡王爾德先生，也就是本案的起訴人。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:17.73,1:05:18.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am.\N我是。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.00,1:05:20.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How old are you, Mr. Wilde?\N你多大了？王爾德先生？
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.52,1:05:22.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm 39.\N我39歲。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.09,1:05:23.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you married, Mr. Wilde?\N你結婚了嗎？王爾德先生？
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.92,1:05:28.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am, and I have two children, one aged nine and the other eight.\N結了，且我又兩個孩子，一個9歲另一個8歲。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.27,1:05:30.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And when did you first become acquainted with Lord Alfred Douglas?\N你什麼時候認識阿爾弗雷德道格拉斯爵士的？
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.23,1:05:34.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In 1891.\N在1891年。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.01,1:05:36.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A friend brought him to my house.\N一個朋友帶他來我家。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.02,1:05:39.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And since that time you have become close friends?\N從那時起，你們就成為密友了？
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.67,1:05:41.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was a guest at my house many times.\N他來我家做客好幾次。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.98,1:05:44.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A guest of yourself and your wife?\N他是你和你夫人的賓客？
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.41,1:05:45.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Certainly.\N當然。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.11,1:05:49.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In March 1893,\N在1893年3月，
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.90,1:05:54.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,did it come to your notice that a letter addressed by you to Lord Alfred Douglas\N你有沒有注意到有一封你寫給阿爾弗雷德·道格拉斯勳爵的信
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.08,1:05:58.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,had come into the hands of a certain person?\N到了某個人的手中？
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.21,1:06:00.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, a man named Wood came to me\N是的，一個叫伍德的人來找我
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.65,1:06:04.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and said that he'd found it in a suit of clothes belonging to Lord Alfred.\N他說在阿爾弗雷德的衣服裡找到這封信。
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.78,1:06:06.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did he demand money for that letter?\N他為了這封信是否向你要錢了？
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.70,1:06:08.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He said a man had offered him 60pounds for it.\N他說有人想出60英鎊買這封信。
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.96,1:06:10.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And what did you say to that?\N那你對他說什麼了？
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.44,1:06:12.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I said I'v never received so large an amount\N我說，我從未花費過那麼一大筆錢
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.53,1:06:14.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for a prose work of that length,\N為了那麼短的一首散文，
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.31,1:06:17.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I advised him to sell it to the man at once.\N我建議他立刻賣給那個想要的人。
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.58,1:06:24.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Prior to this time, you had been subjected to considerable annoyance\N在這件事情之前，你是否還受到了相當多的
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.54,1:06:26.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,by Lord Queensberry, had you not?\N來自昆斯博裡侯爵的騷擾？有過嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.63,1:06:28.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yes.\N哦，有過。
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.46,1:06:30.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's written several abusive letters to myself and my friends\N他幾次寫那種帶有辱罵的信，寄給我本人和我朋友們
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.89,1:06:33.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and on one occasion, he forced his way into my house\N並有一次，他堵在我家門口
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.55,1:06:34.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I was compelled to eject him.\N而我不得已驅逐了他。
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.99,1:06:37.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And what took place on that occasion?\N後來又發生了什麼？
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.34,1:06:40.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He made certain accusations about my relationship with Lord Alfred\N他很確信地指責我和他兒子阿爾弗雷德爵士的關系
Dialogue: 0,1:06:40.99,1:06:43.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I said to him,\N而我跟他說，
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.08,1:06:47.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Lord Queensberry, do you seriously accuse your son and me of improper conduct?"\N“昆斯博裡侯爵，你是很認真地指責你兒子和我的不正當關系嗎？”
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.39,1:06:49.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And what did he say to that?\N那他又說了什麼？
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.26,1:06:52.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He said,"I don't say you are, but I say you look it."\N他說:“我沒說你們是，但我說你們看起來是。”
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.14,1:06:55.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Silence in court!\N肅靜！
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.79,1:06:57.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If there is the slightest disturbance again,\N有誰再發出一點動靜，
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.79,1:06:59.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I shall have the court cleared.\N我要把他請出法庭。
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.75,1:07:05.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Wilde, your attention has been drawn to certain statements\N王爾德先生，你的注意力已經被吸引到一個明確的陳述
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.41,1:07:07.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,made in the plea of justification\N再加上由被告，昆斯博裡侯爵
Dialogue: 0,1:07:07.41,1:07:09.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,filed by the defendant, Lord Queensberry,\N提交的釋罪申辯
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.02,1:07:14.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,with reference to different persons impugning your conduct with them.\N那就是已經有不同的人利用它們來對你的行為進行譴責。
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.07,1:07:15.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.\N是的。
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.94,1:07:18.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Wilde,\N王爾德先生，
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.99,1:07:23.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is there any truth whatever in any of those accusations?\N在這些譴責中有沒有任何符合事實的成分？
Dialogue: 0,1:07:23.08,1:07:24.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,None whatever in any of them.\N一點兒都沒有。
Dialogue: 0,1:07:33.74,1:07:34.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Mr. Wilde.\N謝謝你，王爾德先生。
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.53,1:07:47.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Wilde, you stated earlier that your age was 39.\N王爾德先生，你剛才說你的年齡39歲。
Dialogue: 0,1:07:47.19,1:07:48.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Is that correct?  -Yes.\N-對嗎？  -是的
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.11,1:07:56.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were born in 1854. That makes you over 40, doesn't it?\N你出生在1854年，那就是說你已年過四十，對不對？
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.81,1:08:00.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, very well.\N噢，正是。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.81,1:08:04.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:04.08,1:08:07.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At what age was Lord Alfred Douglas when you first met him?\N當你第一次遇見阿爾弗雷 德道格拉斯爵士時，他多大歲數？
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.56,1:08:09.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was between 20 and 21.\N他那時是在20到21之間。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.47,1:08:11.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not yet 21. Hmm.\N還不到21歲，對吧。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.26,1:08:16.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And since that time you have been close friends?\N自從那時起，你倆就成為密友了？
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.35,1:08:18.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.\N是的。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:18.92,1:08:21.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've stayed with him at many places?\N你和他一起去過很多地方？
Dialogue: 0,1:08:22.44,1:08:24.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.\N是的。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.10,1:08:27.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At Oxford, Brighton, on several occasions?\N是不是去過幾次牛津，布萊頓？
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.45,1:08:29.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.\N是的。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.88,1:08:32.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And at various hotels in London?\N在倫敦還住過各種旅館？
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.36,1:08:34.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.\N是的。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.06,1:08:36.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've also been abroad with him several times.\N您還有幾次和他一起出國。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:36.54,1:08:40.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, to Egypt, Paris and Monte Carlo.\N是的，去過埃及，巴黎和蒙特卡羅（法國尼斯附近的賭城）。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.42,1:08:44.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One could therefore describe your friendship as intimate?\N人們可以用親密來描述你們之間的關系嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.86,1:08:46.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, very.\N是的，合適。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.73,1:08:50.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.\N真的。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.77,1:08:54.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have here a magazine called The Chameleon,\N我手頭有一本名叫變色龍的雜志
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.73,1:08:56.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in which is an article by yourself.\N在上面登有你的一篇文章。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:56.52,1:08:59.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, two poems contributed by Lord Alfred Douglas.\N上面還有，阿爾弗萊德 道格拉斯爵士貢獻的兩首詩。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.65,1:09:01.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I thought them exceedingly beautiful.\N是的，我想他們一定很精彩。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:02.87,1:09:04.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you?\N是嗎?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.57,1:09:07.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you remember the titles of these two poems, Mr. Wilde?\N您還記得這兩首詩的名字嗎？王爾德先生。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:07.27,1:09:09.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. One was called In Praise of Shame,\N是的，一首叫巴黎的恥辱
Dialogue: 0,1:09:09.58,1:09:10.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the other, Two Loves.\N另一首叫，兩個情人。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:11.53,1:09:13.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.\N謝謝你。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.32,1:09:16.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These two loves, they were two boys, weren't they?\N這兩個情人，他們是兩個男孩，對吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:09:17.54,1:09:18.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.\N是的。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:20.54,1:09:26.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One boy calls his love true love and the other boy calls his love shame.\N一個男孩管他的情人叫真愛而另一個男孩管他的情人叫恥辱。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:27.20,1:09:28.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is correct.\N正確。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.90,1:09:32.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think that made any improper suggestion?\N你不覺得他們有不合適的暗示嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.42,1:09:33.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, not at all.\N沒有，一點兒都沒有。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:35.38,1:09:36.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.04,1:09:41.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's another article in this magazine\N這本雜志裡還有另一篇文章
Dialogue: 0,1:09:42.00,1:09:45.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,entitled The Priest and the Acolyte. Have you read that?\N名叫牧師與侍從，你讀過嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:09:46.09,1:09:47.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have.\N讀過。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:47.92,1:09:51.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you consider that this article was in any way immoral?\N你認為這篇文章有傷風敗俗之嫌嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:09:51.66,1:09:53.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was worse. It was very badly written.\N這就更不對了，它只是寫得不好而已。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:55.88,1:09:59.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was it not the story of a priest who fell in love with an altar boy?\N它是不是講一個牧師陷入與祭台侍童的愛情的故事？
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.89,1:10:02.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I read it only once and nothing would induce me to read it again.\N好吧，我只是讀過一遍，沒有什麼吸引我再讀它。
Dialogue: 0,1:10:02.58,1:10:04.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think the story blasphemous?\N你認為這個故事是褻瀆神明嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:10:04.46,1:10:07.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it violates every artistic canon of beauty.\N我認為它違反了每一條美學的藝術標准。
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.50,1:10:09.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is not an answer.\N這不是回答。
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.16,1:10:10.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the only answer I can give.\N這是我可以給出的唯一答案。
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.85,1:10:13.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wish to know whether you thought the story blasphemous?\N我希望知道你是否這個故事褻瀆神明？
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.47,1:10:18.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It disgusted me, and the end was completely wrong.\N它讓我惡心，且結尾完全不對。
Dialogue: 0,1:10:18.38,1:10:19.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will you answer the question?\N你將回答提問嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.95,1:10:22.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you or did you not consider the story blasphemous?\N你是否認為它褻瀆神明？
Dialogue: 0,1:10:22.30,1:10:25.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it was horrid. Blasphemous is not a word of mine.\N我對它很反感。褻瀆神明不是我的用詞。
Dialogue: 0,1:10:25.83,1:10:26.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.\N我明白了。
Dialogue: 0,1:10:28.65,1:10:32.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, from the same magazine here\N現在，從同一本雜志中
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.44,1:10:37.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are some of the phrases and philosophies for the use of the young\N有一些用於年輕人的短語和哲學觀點
Dialogue: 0,1:10:37.27,1:10:39.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which you contributed.\N是你貢獻出來的。
Dialogue: 0,1:10:39.32,1:10:41.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Wickedness is a myth invented by good people\N“邪惡是由好人們構築出來的神話
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.58,1:10:44.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"to account for the curious attractiveness of others."\N“用於解釋別人的古怪的吸引力”
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.11,1:10:46.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think that true?\N你認為這是真實的嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:10:46.32,1:10:48.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I rarely think anything I write is true.\N我很少認為我寫的都是真實的。
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.37,1:10:55.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Religions die hard when they are proved to be true."\N“宗教信仰很難被湮滅，當它們被證明是真的。”
Dialogue: 0,1:10:55.59,1:10:56.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that true?\N這是你寫的吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:10:57.03,1:10:58.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I hold to that,\N是的，我堅持這點，
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.38,1:11:00.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but it's too big a question to go into here.\N但這個論題太龐大了，在這裡很難深入討論下去。
Dialogue: 0,1:11:00.64,1:11:02.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you think that was a safe axiom\N你認為這是可靠的公理
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.51,1:11:05.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to put forward for the philosophy of the young?\N用於向年輕人中作為哲學觀點提出？
Dialogue: 0,1:11:05.17,1:11:07.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's most stimulating.\N我認為它很刺激。
Dialogue: 0,1:11:07.52,1:11:11.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"If one tells the truth, one is sure sooner or later to be found out."\N如果一個人講真話，他遲早會被發現的\N（《不可兒戲》中原文：我的人生經驗是，每當你撒謊，你便在各方面得到鞏固。當你講真話，你便被遺棄在一個孤獨而痛苦的位置，且沒有人相信你半句。）
Dialogue: 0,1:11:13.66,1:11:17.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A pleasing paradox, but I do not set very much store on it as an axiom.\N多麼令人愉悅的悖論，可惜我對這種格言的儲備不多。
Dialogue: 0,1:11:17.14,1:11:19.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whether moral or immoral?\N那它們是道德的還是不道德的？
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.36,1:11:22.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no morality or immorality in thought.\N在思想中就沒有什麼道德不道德。
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.88,1:11:24.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are immoral emotions.\N這就是不道德的情感。
Dialogue: 0,1:11:24.93,1:11:25.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quite so.\N正是如此。
Dialogue: 0,1:11:27.76,1:11:30.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then.\N那麼。
Dialogue: 0,1:11:30.32,1:11:34.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the introduction to your book, The Picture of Dorian Gray.\N在你的小說《道林格雷的肖像》有這樣一段引言。
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.42,1:11:39.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"There is no such thing as a moral or immoral book.\N“從來就沒有什麼道德或不道德的書。
Dialogue: 0,1:11:39.29,1:11:41.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Books are well written or badly written."\N“書只有寫得好與不好。”
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.90,1:11:43.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That expresses your view?\N它表達了你的觀點？
Dialogue: 0,1:11:43.56,1:11:45.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My view on art, yes.\N我對藝術的觀點，是的。
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.34,1:11:49.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then no matter how immoral a book may be, if it is well written,\N如果一本書寫得好，就不管它有多麼不道德，
Dialogue: 0,1:11:49.04,1:11:51.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it is in your opinion a good book.\N這是你對一本好書的觀點。
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.04,1:11:54.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it is well written so as to produce a sense of beauty.\N如果它被寫得產生了美感。
Dialogue: 0,1:11:54.31,1:11:55.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then a well written book\N那它就是一本好書
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.87,1:11:59.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,putting forward perverted moral views may be a good book?\N提出一個歪曲道德標准的觀點也能算是一本好書？
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.22,1:12:01.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A work of art doesn't put forward views.\N藝術作品從來不提出觀點。
Dialogue: 0,1:12:01.57,1:12:03.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Views are for people.\N觀點是有由人們提出的。
Dialogue: 0,1:12:03.10,1:12:05.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A perverted novel might be a good book?\N一本墮落的小說會是好書嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.66,1:12:08.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what you mean by a perverted novel.\N我不知道你怎麼定義墮落的小說。
Dialogue: 0,1:12:08.06,1:12:10.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, I will suggest The Picture of Dorian Gray\N那我就提示《道林格雷的畫像》這本書
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.23,1:12:13.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as being open to the interpretation of being such a book.\N作為這類書公開存在的解釋
Dialogue: 0,1:12:13.37,1:12:15.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only to brutes and illiterates.\N只是對畜生和文盲。
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.41,1:12:19.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The affection and love of the artist for the youth, Dorian Gray,\N藝術家為年輕人展現的情感和愛情，比如像道林格雷這樣，
Dialogue: 0,1:12:19.77,1:12:22.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,might lead an ordinary individual\N會引導一個普通個體\N（書中道林格雷做出很多不道德的事情）
Dialogue: 0,1:12:22.25,1:12:25.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to believe that it might have a certain tendency.\N去相信這會是一個必然趨勢。
Dialogue: 0,1:12:25.64,1:12:28.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no knowledge of the views of ordinary individuals.\N我不知道普通個體的觀點，
Dialogue: 0,1:12:29.82,1:12:30.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:30.82,1:12:33.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I propose, if I may, to quote\N我打算，如果可以，引用
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.56,1:12:36.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a few passages from this book.\N書中一些段落。
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.61,1:12:39.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The artist Hallward is speaking to Dorian Gray.\N藝術家霍爾沃德對道林格雷說\N（書中人物，給道林畫像的藝術家）
Dialogue: 0,1:12:39.61,1:12:42.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"It is quite true that I have worshiped you\N“千真萬確，我非常地崇拜你
Dialogue: 0,1:12:42.27,1:12:46.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"with far more romance than a man usually gives to a friend.\N“我對你懷有一個男人對他的朋友更多的浪漫之情。
Dialogue: 0,1:12:46.49,1:12:49.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I have never loved a woman.\N“我從未愛過一個女人。
Dialogue: 0,1:12:49.75,1:12:52.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"From the moment I met you,\N“自從見到你的那刻起
Dialogue: 0,1:12:52.06,1:12:55.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"your personality had the most extraordinary influence over me.\N你的個性就最強烈地影響著我。
Dialogue: 0,1:12:55.37,1:13:02.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I quite admit I adored you madly, extravagantly, absurdly."\N“我不得不承認我瘋狂地，放肆地，荒唐地仰慕你。”
Dialogue: 0,1:13:02.16,1:13:04.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you mean to say that that passage\N你是否想說那個段落
Dialogue: 0,1:13:04.11,1:13:07.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,describes the natural feeling of one man towards another?\N描寫了一個男人對另外男人的自然的感情？
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.86,1:13:10.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dorian Gray's was a remarkable personality.\N道林格雷有著非常顯著的個性。
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.86,1:13:15.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,May I take it that you as an artist have never known the feeling described here?\N這裡我是否可以把你當成（書中的）那個藝術家，你從來沒有體驗過這裡描述的感覺?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:15.73,1:13:18.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. It is a work of fiction.\N不，它是虛構的作品。
Dialogue: 0,1:13:18.48,1:13:22.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let us go over it phrase by phrase.\N讓我們逐字逐句地看。
Dialogue: 0,1:13:22.22,1:13:25.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I quite admit that I have adored you madly."\N“我不得不承認我瘋狂地仰慕你。”
Dialogue: 0,1:13:25.79,1:13:29.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you say to that? Have you ever adored a young man madly?\N這你怎麼說？你曾經瘋狂地仰慕一個年輕人嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:13:29.31,1:13:31.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've never given adoration to anyone.\N我從來沒有仰慕過任何人。
Dialogue: 0,1:13:31.71,1:13:33.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Except myself.\N我自己除外。
Dialogue: 0,1:13:36.23,1:13:38.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose you think that a very smart thing?\N我猜那是一件很好玩的事？
Dialogue: 0,1:13:38.93,1:13:39.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all.\N一點也不。
Dialogue: 0,1:13:41.46,1:13:44.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I have adored you extravagantly."\N“我已經揮霍無度地仰慕你。”
Dialogue: 0,1:13:44.20,1:13:46.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you mean financially?\N你是要說財務上的嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:13:46.29,1:13:48.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yes, financially!\N噢，是的，財務上的！
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.77,1:13:51.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think that we are talking about finance?\N你認為我們現在是在談論財務？
Dialogue: 0,1:13:51.07,1:13:52.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what you've talking about.\N我不知道你在談論什麼。
Dialogue: 0,1:13:52.64,1:13:54.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you?\N你不知道？
Dialogue: 0,1:13:54.47,1:13:56.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I hope that I shall make myself very plain before I have done.\N那麼，我希望在說完之前就把話說得明白些。
Dialogue: 0,1:13:59.65,1:14:04.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And we come now to the letter which you wrote to Lord Alfred Douglas.\N現在我們來談談你寫給阿爾弗雷德·道格拉斯勳爵的信。
Dialogue: 0,1:14:05.35,1:14:08.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It begins, "My own boy."\N開頭就是，“我的寶貝男孩."
Dialogue: 0,1:14:08.79,1:14:12.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, why should a man of your age address a young boy\N看那，為什麼你這樣年齡的男人稱呼一個比你
Dialogue: 0,1:14:12.62,1:14:16.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,nearly 20 years younger as "My own boy"?\N年輕20歲的男人為“我的寶貝男孩”？
Dialogue: 0,1:14:16.45,1:14:19.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was fond of him. I've always been fond of him.\N我喜歡他，我一直都喜歡他。
Dialogue: 0,1:14:19.54,1:14:20.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you adore him?\N那你仰慕他嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.41,1:14:24.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I like him.\N不，我喜歡他。
Dialogue: 0,1:14:24.37,1:14:25.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that's not an ordinary letter.\N 那不是一封普通的信件。
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.54,1:14:27.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You might as well cross examine me\N你或許可以像盤問我一樣
Dialogue: 0,1:14:27.15,1:14:29.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as to whether a Shakespeare sonnet was improper.\N去盤問莎士比亞的十四行詩是否得體。
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.63,1:14:33.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Suppose a man who was not an artist had written this letter.\N設想一下，如果一個非藝術家的男人寫下這樣一封信
Dialogue: 0,1:14:33.07,1:14:35.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you say that this was a proper letter?\N你是否會認為它是一封得體的信嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:14:35.25,1:14:37.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A man who was not an artist wouldn't have written that letter.\N一個不是藝術家的男人也寫不出這樣的信。
Dialogue: 0,1:14:37.95,1:14:40.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I can suggest, for the sake of your reputation,\N那麼，我就提示一下，為了你的名譽考慮，
Dialogue: 0,1:14:40.43,1:14:43.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that there're nothing very wonderful in this.\N在這封信裡也沒什麼特別精彩的。
Dialogue: 0,1:14:43.08,1:14:46.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Those red rose leaf lips of yours..."\N“你的紅玫瑰花瓣般的嘴唇。。。”
Dialogue: 0,1:14:46.56,1:14:48.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It largely depends on how it's read.\N這封信主要是取決於怎麼去讀它。
Dialogue: 0,1:14:50.18,1:14:55.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Your slim guilt soul walks between passion and poetry."\N“你的纖細的愧疚心靈行走在激情和詩歌之間。”
Dialogue: 0,1:14:58.05,1:15:00.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that a beautiful phrase, Mr. Wilde?\N這是一個很優美語句嗎？王爾德先生。
Dialogue: 0,1:15:00.75,1:15:03.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not as you read it, Mr. Carson. You read it very badly.\N不是您這樣讀的，卡森先生，你讀得太糟糕了。
Dialogue: 0,1:15:05.19,1:15:07.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I do not profess to be an artist, Mr. Wilde.\N我可不是什麼職業藝術家，王爾德先生。
Dialogue: 0,1:15:07.93,1:15:09.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And when I hear you give evidence,\N當我聽說有證據顯示你是，
Dialogue: 0,1:15:09.41,1:15:11.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've very glad that I am not.\N我很高興我不是。
Dialogue: 0,1:15:11.24,1:15:14.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My Lord, I don't think mylearned friend should talk like that.\N大人，我認為不該以這種方式與我博學的朋友談話。
Dialogue: 0,1:15:14.37,1:15:15.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,May I suggest, Mr. Carson,\N我能提示一下嗎？卡森先生，
Dialogue: 0,1:15:16.03,1:15:19.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that you do not air your personal opinions in this court?\N你在法庭上不該公開發表你個人的觀點。
Dialogue: 0,1:15:20.03,1:15:21.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is very difficult, My Lord.\N這很困難，大人。
Dialogue: 0,1:15:21.60,1:15:23.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,JUDGE: Yet nevertheless.\N法官：盡管如此也不行。
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.91,1:15:28.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where did you first meet the man Wood, Mr. Wilde?\N你第一次遇見那個叫伍德的男人是在什麼地方？王爾德先生。
Dialogue: 0,1:15:28.52,1:15:32.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He came to my house. I think it was in January of 1893.\N他來到我家。我想是在1893年1月。
Dialogue: 0,1:15:32.39,1:15:35.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And on the same evening, you took him out to supper?\N就在同一個晚上，你帶他去吃晚飯？
Dialogue: 0,1:15:35.87,1:15:37.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.\N是的。
Dialogue: 0,1:15:37.44,1:15:40.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you consider that he's come to levy blackmail?\N你是否想過，他是來向你索取敲詐金的嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:15:40.36,1:15:42.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I did, and I was determined to face it.\N我想過，而且我決定要面對這件事。
Dialogue: 0,1:15:42.62,1:15:45.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By taking him out to supper and giving him 40pounds?\N以帶他出去吃晚飯，還給他40英鎊的方法嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:15:45.93,1:15:48.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I saw that the letter was of no value,\N其實，我當時認為那封信沒那麼值錢，
Dialogue: 0,1:15:48.19,1:15:50.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I gave him the money after he told me a pitiful tale\N而我給他錢，是因為他告訴我一個可憐的故事
Dialogue: 0,1:15:50.54,1:15:51.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,about being out of work.\N關於他失業的故事。
Dialogue: 0,1:15:51.89,1:15:54.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I suggest that you had immoral relations\N我提示，你們有不道德的關系
Dialogue: 0,1:15:54.68,1:15:56.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,with him first and then gave him the money.\N第一次見面，就給他錢。
Dialogue: 0,1:15:56.46,1:15:58.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My Lord, I really must protest\N大人，我真的要提出抗議
Dialogue: 0,1:15:58.20,1:16:00.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,at my learned friend's method of questioning the witness.\N抗議這種，提問我博學的朋友的方式。
Dialogue: 0,1:16:00.07,1:16:03.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I do not see that Mr. Carson is in any way out of order.\N我沒有看到卡森先生有擾亂次序的方式。
Dialogue: 0,1:16:06.69,1:16:07.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, My Lord.\N謝謝您，法官大人。
Dialogue: 0,1:16:09.34,1:16:12.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know a man named Charles Parker, Mr. Wilde?\N你認識一個名叫查爾斯帕克的男人嗎？王爾德先生。
Dialogue: 0,1:16:18.09,1:16:20.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The witness will answer the question.\N證人要回答問題。
Dialogue: 0,1:16:22.31,1:16:24.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, he was a friend of Lord Alfred's.\N是的，他是阿爾弗雷德勳爵的朋友。
Dialogue: 0,1:16:25.01,1:16:26.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And a man named Atkin?\N還有一個叫阿特金的人?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:28.01,1:16:29.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, he was a friend of Parker's.\N是的，他是帕克的朋友。
Dialogue: 0,1:16:29.71,1:16:32.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A man named Grainger?\N還有一個叫格林傑的男人？
Dialogue: 0,1:16:32.23,1:16:34.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, he was a manservant of Lord Alfred's.\N是的，他是阿爾弗雷德勳爵的僕人。
Dialogue: 0,1:16:34.89,1:16:38.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And Taylor, Mr. Wilde. Do you know anyone called Taylor?\N還有泰勒，王爾德先生。 你認識叫泰勒的人嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:16:38.94,1:16:41.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I have been to parties at his house. We...\N是的，我去過他家的聚會。 我們。。。 \N
Dialogue: 0,1:16:41.68,1:16:46.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Were all these, with the exception of Taylor, young men of about 20?\N除了泰勒，所有這些人都是20歲左右的年輕人嗎?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:46.64,1:16:49.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I like the society of young men.\N我喜歡和年輕人交往。
Dialogue: 0,1:16:49.43,1:16:51.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you given money to any of them?\N你給過他們中的任何一個嗎？ \N
Dialogue: 0,1:16:52.91,1:16:54.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I may have.\N我也許給過。
Dialogue: 0,1:16:54.26,1:16:55.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or presents?\N禮物呢？
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.35,1:16:59.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A silver cigarette case for Mr. Taylor,\N給泰勒先生的一個銀質香煙盒，
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.31,1:17:03.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,gold-topped walking stick for Mr. Parker,\N給派克先生的有鍍金頭的手杖，
Dialogue: 0,1:17:03.53,1:17:08.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a book for Mr. Wood inscribed, "To Alfred from Oscar."\N一本給伍德先生的書，上題寫，“給阿爾弗雷德，自奧斯卡。”
Dialogue: 0,1:17:11.06,1:17:13.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you know, Mr. Wilde,\N以下這些你知道嗎？王爾德先生，
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.62,1:17:16.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that Wood had been unemployed for three years,\N伍德先生已經失業三年了，
Dialogue: 0,1:17:16.24,1:17:20.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that Parker was a valet, and that the man Taylor was also out of work?\N帕克是個男僕，而那個叫泰勒的人也沒工作。
Dialogue: 0,1:17:20.59,1:17:22.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That would not have affected my friendship with them.\N那這也不影響我和他們的友誼啊。
Dialogue: 0,1:17:22.72,1:17:26.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And yet you gave them presents and entertained them to supper on diverse occasions.\N可你卻送他們禮物和在不同的場合請他們吃晚飯。
Dialogue: 0,1:17:26.64,1:17:28.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No doubt you drank wine and champagne.\N無疑你們喝了紅酒和香檳。
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.03,1:17:31.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Iced champagne is a favorite drink of mine,\N冰鎮香檳是我最喜歡的飲料，
Dialogue: 0,1:17:31.29,1:17:32.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,much against my doctor't orders.\N卻違背了我的醫生的囑咐。
Dialogue: 0,1:17:32.73,1:17:34.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Never mind your doctor's orders.\N不管醫生的囑咐。
Dialogue: 0,1:17:34.30,1:17:35.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I never do.\N我從不。
Dialogue: 0,1:17:37.91,1:17:39.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And at these supper parties\N在晚餐聚會上
Dialogue: 0,1:17:39.95,1:17:42.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,your guests no doubt had plenty of champagne.\N你的賓客肯定是暢飲香檳。
Dialogue: 0,1:17:42.35,1:17:43.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't press them to drink.\N我從不強迫他們喝酒。
Dialogue: 0,1:17:43.57,1:17:44.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You did not stint them?\N那你有沒有限制他們？
Dialogue: 0,1:17:44.92,1:17:47.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What gentleman would stint his guests?\N一個紳士會限制他的客人嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:17:47.18,1:17:50.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What gentleman would stint his valet and a groom, Mr. Wilde?\N什麼樣的紳士會限制他的男僕和馬夫呢？王爾德先生。
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.75,1:17:53.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My Lord, I really must protest at my learned friend's sneering remarks.\N法官大人，我抗議我的博學朋友被這樣嘲笑戲弄。
Dialogue: 0,1:17:53.66,1:17:58.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Carson, I suggest you confine yourself to questions, not opinions.\N卡森先生，我提示你，限定在你的問題，而不是你的觀點。
Dialogue: 0,1:17:59.37,1:18:00.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very well, My Lord.\N好的，法官大人。
Dialogue: 0,1:18:04.54,1:18:07.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you know, Mr. Wilde,\N你知道嗎，王爾德先生，
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.11,1:18:09.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that Taylor, Atkin and Parker\N泰勒，阿特金和帕克
Dialogue: 0,1:18:09.55,1:18:13.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,had been arrested in a raid on a house in Fitzroy Square?\N在對菲茨羅伊廣場一所房子的洗劫中被捕。
Dialogue: 0,1:18:13.38,1:18:15.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I read about that.\N是的，我在報紙上讀到過。
Dialogue: 0,1:18:15.34,1:18:18.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know that they were charged with felonious practices?\N你是否知道他們被控以重罪？
Dialogue: 0,1:18:18.65,1:18:21.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand that the magistrate dismissed the charge.\N據我了解，地方法官駁回了控告。
Dialogue: 0,1:18:21.91,1:18:24.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,About the young man Grainger.\N關於那個叫格蘭傑的年輕人。
Dialogue: 0,1:18:26.44,1:18:28.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you ever dined with him?\N你是否曾經和他一起吃過晚飯？
Dialogue: 0,1:18:28.35,1:18:29.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, never.\N不，從沒有。
Dialogue: 0,1:18:30.18,1:18:32.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you know him?\N但你認識他？
Dialogue: 0,1:18:32.14,1:18:36.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, he was a manservant at Lord Alfred's house in Oxford.\N是的，他是阿爾弗雷德勳爵在牛津時的家僕
Dialogue: 0,1:18:36.14,1:18:37.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you saw him on several occasions?\N所以你幾次見到他 ？
Dialogue: 0,1:18:37.93,1:18:39.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I stayed in the house on several occasions.\N因為我幾次去過勳爵的房子。
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.93,1:18:40.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grainger waited at table.\N格蘭傑在旁伺候。
Dialogue: 0,1:18:43.02,1:18:46.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you ever kiss him, Mr. Wilde?\N你是否親吻過他，王爾德先生?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:46.59,1:18:48.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, dear, no. He was extremely ugly.\N哦，天吶，不，他太丑了。
Dialogue: 0,1:19:00.43,1:19:02.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that the reason you did not kiss him?\N這就是你沒有親他的原因嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:19:03.34,1:19:04.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Carson, you are very insolent.\N卡森先生，你太無禮了。
Dialogue: 0,1:19:05.00,1:19:07.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you say that you never kissed him?\N你是說，你從沒有親過他嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:19:07.13,1:19:08.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a foolish question.\N這是一個愚蠢的問題。
Dialogue: 0,1:19:08.91,1:19:11.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why, sir, did you mention that this boy was extremely ugly?\N那麼為什麼，先生，你剛才是否說過這個男孩很丑？
Dialogue: 0,1:19:11.65,1:19:13.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know why I mentioned that he was ugly\N我不知道為什麼我說他很丑
Dialogue: 0,1:19:13.35,1:19:15.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,except that you stunned me with your insolent remark\N除非你的無禮之舉已經深深地擊暈了我
Dialogue: 0,1:19:15.09,1:19:17.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the insulting way you're treated me during this hearing.\N還有，在這場庭審中你對我的侮辱方式。
Dialogue: 0,1:19:17.05,1:19:19.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you mention his ugliness?\N為什麼你要說他丑陋？
Dialogue: 0,1:19:19.14,1:19:20.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was simply that I...\N這很簡單，因為我。。。
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.45,1:19:21.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why? Why? Why?\N為什麼？為什麼？為什麼?\N
Dialogue: 0,1:19:21.88,1:19:24.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I didn't kiss Grainger because he was ugly."\N"我沒有親格蘭傑是因為他很丑。"
Dialogue: 0,1:19:24.15,1:19:26.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quite untrue... I protest, My Lord, at his accusations.\N他的指控不合情理。。。我抗議，法官大人。
Dialogue: 0,1:19:26.10,1:19:27.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My learned friend puts words into the witness's?mouth.\N我的博學朋友是作為證人發言的。
Dialogue: 0,1:19:27.80,1:19:29.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The witness is putting words into his own mouth.\N證人已經親口說出了這些話。
Dialogue: 0,1:19:29.76,1:19:31.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-I object.     -I will not have this brawling between counsels.\N-我反對。   -我不想再發生律師之間的爭吵。
Dialogue: 0,1:19:32.02,1:19:33.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I may say so, My Lord,\N我可以這麼說嗎？法官大人，
Dialogue: 0,1:19:33.98,1:19:35.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,my learned friend has no right to make suggestions of a certain behavior\N我的博學朋友已經沒有對他的某種行為做出提示的權利
Dialogue: 0,1:19:35.94,1:19:37.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,with a group of persons not represented in this court\N就因為一幫沒有出庭的人\N
Dialogue: 0,1:19:38.03,1:19:39.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and whose evidence we have not heard.\N而隨之而來的證據我們卻從未聽說過。
Dialogue: 0,1:19:39.42,1:19:41.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you will hear it, Sir Edward.\N但是你會聽到的，愛德華爵士。
Dialogue: 0,1:19:41.34,1:19:43.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is my intention to produce every one of the persons mentioned here\N我打算把這裡提到的每一個人
Dialogue: 0,1:19:43.73,1:19:46.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,just now in this courtroom tomorrow morning.\N明天上午都帶到法庭來。
Dialogue: 0,1:19:46.25,1:19:48.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wood, Parker, Atkin, Grainger and Taylor\N伍德，帕克，阿特金，格林格和泰勒
Dialogue: 0,1:19:48.60,1:19:51.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,will relate their loathsome experiences at the hands of the witness.\N他們會把自己令人憎惡的經歷與這位證人聯系起來。
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.43,1:19:54.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By your own admission, a group of blackmailers and police suspects, sir.\N你要承認，這是一幫敲詐者和警方懷疑者，先生。
Dialogue: 0,1:19:54.09,1:19:56.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nevertheless,they'll be here to give their testimony,\N然而，他們會在這裡給出他們的證詞，
Dialogue: 0,1:19:56.35,1:19:59.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,testimony that will prove my client's plea of justification\N他們的證詞將證明，我的當事人的釋罪辯解
Dialogue: 0,1:19:59.66,1:20:01.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,beyond any possible shadow of a doubt.\N是沒有任何疑問陰影的。
Dialogue: 0,1:20:02.88,1:20:04.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Silence in court.\N肅靜。
Dialogue: 0,1:20:04.62,1:20:07.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think this would be an appropriate moment to adjourn.\N我認為現在是休庭的合適時機。
Dialogue: 0,1:20:07.93,1:20:09.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The witness may stand down.\N證人退席。
Dialogue: 0,1:20:15.20,1:20:18.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The court will reconvene at 10:00 a.m. tomorrow.\N再次開庭定於明天上午10點。
Dialogue: 0,1:20:19.64,1:20:21.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be upstanding in court.\N全體起立。
Dialogue: 0,1:20:22.81,1:20:25.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All persons who have anything further to do\N所有與本案下一步審理有關人員
Dialogue: 0,1:20:25.51,1:20:28.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,before My Lords,the Queen's justices of oyer and terminer...\N在面對陪審團，女王陛下的法官時。。。\N
Dialogue: 0,1:20:34.91,1:20:37.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Before this unfortunate trial started,\N這場不幸的審判開始之前。。。
Dialogue: 0,1:20:37.04,1:20:39.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you gave me your word that there was no truth whatever\N你向我保證他們的可怕指責
Dialogue: 0,1:20:39.18,1:20:41.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in any of these dreadful accusations.\N無論如何都沒有任何真實的成分。
Dialogue: 0,1:20:41.48,1:20:45.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know, Sir Edward. It was unforgivably stupid of me,\N我知道，愛德華爵士，我的愚蠢是不可饒恕的，
Dialogue: 0,1:20:45.36,1:20:48.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I was afraid you wouldn't take the case.\N我當時擔心您不接受這個案子。
Dialogue: 0,1:20:50.14,1:20:52.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As it is,you realize you've already lost this case.\N那現在，你應該意識到，官司已經輸了。
Dialogue: 0,1:20:53.41,1:20:55.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But what is infinitely more serious\N但事態嚴重性會擴大
Dialogue: 0,1:20:55.19,1:20:57.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is that when Carson puts these young men into the witness box,\N當卡森把那幾個年輕人帶到證人席，
Dialogue: 0,1:20:57.80,1:21:00.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as he obviously intends to do,\N他顯然想要這樣做，
Dialogue: 0,1:21:00.24,1:21:03.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,their evidence will inevitably result in your being arrested\N那幾個年輕人的作證最終會導致你被捕
Dialogue: 0,1:21:03.24,1:21:05.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,on some extremely grave charges.\N而且你將背負幾項非常嚴重的指控。
Dialogue: 0,1:21:05.94,1:21:08.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Edward, may I just say one thing?\N愛德華爵士，我可以說一件事嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.38,1:21:10.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please do.\N請講。
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.43,1:21:14.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The whole case started with my father accusing Mr. Wilde of carrying on an...\N整件事情開頭，是由我父親指責王爾德先生與我
Dialogue: 0,1:21:14.26,1:21:16.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An immoral relationship with me, isn't that so?\N有著不正當的關系，是吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:21:17.26,1:21:18.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.\N是的。
Dialogue: 0,1:21:19.00,1:21:20.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why in heaven't name can I not go into the witness box\N那為什麼我的名字沒有被列入證人名單
Dialogue: 0,1:21:20.70,1:21:22.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-and deny this disgusting accusation?    -Bosie, for the last time.\N-由我去否認這些令人惡心的職責？  -波西，最後一次。
Dialogue: 0,1:21:22.70,1:21:24.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-But it isn't true, Oscar.  -You know it isn't.\N-但它不是真實的，奧斯卡。  -你知道啥呀。
Dialogue: 0,1:21:24.27,1:21:25.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Such a denial would undoubtedly add\N這樣的否認無疑會增加
Dialogue: 0,1:21:25.88,1:21:27.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,considerable weight, Mr. Wilde.\N有力的說服力，王爾德先生。
Dialogue: 0,1:21:27.97,1:21:32.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In my opinion, not to put Lord Alfred into the box would be a grave mistake.\N以我看，不把阿爾弗雷德勳爵列入證人席是一個很嚴重的失誤。
Dialogue: 0,1:21:32.10,1:21:34.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One that you might regret for the rest of your life.\N一個讓你後悔一輩子的失誤
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.32,1:21:39.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gentlemen, I have infinite faith in the good sense of the common man,\N先生們，我一直對好人有好報會有極大的信心，
Dialogue: 0,1:21:39.76,1:21:41.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and if, as you say, this case hangs\N假如，像你們說的，這個案子被
Dialogue: 0,1:21:41.41,1:21:43.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,on the evidence of paid informers\N通過收買而來的證據所絞死
Dialogue: 0,1:21:43.81,1:21:45.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and criminals like Wood and Parker,\N包括被像伍德和帕克這樣的罪犯，
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.72,1:21:48.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I cannot conceive that a British jury would take their word before mine.\N我都無法想象那些不列顛的陪審員們在我面前怎麼開口。
Dialogue: 0,1:21:50.07,1:21:51.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wish I could share your faith.\N我希望我也能有你一樣的信心。
Dialogue: 0,1:21:53.34,1:21:54.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, what must be must be.\N那麼，該來的就讓它來吧。
Dialogue: 0,1:21:54.91,1:21:56.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I want you to understand that Lord Alfred is not\N我想你會理解為什麼不把阿爾弗雷德勳爵
Dialogue: 0,1:21:56.65,1:21:57.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to give evidence at this trial.\N列入審判的證人席。
Dialogue: 0,1:21:59.13,1:22:01.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very well.\N好吧。
Dialogue: 0,1:22:01.09,1:22:04.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I shall endeavor to salvage what is left of your reputation\N那麼，我將盡力挽救你還殘存的名譽
Dialogue: 0,1:22:04.18,1:22:07.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,by withdrawing from the case first thing in the morning.\N上午要做的第一件事就是撤訴。
Dialogue: 0,1:22:07.44,1:22:11.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Incidentally, there's no need for you to be present in court tomorrow.\N順便說一句，明天你不用親自到庭。
Dialogue: 0,1:22:11.57,1:22:13.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed there's no need for you to be present in this country.\N其實，你真的沒有必要在這個國家出現。
Dialogue: 0,1:22:16.36,1:22:19.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is a boat train leaving for Calais at 10:00 tonight, Mr. Wilde.\N今晚十點有一趟開往加來的班輪，王爾德先生。\N（法國城市，與英國隔海峽相望）
Dialogue: 0,1:22:20.76,1:22:21.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're be well advised to be on it.\N聽我勸，你最好上船。
Dialogue: 0,1:22:24.54,1:22:26.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Before you condemn Lord Queensberry,\N在你們判罪昆斯博裡之前，
Dialogue: 0,1:22:26.81,1:22:29.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I ask you to consider whether the gorge of any father ought\N我請求諸位思考一下，在這種情況下
Dialogue: 0,1:22:29.90,1:22:32.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,not to rise in such circumstances.\N是否該提倡吞噬生父這種行為
Dialogue: 0,1:22:32.20,1:22:34.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I ask you to bear in mind that Lord Queensberry's son\N我請你們記住，昆斯博裡侯爵的兒子
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.03,1:22:39.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was so dominated by Wilde that he threatened to shoot his own father.\N是受到王爾德的操控，而向自己父親開槍的。
Dialogue: 0,1:22:39.43,1:22:43.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I now have a more painful part of the case to approach.\N我現在已經接近到了這樁案子的最痛苦的地方。
Dialogue: 0,1:22:43.26,1:22:45.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my unhappy duty to bring before you young men...\N我真不願意把這幾個年輕人帶到你們面前。。。
Dialogue: 0,1:22:45.22,1:22:48.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Did Wilde get away?    -No.\N-王爾德先生逃了嗎？  -不。
Dialogue: 0,1:22:48.05,1:22:50.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...to tell their miserable tales.\N。。。告訴你們他們的痛苦遭遇。
Dialogue: 0,1:22:50.74,1:22:53.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I first call Charles Parker.\N我首先召查爾斯帕克到庭。
Dialogue: 0,1:22:53.14,1:22:55.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,May I claim Your Lordship's indulgence while I interpose\N法官大人，我能不能冒昧地插斷一下，
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.88,1:22:57.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to make a statement, which is, of course,\N做個聲明，當然
Dialogue: 0,1:22:57.66,1:22:59.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,made under a feeling of great responsibility?\N這個聲明也是在強烈的責任感驅使下做的？\N
Dialogue: 0,1:22:59.80,1:23:02.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By all means, Sir Edward.\N當然可以，愛德華爵士。
Dialogue: 0,1:23:02.06,1:23:03.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive me, Mr. Carson.\N原諒我，卡森先生。
Dialogue: 0,1:23:05.24,1:23:06.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure it must be apparent to Your Lordship\N我想法官大人您一定很明白
Dialogue: 0,1:23:06.85,1:23:09.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that those who represent Mr. Wilde in this case\N那些在本案站在王爾德先生立場的人們
Dialogue: 0,1:23:09.68,1:23:12.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,have before them a terrible anxiety.\N面臨著很恐怖的焦慮。
Dialogue: 0,1:23:12.90,1:23:15.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A verdict given in favor of the defendant Lord Queensberry\N一個對被告，昆斯博裡侯爵有利的判決
Dialogue: 0,1:23:15.94,1:23:20.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,might be interpreted as conclusive proof as to the accusations of impropriety\N會被演繹成指責傷風敗俗的真憑實據
Dialogue: 0,1:23:20.38,1:23:23.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,brought against the plaintiff, Mr. Oscar Wilde\N而它是針對原告，王爾德先生的
Dialogue: 0,1:23:23.60,1:23:25.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and thus, we would be going through,\N既然這樣，我們可能會經受
Dialogue: 0,1:23:25.60,1:23:29.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,day after day, an investigation of matters of the most appalling nature.\N日復一日的調查，而真相會是令人震驚的。
Dialogue: 0,1:23:30.04,1:23:31.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Under these circumstances,\N在這種情況下，
Dialogue: 0,1:23:31.78,1:23:34.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I feel I am not going beyond the bounds of my duty\N我覺得我不會再繼續的的職責
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.27,1:23:37.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if I now interpose and say on behalf of Mr. Wilde\N如果現在我為王爾德先生的利益調停
Dialogue: 0,1:23:37.18,1:23:39.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that I would ask to withdraw from the prosecution.\N那麼我將撤回起訴。
Dialogue: 0,1:23:39.97,1:23:42.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that is your wish, Sir Edward, so be it.\N如果這是你的意願，愛德華爵士，那就如你所願吧。
Dialogue: 0,1:23:42.75,1:23:43.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,COURT USHER: Silence.\N庭警：肅靜。
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.01,1:23:45.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And if I may say so in the circumstances,\N在這種情況下，如果讓我說的話，
Dialogue: 0,1:23:45.84,1:23:47.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think you have made a wise decision.\N我認為您做了個明智的決定。
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.84,1:23:49.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you taking a cab? Yes, come on.\N你還不快去叫輛馬車？是的，馬上。
Dialogue: 0,1:23:49.63,1:23:51.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get this to the office as soon as you can.\N你把這個盡可能快地送到辦公室。
Dialogue: 0,1:23:51.33,1:23:53.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Oscar Wilde withdraws from case."\N“奧斯卡王爾德撤訴”
Dialogue: 0,1:23:53.85,1:23:56.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Take a cab and hurry.   -Yes, sir.\N-打輛車，快點。  -是的，先生。
Dialogue: 0,1:23:56.85,1:24:02.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Either the words complained of were justified or they were not.\N不管這些抱怨的文字是否公正。
Dialogue: 0,1:24:02.34,1:24:06.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If they were, then the statement, "posing as a sodomite"\N如果是，那麼“表演地像個雞奸者”的陳述
Dialogue: 0,1:24:06.12,1:24:10.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is true and the publication was for the public benefit.\N就是真實的，而它的公布是符合公共利益的。
Dialogue: 0,1:24:10.04,1:24:12.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You will now consider your verdict.\N你們現在考慮你們的判決。
Dialogue: 0,1:24:17.61,1:24:19.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've already agreed upon a verdict, My Lord.\N我們已經有了判決，法官大人。
Dialogue: 0,1:24:21.66,1:24:22.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The prisoner will rise.\N被告起立。
Dialogue: 0,1:24:27.14,1:24:28.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gentlemen of the jury, do you find\N陪審團的先生們，你們是否查明了
Dialogue: 0,1:24:28.62,1:24:31.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the plea of justification has been proved or not?\N釋罪申辯已經被證明了,還是沒有?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.45,1:24:32.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We do.\N我們查明了。
Dialogue: 0,1:24:32.89,1:24:35.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And do you find the defendant guilty or not guilty?\N那你們查明了被告是有罪還是無罪？
Dialogue: 0,1:24:35.63,1:24:36.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not guilty, My Lord.\N無罪，法官大人。
Dialogue: 0,1:24:38.50,1:24:41.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Silence in court! Silence! Silence!\N肅靜！肅靜！肅靜！
Dialogue: 0,1:24:41.72,1:24:43.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Usher, silence the court.\N庭警，肅靜。
Dialogue: 0,1:24:43.94,1:24:44.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Usher!\N庭警！
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.60,1:24:48.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, they haven't wasted any time.\N這下，他們沒有浪費任何時間。
Dialogue: 0,1:24:48.30,1:24:49.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why, what do you mean?\N什麼，你什麼意思？
Dialogue: 0,1:24:49.69,1:24:51.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A copy of the evidence has already been sent\N證據的副本已被送達
Dialogue: 0,1:24:51.60,1:24:52.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to the Director of Public Prosecutions.\N公訴檢察官那裡。
Dialogue: 0,1:25:03.75,1:25:07.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bosie, for God's sake, stop walking up and down.\N波西，看在上帝的份兒上，停止走來走去吧。
Dialogue: 0,1:25:17.98,1:25:19.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.\N哦。
Dialogue: 0,1:25:19.59,1:25:21.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you haven't eaten a thing, sir.\N哦，你一點兒都沒吃，先生。
Dialogue: 0,1:25:23.03,1:25:24.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't really want it.\N我吃不下。
Dialogue: 0,1:25:25.16,1:25:26.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Arthur.\N謝謝你，阿瑟。
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.52,1:25:38.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oscar, I've just heard from one of the reporters.\N奧斯卡，我從一個記者那裡聽說。
Dialogue: 0,1:25:38.43,1:25:39.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a warrant out for your arrest.\N有一張你的逮捕令。
Dialogue: 0,1:25:42.44,1:25:43.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about Constance and the children?\N那康斯坦斯和孩子們怎麼辦？
Dialogue: 0,1:25:45.22,1:25:47.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw them off on the train myself.\N我親眼看著他們上了火車。
Dialogue: 0,1:25:49.05,1:25:49.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Robbie.\N謝謝你，羅比。
Dialogue: 0,1:25:51.10,1:25:52.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oscar, I beg of you.\N奧斯卡，我求你。
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.45,1:25:53.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's still time to catch the 10:00 train.\N現在還來得及趕上10點的火車。
Dialogue: 0,1:25:53.75,1:25:54.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have a cab waiting outside.\N我有一輛馬車等在外面。
Dialogue: 0,1:25:54.93,1:25:57.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've wasting your time, Robbie.\N你在耽誤你的時間，羅比。
Dialogue: 0,1:25:57.06,1:25:59.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been trying for the past two hours.\N過去兩小時，我一直在勸他。
Dialogue: 0,1:25:59.32,1:26:01.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oscar, will you please listen to me?\N奧斯卡，你能聽我的嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:26:01.59,1:26:03.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-It's too late.   -It's not too late, I tell you.\N-太晚了。   -我告訴你，還不晚。
Dialogue: 0,1:26:03.41,1:26:05.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Look, it's 9:35.   -Oh, Robbie, have a drink.\N-看，現在9：35.  -噢，羅比，喝杯酒吧。
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.37,1:26:06.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In three hours we can be in France.\N三小時後我們就到法國了。
Dialogue: 0,1:26:06.81,1:26:08.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You look as if you need it.\N看來是你需要離開。
Dialogue: 0,1:26:32.09,1:26:34.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Mr. Wilde?   -Yes.\N-王爾德先生？  -是的。
Dialogue: 0,1:26:34.40,1:26:36.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're police officers. We hold a warrant for your arrest.\N我們是警官，我們有一張你的逮捕令。
Dialogue: 0,1:26:38.10,1:26:40.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?\N是嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:26:40.15,1:26:42.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I must ask you to accompany us to the police station.\N我必須要帶你去警察局。
Dialogue: 0,1:26:54.55,1:26:57.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bosie, do something for me.\N波西，替我做幾件事。
Dialogue: 0,1:26:57.90,1:26:59.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anything.\N任何事都行。
Dialogue: 0,1:26:59.34,1:27:01.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave the country. If possible, tonight.\N如果有可能，今晚就出國。
Dialogue: 0,1:27:02.78,1:27:04.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-I can't desert you.    -Bosie, please.\N-我不能拋下你。  -波西，聽我的。
Dialogue: 0,1:27:09.00,1:27:10.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very well.\N好吧。
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.05,1:27:13.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So it's goodbye, hmm?\N這就是告別嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:27:13.83,1:27:15.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Oscar, I can't believe...    -Goodbye.\N-奧斯卡，不敢相信。。。  -再見。
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.96,1:27:17.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll come with you.\N我們和你一起去。
Dialogue: 0,1:27:17.44,1:27:19.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-There'll be no need for that, sir.    -Thank you.\N-沒有必要，先生。    -謝謝你。
Dialogue: 0,1:27:47.39,1:27:49.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you look at me like that?\N你為什麼那樣看我？
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.91,1:27:51.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not my fault.\N這不是我的錯。
Dialogue: 0,1:27:51.35,1:27:53.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I loved him just as much as you did.\N我和你一樣愛他。
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.48,1:27:55.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think if there was anything I could have...\N難道你不認為我會為他做任何事情。。。
Dialogue: 0,1:27:55.31,1:27:56.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can do as Oscar says, Bosie.\N按照奧斯卡的話去做，波西。
Dialogue: 0,1:27:58.70,1:27:59.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave the country.\N出國。
Dialogue: 0,1:28:04.62,1:28:06.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the sooner the better, I should say.\N越早越好，我說的。
Dialogue: 0,1:28:36.18,1:28:37.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Lord Queensberry is triumphant.\N“昆斯博裡侯爵勝利了."
Dialogue: 0,1:28:37.87,1:28:40.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Mr. Oscar Wilde is damned and done forever."\N“奧斯卡王爾德先生永遠被詛咒。”
Dialogue: 0,1:28:40.44,1:28:41.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And about time.\N時報怎麼評論。
Dialogue: 0,1:28:41.92,1:28:43.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-"Public morality will be vindicated."   -Hear, hear.\N-“公共道德將被維護."  -好，好。
Dialogue: 0,1:28:43.70,1:28:47.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"And this evil in our midst will, I hope, be removed forever."\N“我希望，這種在我們中間的罪惡將永遠被去除。”
Dialogue: 0,1:28:47.67,1:28:49.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn good thing, too. I never liked the fellow from the first.\N這也太他媽的痛快了，我一開始就不喜歡這個家伙。
Dialogue: 0,1:28:49.97,1:28:53.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Couldn't stand his plays. Lot of immoral rubbish.\N真受不了他的戲劇，裡面有太多不道德的垃圾。
Dialogue: 0,1:28:53.24,1:28:55.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it all, Bentley, the fellow hasn't been tried yet.\N該死的，賓利，這家伙還沒有被審呢。
Dialogue: 0,1:28:55.37,1:28:57.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Innocent until proved guilty and all that sort of...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:57.50,1:28:58.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he's been in my regiment, sir,\N如果他在我的團裡，爵士，
Dialogue: 0,1:28:59.02,1:29:01.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he's have been lashed to a gun carriage and flogged.\N他將被綁在炮架上挨鞭子。
Dialogue: 0,1:29:01.16,1:29:03.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These artistic chaps are all the same.\N這些文藝青年都一個德性。
Dialogue: 0,1:29:03.64,1:29:05.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A lot of long-haired degenerates.\N留著長頭發的頹廢派。
Dialogue: 0,1:29:05.51,1:29:07.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think you fellows are taking the whole damn thing too seriously.\N我認為你們哥兒幾個把整個事情看得過份嚴重了。
Dialogue: 0,1:29:07.99,1:29:09.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Live and let live, that's what I say.\N別理它們，把它們放一邊，這就是我想說的。
Dialogue: 0,1:29:09.73,1:29:11.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, I don't care what they do\N無論如何，我都不介意他們做什麼
Dialogue: 0,1:29:11.60,1:29:13.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as long as they don't do it in the street and frighten the horses.\N只要他們不在街上做，不嚇到馬就行。
Dialogue: 0,1:29:27.57,1:29:29.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right.\N好吧。
Dialogue: 0,1:29:35.32,1:29:37.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you want me to burn them, Mr. Brace?\N你想讓我焚燒書籍嗎？布雷斯先生。
Dialogue: 0,1:29:37.11,1:29:40.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good heavens, no. Fellow might get off.\N上帝啊，不，那個家伙也許會免責。
Dialogue: 0,1:29:58.43,1:29:59.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Humphries.\N漢弗萊斯先生。
Dialogue: 0,1:30:00.39,1:30:01.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Edward.\N愛德華爵士。
Dialogue: 0,1:30:01.61,1:30:04.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I... They didn't tell me that it was you.\N我。。。他們沒有告訴我這會是你們。
Dialogue: 0,1:30:07.05,1:30:08.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Wilde.\N王爾德先生。
Dialogue: 0,1:30:10.49,1:30:14.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what arrangements you're made about your defense,\N我不知道你為了你的辯護做了什麼安排，
Dialogue: 0,1:30:16.45,1:30:18.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but if you wish it,\N但是如果你願意，
Dialogue: 0,1:30:18.15,1:30:20.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Edward and I would be most happy to act on your behalf.\N愛德華爵士和我將很樂意站為你代理。
Dialogue: 0,1:30:22.50,1:30:24.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, I'm...   I'm very grateful.\N謝謝你們，我。。。 我感激不盡。
Dialogue: 0,1:30:24.98,1:30:27.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are certain legal aspects of this case, Mr. Wilde,\N這個案子裡有一個確定的法律問題，王爾德先生
Dialogue: 0,1:30:27.42,1:30:29.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that have shocked me greatly.\N這個問題是我很震驚。
Dialogue: 0,1:30:29.33,1:30:32.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The prosecution has based its entire case on the evidence of witnesses\N控方在本案中舉出的證人都被證明\N
Dialogue: 0,1:30:32.20,1:30:38.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who admitted crimes ranging from assault, petty larceny to blackmail.\N他們承認犯有搶劫，小偷小摸和敲詐勒索。\N
Dialogue: 0,1:30:38.73,1:30:41.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yet the Crown has no intention of prosecuting any of these witnesses.\N而最高法院卻沒有打算，檢控其中任何一個證人
Dialogue: 0,1:30:41.82,1:30:43.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They are to go scot-free.\N他們都安然逃脫。
Dialogue: 0,1:30:44.56,1:30:46.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Such a state of affairs has profoundly shaken\N居然會有這種事情發生，它極大地震撼了
Dialogue: 0,1:30:46.52,1:30:49.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,my inherent faith in British justice.\N我對不列顛法律公正的固有信心
Dialogue: 0,1:30:49.13,1:30:51.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In these circumstances, I would consider it an honor,\N在這種情況下，我將為榮譽而戰，
Dialogue: 0,1:30:51.70,1:30:53.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if you'll permit me to offer my services.\N如果您願意讓我為您效勞。
Dialogue: 0,1:30:55.14,1:30:57.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.\N謝謝您。
Dialogue: 0,1:30:57.10,1:31:00.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm afraid the cost of the other case is still unpaid,\N我恐怕其他案件的費用還沒有付清，
Dialogue: 0,1:31:00.28,1:31:01.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I'm in considerable debt.\N可我卻欠了不少債。
Dialogue: 0,1:31:04.19,1:31:05.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Wilde,\N王爾德先生，
Dialogue: 0,1:31:05.98,1:31:09.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Edward and I are agreed that there is no question of a fee.\N愛德華爵士和我都同意費用不是問題。
Dialogue: 0,1:31:11.20,1:31:12.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.\N謝謝你們。
Dialogue: 0,1:31:13.38,1:31:14.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.\N謝謝你們。
Dialogue: 0,1:31:14.99,1:31:17.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, there are many matters we should discuss, Mr. Wilde.\N那麼，這兒有很多問題我們要討論，王爾德先生。
Dialogue: 0,1:31:22.21,1:31:26.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,CLERK: Put up Oscar Fingal O'Flahertie Wills Wilde.\N書記員：帶奧斯卡·芬達爾·奧弗萊赫蒂·威爾斯·王爾德到庭
Dialogue: 0,1:31:26.21,1:31:28.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oscar Fingal O'Flahertie Wills Wilde.\N奧斯卡·芬達爾·奧弗萊赫蒂·威爾斯·王爾德
Dialogue: 0,1:31:32.18,1:31:34.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,COURT USHER: Silence in court. Silence!    JUDGE: Order. Order.\N庭警：肅靜。肅靜！   法官：秩序。秩序。
Dialogue: 0,1:31:37.79,1:31:40.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,CLERK: Are you Oscar Fingal O'Flahertie Wills Wilde?\N書記員：您是奧斯卡·芬達爾·奧弗萊赫蒂·威爾斯·王爾德 ？
Dialogue: 0,1:31:40.93,1:31:42.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am.\N我是。
Dialogue: 0,1:31:42.14,1:31:43.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oscar Fingal O'Flahertie Wills Wilde,\N奧斯卡·芬達爾·奧弗萊赫蒂·威爾斯·王爾德
Dialogue: 0,1:31:43.97,1:31:46.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you stand charged on 25 counts.\N您有25項指控。
Dialogue: 0,1:31:48.89,1:31:52.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the first count, the jurors for Our Lady, the Queen, upon their oath\N第一項，由宣誓效忠女王陛下的陪審團
Dialogue: 0,1:31:52.63,1:31:56.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,present that Oscar Fingal O'Flahertie Wills Wilde,\N向法庭提交奧斯卡·芬達爾·奧弗萊赫蒂·威爾斯·王爾德
Dialogue: 0,1:31:56.33,1:32:00.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,on 14th day of March in the year of Our Lord 1893,\N於1893年3月14日
Dialogue: 0,1:32:00.77,1:32:03.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in the County of London and within the jurisdiction of this court,\N在倫敦郡，在本法院的管轄范圍內，
Dialogue: 0,1:32:03.77,1:32:08.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,being a male person, unlawfully did commit acts of gross indecency\N作為一個男人，涉嫌非法嚴重猥褻
Dialogue: 0,1:32:08.47,1:32:12.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,with another male person, one Alfred Wood.\N另一名男人，阿爾弗雷德 伍德
Dialogue: 0,1:32:12.78,1:32:16.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And against the form of the statuette in such case made and provided,\N在這種情況下以傷風敗俗的形式
Dialogue: 0,1:32:16.61,1:32:18.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and against the peace of Our Lady the Queen,\N擾亂在女王陛下的
Dialogue: 0,1:32:18.70,1:32:20.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,her crown and dignity.\N王權和尊嚴治下的治安。
Dialogue: 0,1:32:21.88,1:32:25.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the second count, the juries aforesaid...\N第二項，前述陪審團。。。
Dialogue: 0,1:32:25.58,1:32:29.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...against the form of the statute in such case made and provided\N以傷風敗俗的形式
Dialogue: 0,1:32:29.89,1:32:34.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and against the peace of our said Lady the Queen, her crown and dignity.\N擾亂女王陛下的王權和尊嚴治下的治安。
Dialogue: 0,1:32:36.63,1:32:40.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oscar Fingal O'Flahertie Wills Wilde,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:40.64,1:32:43.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,on the aforesaid indictments, how do you plead?\N依前所述的指控，你有什麼申辯的？
Dialogue: 0,1:32:43.77,1:32:45.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guilty or not guilty?\N有罪還是無罪？
Dialogue: 0,1:32:47.08,1:32:48.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not guilty.\N無罪。
Dialogue: 0,1:32:50.43,1:32:53.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My Lord, gentlemen of the jury,\N法官大人，陪審團各位先生們，
Dialogue: 0,1:32:53.78,1:32:58.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the first nine counts in the indictment refer to the prisoner's misconduct\N起訴書的前九項涉及犯人
Dialogue: 0,1:32:58.31,1:33:01.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,with a young man named Alfred Wood.\N與一名叫阿爾弗雷德 伍德的年輕男人的不端行為。
Dialogue: 0,1:33:01.57,1:33:03.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The next three to Frederick Atkin.\N下面的三項涉及弗雷德裡克·特金
Dialogue: 0,1:33:04.01,1:33:07.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Two to the man Taylor. Three to Charles Parker.\N兩項涉及泰勒。三項涉及查爾斯帕克。
Dialogue: 0,1:33:07.93,1:33:11.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the last to Wilde's conduct with a lad named Shelley.\N最後一項涉及王爾德與一名叫雪莉的小伙子的行為。
Dialogue: 0,1:33:11.58,1:33:14.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It will be shown that Wilde systematically endeavored\N這都顯示著王爾德一步一步地試圖
Dialogue: 0,1:33:14.41,1:33:17.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to influence these young men's minds towards vicious causes.\N影響著這些年輕人的思想，按照他的邪惡目的。
Dialogue: 0,1:33:17.63,1:33:20.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And to mold them to his own depraved will.\N以他自己的腐化意願去塑造年輕人。
Dialogue: 0,1:33:20.98,1:33:24.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gentlemen of the jury, when you have heard the evidence of these men,\N陪審團的先生們，當你們聽到這些人的作證時，
Dialogue: 0,1:33:24.51,1:33:27.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I assure you that you will be justified\N我保證你們會做出
Dialogue: 0,1:33:27.12,1:33:29.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in finding the prisoner guilty on all counts.\N認定被告對各項罪名有罪的裁斷。
Dialogue: 0,1:33:29.47,1:33:31.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I call first Alfred Wood.\N我召第一個證人阿爾弗雷德伍德。
Dialogue: 0,1:33:33.52,1:33:35.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,COURT USHER: Call Alfred Wood.\N庭警：帶阿爾弗雷德 伍德上庭。
Dialogue: 0,1:33:35.61,1:33:36.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alfred Wood.\N阿爾弗雷德伍德。
Dialogue: 0,1:33:48.92,1:33:52.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take the Bible in your right hand and read from the card.\N右手持聖經，按照卡片上的念。
Dialogue: 0,1:33:52.14,1:33:55.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I swear by Almighty God that the evidence I give to this court\N“我向全能的上帝宣誓，我給法庭的證據”
Dialogue: 0,1:33:55.28,1:33:58.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"shall be the truth, the whole truth and nothing but the truth,\N“將會是真實的，全部真實的，沒有不真實的，”
Dialogue: 0,1:33:59.37,1:34:00.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"so help me, God."\N“上帝保佑我。”
Dialogue: 0,1:34:06.46,1:34:09.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In all my years at the bar, I cannot remember coming face to face\N在我的法庭生涯中，不記得這種面對面
Dialogue: 0,1:34:09.64,1:34:12.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,with such a miserable collection of witnesses.\N痛苦地收集證據。
Dialogue: 0,1:34:13.64,1:34:16.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wood, Parker, Atkin.\N伍德，帕克，阿特金。
Dialogue: 0,1:34:18.82,1:34:20.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The prosecution must have scraped\N公訴人一定是
Dialogue: 0,1:34:20.39,1:34:23.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the bottom of the barrel to get that lot together.\N搜腸刮肚地想到把這些人湊在一起。
Dialogue: 0,1:34:23.09,1:34:26.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What I cannot understand is how a man of Wilde's taste and breeding\N我想不到的是，像王爾德這樣的品味和修養
Dialogue: 0,1:34:26.57,1:34:28.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,can come to associate with such people.\N居然和這些人搞在一起。
Dialogue: 0,1:34:28.31,1:34:29.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, to understand that, Charles,\N你要明白，查爾斯，
Dialogue: 0,1:34:30.01,1:34:31.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you'd have to understand the nature of Wilde's perversion.\N你不得不理解王爾德的反常本性。
Dialogue: 0,1:34:31.66,1:34:33.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I'm a lawyer, not a doctor.\N可我是律師，不是心理醫生。
Dialogue: 0,1:34:33.88,1:34:37.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To me, it's loathsome, degenerate and unnatural.\N對我個人來說，這也是令我討厭的，墮落的和不正常的。
Dialogue: 0,1:34:38.41,1:34:40.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yet I feel so sorry for him.\N我對他也感到很遺憾。
Dialogue: 0,1:34:40.97,1:34:44.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is a terrible thing, Charles, when a man of Wilde's talents and genius\N這真是一件可怕的事情，查爾斯，當一個像王爾德這樣有才華和天賦的人
Dialogue: 0,1:34:44.94,1:34:48.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is slowly crucified by a lot of blackmailers and common criminals.\N逐漸被因為一些敲詐和普通犯罪而釘上十字架。
Dialogue: 0,1:34:51.90,1:34:54.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's very little hope for an acquittal, is there?\N是不是已經無望免罪了？
Dialogue: 0,1:34:54.77,1:34:58.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, the case has already been judged by the press and the public.\N其實，這案子已經被新聞界和公眾給判了。
Dialogue: 0,1:34:58.38,1:35:01.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As far as they're concerned, Wilde is guilty.\N在他們看來，王爾德是有罪的。
Dialogue: 0,1:35:01.52,1:35:04.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It only remains for him to be sentenced.\N對他來說，剩下的就是定罪。
Dialogue: 0,1:35:04.96,1:35:11.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The most we can hope for is that, out of this hysteria of prejudice and hatred,\N我們最希望做的也就是，擺脫偏見和仇恨帶來的歇斯底裡，
Dialogue: 0,1:35:11.05,1:35:15.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there might shine a glimmer of Christian charity and forgiveness.\N讓基督的慈善和寬容再閃出一絲光芒。
Dialogue: 0,1:35:15.88,1:35:17.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do I understand you to say then, Mr. Wilde,\N我能這麼理解嗎？王爾德先生，
Dialogue: 0,1:35:18.01,1:35:20.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that there is no truth whatsoever in the evidence of Alfred Wood?\N那就是阿爾弗雷德伍德所做的證詞沒有一點是真實的。
Dialogue: 0,1:35:21.93,1:35:23.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that we had supper together,\N我們一起吃晚飯是真實的，
Dialogue: 0,1:35:23.76,1:35:26.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but the accusations of impropriety are quite untrue.\N但是不正當的指控一點都不真實。
Dialogue: 0,1:35:26.72,1:35:29.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Charles Parker, what part of his evidence is untrue?\N查爾斯帕克，證詞的哪一部分不真實？
Dialogue: 0,1:35:31.24,1:35:33.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He never came to the hotel with me.\N他沒有和我一起去賓館。
Dialogue: 0,1:35:33.07,1:35:35.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He never had dinner with me and he never came to my room.\N他沒有和我一起吃晚飯，也從來沒進過我的房間。
Dialogue: 0,1:35:36.73,1:35:40.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We had tea at the St. James's once, but all of the rest...\N我們曾經在聖詹姆斯喝過茶，其他的。。。
Dialogue: 0,1:35:40.90,1:35:42.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is untrue.\N就不真實了。
Dialogue: 0,1:35:42.64,1:35:45.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, Atkin. What of his evidence?\N那麼，阿特金。他的證詞呢？
Dialogue: 0,1:35:45.52,1:35:47.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My Lord, my learned friend seems to have forgotten\N法官大人，我的博學朋友看起來已經忘了
Dialogue: 0,1:35:47.65,1:35:49.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that the witness Atkin perjured himself in the box.\N證人阿特金曾經在他自己的案子上做偽證。
Dialogue: 0,1:35:49.83,1:35:52.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your Lordship dismissed this witness for that reason.\N法官大人因為這個原因取消了他的證詞。
Dialogue: 0,1:35:52.35,1:35:55.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The witness's evidence was not struck from the record, Sir Edward.\N證人的證詞不受記錄的影響，愛德華爵士。
Dialogue: 0,1:35:55.40,1:35:57.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In my humble submission, My Lord, it should have been.\N我懇請法官大人收回成命。
Dialogue: 0,1:35:57.92,1:35:59.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is for me to decide.\N這是我的決定。
Dialogue: 0,1:36:02.45,1:36:03.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As Your Lordship pleases.\N隨大人的便吧。
Dialogue: 0,1:36:05.41,1:36:08.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What of Atkins's evidence, Mr. Wilde?\N阿特金的證詞呢？王爾德先生。
Dialogue: 0,1:36:08.80,1:36:11.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The accusations of indecency are quite untrue.\N關於猥褻的指控很不真實。
Dialogue: 0,1:36:11.59,1:36:15.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In fact, these witnesses, according to you,\N實際上，這些證詞，照你說的，
Dialogue: 0,1:36:15.81,1:36:17.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,have lied throughout the trial.\N從庭審自始都是在說謊。
Dialogue: 0,1:36:17.81,1:36:19.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With remarkable ease.\N他們太熟練了。
Dialogue: 0,1:36:19.20,1:36:21.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As an experienced writer and storyteller,\N作為一個老道的作家和編劇，
Dialogue: 0,1:36:21.16,1:36:23.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've lost in admiration of their inventiveness.\N我已經對他們的創造力驚歎不已。
Dialogue: 0,1:36:25.86,1:36:29.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You seem also to have been lost in admiration for their youth, sir.\N你看起來似乎更關心他們的年輕，先生。
Dialogue: 0,1:36:30.00,1:36:31.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a lover of youth.\N我愛好青年人。
Dialogue: 0,1:36:36.61,1:36:39.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, we have gathered that.\N是的，我們已經收集到了。
Dialogue: 0,1:36:40.01,1:36:43.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, let us turn to this publication, The Chameleon.\N現在，讓我們轉向出版物，變色龍雜志。
Dialogue: 0,1:36:43.88,1:36:46.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My Lord, are we to be subjected to a further discourse\N法官大人，我們下一步是否要討論一下\N
Dialogue: 0,1:36:46.32,1:36:48.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,on the literary morals of the defendant?\N被告的文學道德？
Dialogue: 0,1:36:49.02,1:36:51.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I understood from my learned friend that he's going to confine himself\N我從我博學的朋友那裡了解到，他想自己界定
Dialogue: 0,1:36:51.84,1:36:53.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to the specific charges made in the indictment.\N起訴書的專門指控
Dialogue: 0,1:36:53.89,1:36:56.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is cross examination as to credit, My Lord.\N這是對信用的盤查，法官大人。
Dialogue: 0,1:36:56.89,1:37:00.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I feel obliged to say that questions which learned counsel thinks\N我不得不說一個博學的律師思考這個問題
Dialogue: 0,1:37:00.29,1:37:02.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,should go to credit, he is entitled to put.\N是應該的，他有資格進行下去。
Dialogue: 0,1:37:08.34,1:37:11.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I shall not keep you long, Mr. Wilde.\N我不會持續很長時間的，王爾德先生。
Dialogue: 0,1:37:11.08,1:37:13.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I trust not, Mr. Gill.\N我相信你不會，吉爾先生。
Dialogue: 0,1:37:13.34,1:37:15.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In this magazine, to which you made a contribution,\N在你投稿的這本雜志裡，
Dialogue: 0,1:37:15.83,1:37:18.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there appears a poem by Lord Alfred Douglas\N刊登了一首艾爾弗雷德道格拉斯勳爵的詩歌
Dialogue: 0,1:37:18.61,1:37:21.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,entitled Two Loves.\N名字叫兩個情人。
Dialogue: 0,1:37:22.31,1:37:24.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It contains these lines.\N有幾行是這樣的。
Dialogue: 0,1:37:25.44,1:37:27.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Sweet youth,\N“親愛的年輕人，”
Dialogue: 0,1:37:27.53,1:37:29.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"tell me why, sad and sighing,\N“告訴我為什麼悲傷和歎息，”
Dialogue: 0,1:37:29.88,1:37:32.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"does thou rove these pleasant realms?\N“伴著你徜徉在快樂國度中？”
Dialogue: 0,1:37:32.80,1:37:36.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I pray, tell me sooth. What is thy name?\N“我懇求，告訴我實情。你叫什麼名字？”
Dialogue: 0,1:37:37.24,1:37:40.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"He said, 'my name is Love.'\N“他說，我的名字叫愛情”
Dialogue: 0,1:37:40.46,1:37:43.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Then straight the first did turn himself to me\N“然後第一個直接轉向我”
Dialogue: 0,1:37:43.24,1:37:47.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"and cried, 'he lieth, for his name is Shame.\N“並哭泣著說：他撒謊，因為他的名字叫羞恥。”
Dialogue: 0,1:37:47.12,1:37:50.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"'but I am Love, and I was to be alone in this fair garden,\N“我才是愛情，而我在這個美麗的花園裡卻很寂寞，”
Dialogue: 0,1:37:50.95,1:37:53.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"'till he came unasked by night.\N“知道他夜裡冒昧闖進。”
Dialogue: 0,1:37:53.95,1:37:55.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"'I am true Love.\N“我是真愛。”
Dialogue: 0,1:37:56.00,1:37:59.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"'I fill the hearts of boy and girl with mutual flame.'\N“我用相通火焰撩撥著男孩與女孩的心”
Dialogue: 0,1:38:00.70,1:38:02.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Then, sighing, said the other,\N“隨後，長歎一聲，而另一個卻說，”
Dialogue: 0,1:38:03.61,1:38:05.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"'have thy will,\N“你要做什麼，”
Dialogue: 0,1:38:05.70,1:38:10.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"'I am the love that dare not speak its name.'?\N“我才是愛情，卻不敢說出名字？”
Dialogue: 0,1:38:13.32,1:38:20.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And what, Mr. Wilde, is the love that dare not speak its name?\N那麼，王爾德先生，什麼樣的愛不敢說出名字？
Dialogue: 0,1:38:23.98,1:38:27.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The love that dare not speak its name, in this century,\N不敢說出名字的愛，在這個世紀，
Dialogue: 0,1:38:27.98,1:38:31.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is such a great affection of an elder for a younger man.\N是一個長者對青年的偉大情感。
Dialogue: 0,1:38:31.64,1:38:34.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As there was between David and Jonathan.\N正如大衛和喬納森之間的感情。\N（出自聖經，兩人之間心心相印，純潔友愛）
Dialogue: 0,1:38:34.77,1:38:37.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Such as Plato made the very basis of philosophy\N正如柏拉圖奠定的哲學基礎
Dialogue: 0,1:38:37.47,1:38:40.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and such as you will find in the sonnets of Michelangelo and Shakespeare.\N正如你可以在米開朗基羅和莎士比亞的十四行詩中找到的一樣。
Dialogue: 0,1:38:42.39,1:38:46.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is a deep, spiritual affection\N它是一種深深的，精神層面的情感
Dialogue: 0,1:38:46.92,1:38:49.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that is as perfect as it is pure.\N它純潔地近乎完美。
Dialogue: 0,1:38:50.92,1:38:54.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is in this century misunderstood, so much misunderstood\N在這個世紀，它被誤解了，被誤解到
Dialogue: 0,1:38:54.58,1:39:00.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that it may be called the love that dare not speak its name.\N它都不敢說出它的名字。
Dialogue: 0,1:39:00.28,1:39:03.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And on account of it, I'm placed where I am today.\N正是因為這樣，我今天才被帶到這裡。
Dialogue: 0,1:39:04.80,1:39:06.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it is beautiful,\N但它是美麗的，
Dialogue: 0,1:39:06.89,1:39:09.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it is fine,\N它是健康的，
Dialogue: 0,1:39:09.11,1:39:11.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it is the noblest form of affection.\N它是情感的最高貴形式。
Dialogue: 0,1:39:11.68,1:39:13.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is nothing unnatural about it.\N這裡面沒有任何矯揉造作。
Dialogue: 0,1:39:14.77,1:39:16.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is intellectual.\N它是理智的。
Dialogue: 0,1:39:16.64,1:39:20.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And is repeatedly to be found between an elder and a younger man\N它多次在長者和青年之間被發現
Dialogue: 0,1:39:20.69,1:39:25.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when the elder man has intellect and the younger man has all the hope and joy\N因長者飽含智慧，而青年充滿希望與快樂
Dialogue: 0,1:39:25.78,1:39:27.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and glamour of life before him.\N在他面前是生命的魅力。
Dialogue: 0,1:39:30.31,1:39:32.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it is so the world does not understand.\N它不被這個世界所理解。
Dialogue: 0,1:39:34.14,1:39:36.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The world mocks at it.\N這個世界嘲笑它。
Dialogue: 0,1:39:36.62,1:39:39.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And sometimes puts one in the pillory for it.\N有時人們會把木枷套在它頭上。
Dialogue: 0,1:39:45.28,1:39:46.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,COURT USHER: Silence in court.\N庭警：肅靜。
Dialogue: 0,1:39:46.76,1:39:47.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rubbish!\N一派胡言！
Dialogue: 0,1:39:47.76,1:39:50.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Silence in court!  Sit down, sir!\N肅靜！坐下，先生！
Dialogue: 0,1:39:50.89,1:39:55.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If there is the slightest manifestation of feeling like this again,\N如果再有誰表現出這樣的情感，
Dialogue: 0,1:39:55.07,1:39:57.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I shall have the court cleared.\N我將把他請出法庭。
Dialogue: 0,1:39:57.33,1:40:00.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no further questions, My Lord.\N我沒有問題了，法官大人。
Dialogue: 0,1:40:00.51,1:40:02.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,JUDGE: The witness may stand down.\N法官：證人可以退席。
Dialogue: 0,1:40:08.04,1:40:10.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That concludes the case for the prosecution, My Lord.\N為公訴人做結案陳辭，法官大人。
Dialogue: 0,1:40:23.06,1:40:27.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,May it please you, My Lord, gentlemen of the jury,\N法官大人，陪審團的先生們，
Dialogue: 0,1:40:27.45,1:40:31.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,this is a serious and grave question for you to decide.\N這是一個非常嚴重的問題，需要你來決定。
Dialogue: 0,1:40:31.89,1:40:34.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And yours is a position of great responsibility.\N你們的職位責任重大。
Dialogue: 0,1:40:36.16,1:40:39.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, a great deal of public feeling has been excited against Mr. Wilde\N現在，公眾對王爾德先生的不滿情緒高漲
Dialogue: 0,1:40:39.16,1:40:42.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,by the quotation of passages of poetry and literature\N通過引用詩歌和文學段落的言論
Dialogue: 0,1:40:42.29,1:40:46.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and in particular from Mr. Wilde's book, The Picture of Dorian Gray.\N特別是通過王爾德先生的小說，《道林格雷的肖像》
Dialogue: 0,1:40:46.08,1:40:48.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I ask you, members of the jury,\N現在我問你們，陪審團的成員們，
Dialogue: 0,1:40:48.17,1:40:52.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is an author to be judged on the morals of the characters of his book?\N要根據書中人物的道德標准來評判一個作家嗎?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:52.48,1:40:55.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was Stevenson accused of being a lustful and depraved monster\N史蒂文森是否被指責為一個好色墮落的怪物
Dialogue: 0,1:40:55.65,1:40:58.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because he wrote Dr. Jekyll and Mr. Hyde?\N因為他寫了《化身博士》？
Dialogue: 0,1:40:58.79,1:41:03.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As to the affection which Mr. Wilde expressed in his letters,\N至於王爾德先生在他的信中所表達的情感，
Dialogue: 0,1:41:03.44,1:41:06.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he himself has described it as pure, true affection,\N他自己曾把它描述為純潔、真誠的愛
Dialogue: 0,1:41:06.49,1:41:09.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,absolutely unconnected with and completely alien to the\N絕對不能聯系到，甚至完全不同於
Dialogue: 0,1:41:09.45,1:41:12.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,filthy practices described in this court\N在這個法庭上所被檢方列舉出的一幫罪犯
Dialogue: 0,1:41:12.15,1:41:14.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,by the prosecution's band of criminals.\N所描述的骯髒行為。
Dialogue: 0,1:41:16.46,1:41:19.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Wilde is not an ordinary man.\N王爾德先生不是一個普通人。
Dialogue: 0,1:41:19.20,1:41:22.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He is a man who has written poetry and prose,\N他是一個寫過詩和散文的人，
Dialogue: 0,1:41:22.38,1:41:25.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,brilliant dramas, charming essays.\N還寫過精彩的戲劇和迷人的短文。
Dialogue: 0,1:41:25.94,1:41:28.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He writes letters in a tone which to most of us may appear\N他寫信的語氣，在我們大多數人看來，可能是
Dialogue: 0,1:41:28.73,1:41:34.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,high-flown, inflated, exaggerated, even absurd.\N高高在上、誇大其詞、甚至是荒謬的。
Dialogue: 0,1:41:34.52,1:41:38.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he's not ashamed or afraid to produce those letters.\N但他並不羞於或害怕出示這些信件。
Dialogue: 0,1:41:38.52,1:41:41.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When a man comes forward with letters such as these and says,\N當一個人拿著這樣的信走上前來說，
Dialogue: 0,1:41:41.61,1:41:44.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I do not shrink from the judgment of the world upon these productions,"\N“我並不畏懼世界對這些作品的評判，”
Dialogue: 0,1:41:44.70,1:41:48.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,has he not given the best proof of his innocence?\N他沒有給出他清白的最好證據嗎?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:48.97,1:41:51.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Innocence, gentlemen of the jury, has courage and faith\N陪審團的先生們，在人類最終的審判中，
Dialogue: 0,1:41:51.80,1:41:53.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in the ultimate judgment of mankind.\N清白是需要有勇氣和信念的。\N
Dialogue: 0,1:41:56.02,1:42:00.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As to the evidence of the youths, Parker, Atkin, Wood\N至於帕克、阿特金、伍德這些年輕人的證據
Dialogue: 0,1:42:00.46,1:42:03.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and their associates,\N還有他們的同伙。
Dialogue: 0,1:42:03.33,1:42:06.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I respectfully submit that no jury can find a man guilty\N在他們有污點的證據下，我恭敬地斷言，
Dialogue: 0,1:42:06.55,1:42:09.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,on their tainted evidence.\N陪審團無法判定一個人有罪。
Dialogue: 0,1:42:09.25,1:42:12.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It deepens one's horror to think the prisoner's freedom\N一想到囚犯的自由就加深了人們的恐懼
Dialogue: 0,1:42:12.12,1:42:13.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is at the peril of such persons.\N是冒著這樣的危險的人嗎
Dialogue: 0,1:42:16.56,1:42:19.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Before you consider this case, therefore,\N因此，在你考慮這件事之前，
Dialogue: 0,1:42:19.26,1:42:24.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I implore you to let your judgment only be affected by those witnesses\N我懇求你讓你們的判決只受那些證人的影響
Dialogue: 0,1:42:24.05,1:42:27.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,of whom you, as true and honorable men\N那些說真話和高尚的證人
Dialogue: 0,1:42:27.05,1:42:29.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,can say, with a clear conscience have given\N只有他們，可以問心無愧地給出
Dialogue: 0,1:42:29.18,1:42:33.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,true, honest and honorable testimony.\N准確，誠實和可敬的證詞。
Dialogue: 0,1:42:33.45,1:42:36.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And if, upon the examination of the evidence, you find it your duty to say\N如果在審查證據時，你們發現有責任去說
Dialogue: 0,1:42:36.84,1:42:40.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that the charges against the prisoner have not been proved,\N那些對被告的指控都是未被證實的，
Dialogue: 0,1:42:40.15,1:42:43.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know you'll be glad that that bright reputation,\N我想你們一定很高興地看到，你們的鮮明的名譽
Dialogue: 0,1:42:43.24,1:42:46.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so nearly quenched in a torrent of prejudice,\N在快要被偏見的激流澆滅的時候，
Dialogue: 0,1:42:46.33,1:42:51.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,will have been saved by your verdict from absolute ruin.\N又被你們的判決從絕對的廢墟中拯救出來。
Dialogue: 0,1:42:51.20,1:42:54.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that it will leave Mr. Wilde,a distinguished man of letters,\N這將使王爾德先生，一位傑出的文學家，
Dialogue: 0,1:42:54.86,1:42:57.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to live a life of honor and repute\N過上有榮譽和有聲望的生活
Dialogue: 0,1:42:57.43,1:43:01.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and to give, in the maturity of his genius, gifts to our literature\N在他的天賦成熟之時，給我們的文學以天賦的禮物
Dialogue: 0,1:43:01.26,1:43:04.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,of which, already, he has shown such brilliant promise.\N而且，它已經顯示出燦爛的希望。
Dialogue: 0,1:44:34.05,1:44:36.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,COURT USHER: Be upstanding in court.\N庭警：全體起立。
Dialogue: 0,1:44:48.71,1:44:53.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gentlemen of the jury, I understand that you are unable to arrive at a verdict.\N陪審團的先生們，我知道你們無法作出裁決。
Dialogue: 0,1:44:53.15,1:44:54.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is so, My Lord.\N是這樣的，法官大人。
Dialogue: 0,1:44:54.85,1:44:57.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there any prospect that if you retired\N如果讓你們再退下一會兒
Dialogue: 0,1:44:57.29,1:44:59.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and continued your deliberations a little longer,\N繼續你們的討論
Dialogue: 0,1:44:59.64,1:45:01.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you'll be able to come to some agreement?\N你們有希望達成一致的意見嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:45:01.77,1:45:04.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have considered the question for three hours, My Lord.\N這個問題我們已經深思熟慮了三個小時，法官大人。
Dialogue: 0,1:45:04.38,1:45:07.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the only result we have come to is that we cannot agree.\N結果卻是我們不能達成一致意見。
Dialogue: 0,1:45:07.69,1:45:11.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I have no doubt that you have tried very hard\N是的，我毫不懷疑你們已經非常努力用以
Dialogue: 0,1:45:11.47,1:45:14.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to come to some agreement, but on the other hand,\N達成一至意見，但是另一方面，
Dialogue: 0,1:45:14.48,1:45:18.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the inconveniences of another trial are very great.\N另一場審判結果對本案帶來極大的麻煩。
Dialogue: 0,1:45:18.09,1:45:21.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My Lord, I fear there is no chance of an agreement.\N法官大人，我恐怕沒機會以達成一致意見。
Dialogue: 0,1:45:21.05,1:45:23.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,JUDGE: Then, gentlemen, you are discharged.\N法官：先生們，你們可以退席了。
Dialogue: 0,1:45:23.75,1:45:25.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,FOREMAN: Thank you, My Lord.\N首席陪審員：謝謝，法官大人。
Dialogue: 0,1:45:25.14,1:45:27.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My Lord, on the question of bail,\N法官大人，關於保釋的問題，
Dialogue: 0,1:45:27.53,1:45:29.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it may be some weeks before a retrial...\N離重審此案還有幾周時間。。。
Dialogue: 0,1:45:32.41,1:45:38.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Retrial! Retrial! Retrial! Retrial! Retrial! Retrial! Retrial!\N重審！重審！。。。。。重審！
Dialogue: 0,1:45:48.42,1:45:50.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, Robbie.\N你好，羅比。
Dialogue: 0,1:45:50.34,1:45:52.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Wilde, we managed to raise bail.\N王爾德先生，我們已經籌集到保釋金了。
Dialogue: 0,1:45:53.04,1:45:55.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Oscar. Let me take you home.\N走吧，奧斯卡。咱們回家吧。
Dialogue: 0,1:45:55.52,1:45:57.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who put up the money for my bail?\N是誰提供了我的保釋金？
Dialogue: 0,1:45:57.22,1:45:59.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bosie's brother Percy put up most of the money.\N波西的哥哥佩西提供了大部分的資金。
Dialogue: 0,1:45:59.87,1:46:01.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Percy? How kind.\N佩西？這麼好心。
Dialogue: 0,1:46:01.92,1:46:04.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The rest was put up by the Reverend Headlam.\N其余的部分由海德勒姆牧師提供。
Dialogue: 0,1:46:04.14,1:46:05.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,5,000pounds in all.\N一共5000英鎊。
Dialogue: 0,1:46:06.01,1:46:09.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's preposterous. A common felon would not be so heavily penalized.\N太荒謬了。一起普通的重罪都要不了這麼多罰金。
Dialogue: 0,1:46:10.36,1:46:11.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Reverend Headlam? Mmm-hmm.\N海德勒姆牧師？Mmm-hmm
Dialogue: 0,1:46:13.41,1:46:16.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Extraordinary! I hardly know him.\N非常奇特！我幾乎都不認識他。
Dialogue: 0,1:46:37.08,1:46:39.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Oscar, let's go to a hotel.    -No!\N-奧斯卡，讓我們去住酒店吧。   -不!
Dialogue: 0,1:46:46.22,1:46:48.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ARTHUR: Mr. Wilde!\N阿瑟：王爾德先生！
Dialogue: 0,1:46:48.92,1:46:53.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Wilde. Oh, sir, I've done everything I could.\N王爾德先生。噢，先生，我已經做了所能的一切。
Dialogue: 0,1:46:53.79,1:46:57.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your manuscripts. I've managed to save some of them,\N您的手稿。我設法保存了大部分，
Dialogue: 0,1:46:57.28,1:47:00.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but they're been going through the house like vultures, sir.\N但是他們像禿鷲一樣把這房子搜查了一遍，先生。
Dialogue: 0,1:47:02.15,1:47:04.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,AUCTIONEER: 20pounds! 25!\N拍賣者：20英鎊！25！
Dialogue: 0,1:47:04.37,1:47:09.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,25pounds I've bid for this priceless first edition by Walt Whitman, whoever he may be.\N25英鎊，我對這本沃爾特惠特尼的首版詩集的出價，有誰更高\N（美國詩人，《草葉集》作者）
Dialogue: 0,1:47:09.81,1:47:12.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now, come along, gentlemen. Do I hear 30pounds?\N快，快，快來，先生們。我是否聽到了30英鎊？
Dialogue: 0,1:47:12.94,1:47:14.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,30pounds, 30. 35pounds.\N30英鎊，30.35英鎊
Dialogue: 0,1:47:14.68,1:47:17.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,35pounds, 35. Come along, we haven't got all night.\N35 英鎊，35。來吧，我們不能呆到整晚。
Dialogue: 0,1:47:17.60,1:47:21.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Going then at 30pounds. Going once, twice, three times.\N就30英鎊了。計數一次，兩次，三次，成交。
Dialogue: 0,1:47:21.91,1:47:24.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Charles, the gent over there with the cigar.\N查爾斯，那位抽雪茄的先生中標。
Dialogue: 0,1:47:24.22,1:47:29.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then. Hello, hello, hello. What have we got here?\N那麼現在，喂，喂，喂。我們搞到什麼了？
Dialogue: 0,1:47:29.35,1:47:32.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A painting of the dear boy himself.\N那個可愛男孩的自畫像。
Dialogue: 0,1:47:32.96,1:47:35.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very pretty, I'm sure. Very pretty.\N非常可愛，我肯定。非常可愛。
Dialogue: 0,1:47:35.36,1:47:39.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now what am I bid for this masterpiece? Do I hear 10 shillings?\N現在，我是否該為這件大師作品出價10先令？
Dialogue: 0,1:47:39.67,1:47:41.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,MAN: Ten shillings. AUCTIONEER: Ten shillings I'v bid.\N男人：10先令。拍賣者：我已經標價10先令。
Dialogue: 0,1:47:41.93,1:47:43.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do I hear a pound?\N我是否聽到1英鎊？
Dialogue: 0,1:47:43.28,1:47:44.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-1pounds.    -1pounds!\N-1英鎊。   -1英鎊！
Dialogue: 0,1:47:44.19,1:47:46.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,1pounds, 1.\N1英鎊，一
Dialogue: 0,1:47:49.02,1:47:53.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, ladies and gentlemen, I think we have company.\N對不起，女士們先生們，我想我們有客人來了。
Dialogue: 0,1:47:55.81,1:47:59.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps His Eminence will bid for this artistic painting.\N也許這位閣下想參與這件藝術品的競標。
Dialogue: 0,1:48:01.82,1:48:03.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about 30 bob, sir?\N30先令怎麼樣，先生？
Dialogue: 0,1:48:04.60,1:48:06.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Oscar. Haven't you seen enough?\N走吧，奧斯卡。你難道沒有看夠？
Dialogue: 0,1:48:09.57,1:48:11.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-No?\N-不想？
Dialogue: 0,1:48:11.87,1:48:17.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, all right, then. Going at a pound. Going, going...\N那麼，好吧，接著進行，1英鎊。接著，接著。。。
Dialogue: 0,1:48:17.92,1:48:19.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,40 guineas!\N40畿尼！
Dialogue: 0,1:48:19.23,1:48:22.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-AUCTIONEER: 40 guineas.\N-拍賣者：40畿尼。
Dialogue: 0,1:48:22.06,1:48:24.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, then. Any advance on 40 guineas?\N那麼，有誰想超過40畿尼？
Dialogue: 0,1:48:26.58,1:48:29.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right. Sold to His Lordship for 40 guineas.\N好吧，賣給這位紳士40畿尼。
Dialogue: 0,1:48:29.50,1:48:32.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Charlie, give the gentleman his painting.\N查理，把這幅畫給這位先生。
Dialogue: 0,1:48:32.81,1:48:34.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-40 guineas.    -Thank you, My Lord.\N-40畿尼。  -謝謝您，先生。
Dialogue: 0,1:48:34.89,1:48:36.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Thank you.   -What are you going to do with it now you've bought it?\N-謝謝你。  -您買下它打算拿它干什麼？
Dialogue: 0,1:48:36.98,1:48:38.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hang it in the bathroom!\N把它掛在浴室！
Dialogue: 0,1:48:47.21,1:48:50.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aw, blimey, governor. What a waste of 40 quid.\N奧，天吶，長官。40英鎊就這麼浪費了。
Dialogue: 0,1:48:50.43,1:48:53.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,MAN: I say, a little bit rash, what?\N男人：我說，真有點魯莽，什麼？
Dialogue: 0,1:48:56.57,1:48:57.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I feel like a drink.\N我想去喝一杯。
Dialogue: 0,1:49:01.92,1:49:03.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, please.\N請讓一下。
Dialogue: 0,1:49:04.62,1:49:07.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me. Thank you.  Excuse me, madam.\N讓一下。謝謝你。讓一下，夫人。
Dialogue: 0,1:49:08.36,1:49:10.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me. Thank you.\N讓一下，謝謝你。
Dialogue: 0,1:49:11.50,1:49:12.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.\N讓一下。
Dialogue: 0,1:49:15.89,1:49:17.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Oscar.\N走吧，奧斯卡。
Dialogue: 0,1:49:19.37,1:49:21.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,AUCTIONEER: Well, we weren't very quick there.\N拍賣者：好吧，我們可不會那麼快結束。
Dialogue: 0,1:49:21.90,1:49:25.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We should have asked His Eminence to autograph a few books, eh?\N我們應該請閣下在幾本書上簽名，嗯?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:27.38,1:49:30.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, an original manuscript of that uproarious comedy,\N現在，這出轟動一時的喜劇的原始手稿，
Dialogue: 0,1:49:30.86,1:49:33.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Importance of Being Earnestby the late Oscar Wilde.\N《不可兒戲》，奧斯卡王爾德近期作品。
Dialogue: 0,1:49:33.69,1:49:35.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Now, then, do I hear 10pounds?\N-現在，好吧，我聽到10英鎊？
Dialogue: 0,1:49:58.76,1:49:59.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Wilde.\N王爾德先生。
Dialogue: 0,1:50:01.81,1:50:03.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm most dreadfully sorry about this, sir,\N我很抱歉，先生，
Dialogue: 0,1:50:03.64,1:50:05.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I'm afraid we must ask you to leave.\N我想我你們必須離開這裡。
Dialogue: 0,1:50:06.03,1:50:07.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ask us to leave? But how dare you come up...\N讓我們離開？你怎麼敢過來。。。
Dialogue: 0,1:50:07.86,1:50:09.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-I'm very sorry, sir.  -Don't you realize that Mr. Wilde's...\N我很抱歉，先生。  -你不知道這位先生是奧斯卡王爾德。。。
Dialogue: 0,1:50:09.69,1:50:10.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right, Robbie.\N算了吧，羅比。
Dialogue: 0,1:50:10.95,1:50:11.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go.\N我們走吧。
Dialogue: 0,1:50:19.48,1:50:21.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Remarkable, the sort of people they allow in here these days!\N這也太顯眼了，有些人這些日子也來這種地方！
Dialogue: 0,1:50:21.78,1:50:23.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-I thought it was a high-class place!\N-我曾以為這是一個高等地方！
Dialogue: 0,1:50:23.96,1:50:26.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's blooming disgusting.\N現在我認為這有一股臭氣。
Dialogue: 0,1:50:26.09,1:50:28.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, my friends, drink up. Pay the bill, will you, Freddie?\N來吧，我的朋友，干了，付錢，你行嗎?弗雷迪。
Dialogue: 0,1:50:28.75,1:50:30.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why, certainly, Q.\N啥呀，當然行，Q。
Dialogue: 0,1:50:30.05,1:50:31.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cab!\N馬車！
Dialogue: 0,1:50:31.23,1:50:33.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,God bless you, Mr. Wilde.\N上帝保佑你，王爾德先生。
Dialogue: 0,1:50:34.19,1:50:35.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, Amy.\N你好，艾米。
Dialogue: 0,1:50:36.84,1:50:38.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Knightsbridge, cabby.\N去騎士橋，車夫。
Dialogue: 0,1:50:38.24,1:50:39.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.\N是的，先生。
Dialogue: 0,1:50:42.89,1:50:44.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,MAN 1: Blimey! It's raining!\N男人1：天吶，下雨了！
Dialogue: 0,1:50:44.94,1:50:46.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,QUEENSBERRY: Get my carriage.\N昆斯博裡：上我的馬車。
Dialogue: 0,1:50:46.29,1:50:47.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So long, Oscar!\N再見，奧斯卡！
Dialogue: 0,1:50:47.51,1:50:48.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are we going to have a bit of sport then?\N等會兒我們去消化消化食兒？
Dialogue: 0,1:50:48.81,1:50:50.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I think so.\N是的，我也這麼想。
Dialogue: 0,1:50:50.12,1:50:52.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,MAN 2: Come on, there we go, let's get in.\N男人2：來吧，我們走，上車。
Dialogue: 0,1:50:53.03,1:50:54.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on.\N來吧。
Dialogue: 0,1:50:55.30,1:50:57.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Follow him. As fast as you can.\N以你最快的速度跟上他。
Dialogue: 0,1:50:57.47,1:50:58.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,MAN 2: Tallyho!\N男人2：帶勁兒！
Dialogue: 0,1:51:06.87,1:51:09.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By God, they're following us. The man must be mad.\N上帝啊，他們在跟著我們。這人一定瘋了。
Dialogue: 0,1:51:09.61,1:51:11.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I should have thought it was common knowledge by now, Robbie.\N我還以為這已經是常識了呢，羅比。
Dialogue: 0,1:51:11.57,1:51:12.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go faster, driver!\N加快，車夫！
Dialogue: 0,1:51:16.53,1:51:17.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,MAN 2: Tallyho!\N男人2：帶勁兒！
Dialogue: 0,1:51:20.58,1:51:22.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Faster, driver, faster!\N快點兒，車夫，再快點兒！
Dialogue: 0,1:51:22.80,1:51:24.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,MAN 2: Tallyho!\N男人2：帶勁兒！
Dialogue: 0,1:51:27.72,1:51:30.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is madness. I'm going to walk. Stop the cab, driver!\N這簡直是瘋狂，我要步行。停車，車夫！
Dialogue: 0,1:51:30.59,1:51:31.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oscar, don't be foolish.\N奧斯卡，別犯傻了。
Dialogue: 0,1:51:31.94,1:51:32.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not going to put you through all this.\N我不想把你牽扯進去。
Dialogue: 0,1:51:37.77,1:51:39.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oscar, where will you be?\N奧斯卡，你要去哪裡？
Dialogue: 0,1:51:39.34,1:51:40.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-I'm going to my mother.   -Right.\N-我去我媽那兒。   -好的。
Dialogue: 0,1:51:40.65,1:51:41.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Carry on, driver.\N接著走，車夫。
Dialogue: 0,1:52:18.81,1:52:20.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, now, my old darling, where's your friend?\N好了，現在，我的老伙計，你的朋友在哪兒?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:20.86,1:52:22.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you doing this, Queensberry?\N你為什麼這麼做，昆斯伯裡?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:22.38,1:52:23.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you hounding this man in this way?\N你為什麼這樣糾纏著這個人?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:23.99,1:52:26.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Haven't you had your pound of flesh?\N你沒有得到你應得的那磅肉嗎?\N（借用莎士比亞《威尼斯商人》夏洛克花錢買仇人的肉）
Dialogue: 0,1:52:26.91,1:52:28.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't know me very well, do you, Mr. Ross?\N難道你還不了解我嗎？羅斯先生。
Dialogue: 0,1:52:28.95,1:52:30.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not so easily satisfied.\N我可不是那麼容易滿足的。
Dialogue: 0,1:52:30.39,1:52:31.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's quite evident.\N這顯而易見。
Dialogue: 0,1:52:31.52,1:52:33.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell Wilde that I shall not be happy\N告訴王爾德，我不會高興的
Dialogue: 0,1:52:33.31,1:52:35.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,until I see him under six feet of earth.\N除非他被深埋在地下6英尺。\N（習俗起源於1665年倫敦大瘟疫期間,為了防止病毒傳播，屍體被埋時要至少埋在離地表6英尺的地下）
Dialogue: 0,1:52:35.13,1:52:36.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Six feet of earth, Lord Queensberry,\N地下6英尺，昆斯博裡侯爵，
Dialogue: 0,1:52:36.66,1:52:38.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,puts us all very much on the same level.\N那把我們都埋在同一深度。
Dialogue: 0,1:52:40.66,1:52:42.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've not finished with him yet!\N我和他沒完！
Dialogue: 0,1:52:43.01,1:52:45.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I shall hound him until his dying day!\N我要一直追到他死!
Dialogue: 0,1:52:46.97,1:52:49.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Until his dying day!\N直到他死的那天！
Dialogue: 0,1:52:49.24,1:52:51.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, what now, Q? Is the hunt still on?\N好吧，現在做什麼，Q？獵狐繼續嗎？\N（在2005年英國頒布法令，明文禁止已經風行了六百年的古老貴族運動——獵狐運動）
Dialogue: 0,1:52:52.54,1:52:53.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go to The Savoy.\N我們薩伏伊酒店。
Dialogue: 0,1:52:53.81,1:52:55.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, let's go to The Savoy. Go to The Savoy.\N啊，我們去薩伏伊，去薩伏伊。
Dialogue: 0,1:53:04.77,1:53:05.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oscar!\N奧斯卡！
Dialogue: 0,1:53:06.60,1:53:08.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oscar, is that you?\N奧斯卡，那是你嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:53:10.04,1:53:11.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Willie!\N威利！
Dialogue: 0,1:53:11.13,1:53:15.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dear darling Mother. Yes, what is it?\N親愛的媽媽，是的，那是什麼？
Dialogue: 0,1:53:15.13,1:53:18.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dearest Mother, you know you should have been an actress.\N最親愛的媽媽，你該去當個女演員。
Dialogue: 0,1:53:18.57,1:53:21.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt if the great Sarah Bernhardt herself\N我懷疑偉大的莎拉·伯恩哈特本人\N（1844年10月23日出生於巴黎，1923年3月26日逝世於巴黎，是一位法國演員）
Dialogue: 0,1:53:21.18,1:53:24.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,made a more imposing Lady Macbeth.\N使麥克白夫人顯得更加威嚴。\N（改編自俄國備受爭議小說，窮家少女被賣作莊園主人的媳婦，面對冷感的丈夫、刁難的家翁，她都默默啞忍）
Dialogue: 0,1:53:24.14,1:53:27.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But aren't you just a little premature to wear mourning?\N但是你穿喪服是不是有點太早了?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:28.88,1:53:31.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oscar isn't quite dead yet, you know.\N你知道，奧斯卡還沒有完全死。
Dialogue: 0,1:53:32.02,1:53:33.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They crucified him.\N他已被釘在十字架上。
Dialogue: 0,1:53:33.63,1:53:35.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, Mother, if you're going to go on like this, I...\N媽媽，如果你再這樣下去，我…
Dialogue: 0,1:53:48.69,1:53:49.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's there?\N誰在那裡？
Dialogue: 0,1:53:49.95,1:53:51.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OSCAR: Willie, let me in, for God's sake.\N奧斯卡:威利，讓我進去，看在上帝的份上。
Dialogue: 0,1:53:58.04,1:54:00.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Willie, let me stay. Let me stay.\N威利，讓我待一會兒。讓我待一會兒。
Dialogue: 0,1:54:01.57,1:54:03.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or I shall die on the streets.\N否則我就會死在街上。
Dialogue: 0,1:54:09.23,1:54:10.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you drunk?\N你喝醉了？
Dialogue: 0,1:54:19.37,1:54:20.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here you are.\N拿著。
Dialogue: 0,1:54:21.15,1:54:24.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this my son?\N這就是我的兒子嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:54:24.37,1:54:28.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this Oscar Wilde, cringing in the dark like a frightened animal?\N這是奧斯卡·王爾德，像受驚的動物一樣在黑暗中畏縮嗎?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:28.73,1:54:30.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mother, for heaven's sake!\N媽媽，看在上帝的份上!
Dialogue: 0,1:54:30.42,1:54:31.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stand up, sir.\N站起來，先生。
Dialogue: 0,1:54:32.03,1:54:33.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stand up and face them, sir!\N站起來，面對他們，先生！
Dialogue: 0,1:54:35.60,1:54:36.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For God's sake, don't let them in, Willie.\N看在上帝份上，別讓他們進來，威利。
Dialogue: 0,1:54:38.95,1:54:41.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Willie, open the door.\N威利，去開門。
Dialogue: 0,1:54:41.43,1:54:43.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My son is ready for them.\N我兒子已經准備好了對付他們。
Dialogue: 0,1:54:50.79,1:54:52.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Robbie. Thank God you've come.\NRobbie。感謝上帝，你來了。
Dialogue: 0,1:54:56.93,1:54:58.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ada.\N艾達。
Dialogue: 0,1:54:58.80,1:55:00.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Robbie, what's to become of me? -It's all right.\N-羅比，我怎麼辦呢?   -好吧。
Dialogue: 0,1:55:00.80,1:55:03.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Couldn't you have taken his coat off? He's soaked to the skin.\N你難道不能把他的外套脫掉嗎? 他全身濕透了。
Dialogue: 0,1:55:04.46,1:55:05.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's ill. He should be in bed.\N他病了。他應該在床上。
Dialogue: 0,1:55:05.98,1:55:08.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he... He can't stay here, you know. Well...\N但他……他不能呆在這裡，你知道的。嗯…
Dialogue: 0,1:55:08.90,1:55:10.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, it would be awkward, you see.\N我的意思是，這會很尷尬，你知道。
Dialogue: 0,1:55:10.99,1:55:12.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's been mobs hanging about in the street all day,\N有一群暴徒整天在街上游蕩，
Dialogue: 0,1:55:12.99,1:55:14.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and if they were to find out he was here,\N如果他們發現他在這裡
Dialogue: 0,1:55:14.95,1:55:17.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,well, there's no knowing what they'll do.\N沒人知道他們會怎麼做
Dialogue: 0,1:55:17.08,1:55:19.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My son is not afraid of them!\N我兒子不怕他們!
Dialogue: 0,1:55:19.78,1:55:22.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He'll stand up and face them\N他會站起來面對他們
Dialogue: 0,1:55:22.39,1:55:24.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,like a true Irish gentleman.\N像一個真正的愛爾蘭紳士。
Dialogue: 0,1:55:24.61,1:55:27.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can find him a bed at my house. Come, Oscar.\N我可以在我家給他准備張床。來,奧斯卡。
Dialogue: 0,1:55:27.87,1:55:31.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't sit up too late, my son.\N孩子，不要熬夜。
Dialogue: 0,1:55:31.27,1:55:34.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You need all the sleep you can get\N你需要盡可能多的睡眠
Dialogue: 0,1:55:34.27,1:55:37.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in this terrible time we've all passing through.\N在這可怕的時刻，我們都經歷過。
Dialogue: 0,1:55:39.58,1:55:41.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Oscar.\N來吧,奧斯卡。
Dialogue: 0,1:55:41.45,1:55:43.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not thinking of myself, you understand.\N我不是在為自己著想，你明白的。
Dialogue: 0,1:55:43.76,1:55:46.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He is my brother. But it's my mother.\N他是我的兄弟。但那是我媽媽。
Dialogue: 0,1:55:46.24,1:55:48.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's not very well and any sudden shock might...\N她身體不太好任何突如其來的打擊都可能…
Dialogue: 0,1:55:58.56,1:56:00.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The prisoner will rise.\N被告請起立。
Dialogue: 0,1:56:02.56,1:56:06.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gentlemen of the jury, have you agreed upon a verdict?\N陪審團的先生們，你們有了一致的裁決了嗎?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:06.13,1:56:07.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have.\N我們有了。
Dialogue: 0,1:56:07.83,1:56:11.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you find the prisoner at the bar guilty or not guilty?\N你認為被告席上的被告有罪還是無罪?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:12.44,1:56:13.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guilty, My Lord.\N有罪，法官大人。
Dialogue: 0,1:56:14.92,1:56:16.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,COURT USHER: Silence in court!\N庭警：肅靜！
Dialogue: 0,1:56:16.92,1:56:19.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And is that the verdict of you all?\N這就是你們所有人的判決嗎?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:19.53,1:56:21.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Guilty.\N是的，有罪。
Dialogue: 0,1:56:23.80,1:56:26.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,COURT USHER: Silence!\N庭警：肅靜！
Dialogue: 0,1:56:26.06,1:56:30.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oscar Wilde, the crime for which you have been convicted\N奧斯卡·王爾德，你被判決的罪行
Dialogue: 0,1:56:30.76,1:56:37.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is so bad that one has to put a stern restraint upon one's self\N是如此的惡劣，以至於我真的不想讓一個嚴於自律的人
Dialogue: 0,1:56:37.12,1:56:42.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to avoid describing, in language I would rather not use,\N用語言來描述它，
Dialogue: 0,1:56:42.95,1:56:47.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the sentiments that must rise in the breasts of every man of honor\N任何一個正直的人在聽了庭審細節後
Dialogue: 0,1:56:47.17,1:56:51.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who has listened to the details of these terrible trials.\N都會義憤填胸
Dialogue: 0,1:56:51.48,1:56:55.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That you have been the center of a circle\N你位於一個圈子的中心，一個由
Dialogue: 0,1:56:55.18,1:56:58.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,of the most terrible corruption among young men,\N最無恥下流的年輕人組成的圈子，
Dialogue: 0,1:56:58.48,1:57:01.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it is impossible to doubt.\N這是無可懷疑的。
Dialogue: 0,1:57:01.79,1:57:06.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And under the circumstances, I shall pass the severest sentence the law allows.\N基於上述情況，我將依法嚴懲。
Dialogue: 0,1:57:08.02,1:57:10.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Although, in my judgment\N盡管，在我看來
Dialogue: 0,1:57:10.76,1:57:14.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it is totally inadequate for a case of this sort.\N這對於這種情況是完全不夠的。
Dialogue: 0,1:57:15.68,1:57:19.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sentence of the court is that you go to imprisonment\N法庭的判決是你要坐牢
Dialogue: 0,1:57:19.29,1:57:22.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and be kept to hard labor for two years.\N要服苦役兩年。
Dialogue: 0,1:57:24.34,1:57:25.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,COURT USHER: Silence!\N庭警：肅靜！
Dialogue: 0,1:57:29.56,1:57:31.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be upstanding in court.\N全體起立。
Dialogue: 0,1:57:33.52,1:57:37.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All persons having anything further to do before My Lords...\N所有在陪審團各位面前還有事要做的人……
Dialogue: 0,1:57:37.22,1:57:39.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, back! Back. Come on, back!\N退後，退後，退後！
Dialogue: 0,1:57:52.54,1:57:54.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He'll get his hair cut now, won't he?\N他是要被剃去頭發嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:57:58.50,1:58:02.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在瑞丁監獄關押期間，王爾德醞釀完成《獄中書》和《瑞丁監獄之歌》兩部詩集。\N2016年，在該監獄舉辦了王爾德紀念展覽
Dialogue: 0,1:58:46.20,1:58:51.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OSCAR: "I never saw sad men who looked with such a wistful eye\N奧斯卡:“我從未見過悲傷的人用如此渴望的眼神看著我”
Dialogue: 0,1:58:51.47,1:58:57.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"upon that little tent of blue we prisoners call the sky,\N“在我們囚徒所稱的藍色小帳篷上”
Dialogue: 0,1:58:57.30,1:59:02.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"and at every happy cloud that passed in such strange freedom by."\N"看著每一朵快樂的雲以這種奇異的方式悠悠飄過。"
Dialogue: 0,2:00:24.26,2:00:25.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My dearest, your hands.\N親愛的，你的手怎麼了。
Dialogue: 0,2:00:28.56,2:00:32.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've never been so idle and worked so hard.\N我從未如此空閒，也未如此勞累。
Dialogue: 0,2:00:35.88,2:00:38.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, my dear, we have so little time.\N好吧，親愛的，我們沒有多少時間。\N
Dialogue: 0,2:00:39.92,2:00:42.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Constance, I've waited all these months for you to come.\N哦，康斯坦斯，這幾個月來我一直在等你來。
Dialogue: 0,2:00:44.14,2:00:47.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I would've come before, Oscar, only...\N我是該早點來，奧斯卡，只是。。。
Dialogue: 0,2:00:47.24,2:00:49.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know, it's all been so confusing.\N我不知道，這一切都太令人困惑了。
Dialogue: 0,2:00:51.41,2:00:52.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why have you come now?\N你現在為什麼來了?
Dialogue: 0,2:00:54.11,2:00:55.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have some bad news for you, Oscar.\N奧斯卡，我有個壞消息要告訴你。
Dialogue: 0,2:00:55.94,2:00:58.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't want you to hear it from anyone else.\N我不想讓你從別人那裡聽到。
Dialogue: 0,2:01:00.94,2:01:02.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your mother...\N你的母親……
Dialogue: 0,2:01:03.77,2:01:04.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's dead, Oscar.\N她死了,奧斯卡。
Dialogue: 0,2:01:07.34,2:01:09.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was no pain. She passed away in her sleep.\N沒有痛苦。她在睡夢中去世了。
Dialogue: 0,2:01:14.09,2:01:16.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wish I could leave here in that way.\N我希望我能這樣離開這裡。
Dialogue: 0,2:01:16.39,2:01:18.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, Oscar, you mustn't say that. You must be patient.\N不，奧斯卡，你不能這麼說。你必須有耐心。
Dialogue: 0,2:01:18.74,2:01:21.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not patience that's needed here, it's apathy.\N這裡需要的不是耐心，而是冷漠。
Dialogue: 0,2:01:21.23,2:01:25.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And apathy is the most pitiful of vices.\N而冷漠卻是最可憐的罪惡。
Dialogue: 0,2:01:25.27,2:01:28.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Constance, I don't think I can survive another year of this.\N康斯坦斯，我想我一年也活不下去了。
Dialogue: 0,2:01:28.49,2:01:31.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my dear. It's only the thought of the children\N哦,我親愛的。就是靠著想見孩子們的念頭
Dialogue: 0,2:01:31.10,2:01:33.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that keeps me alive in these terrible months of waiting.\N這讓我在這幾個月可怕的等待中活了下來。
Dialogue: 0,2:01:35.81,2:01:36.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How are they?\N孩子們怎麼樣了？
Dialogue: 0,2:01:41.72,2:01:42.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're well.\N他們都很好。
Dialogue: 0,2:01:45.29,2:01:47.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be Vyvyan's birthday soon.\N維維安馬上要過生日了。
Dialogue: 0,2:01:47.69,2:01:51.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Oscar, I...  -Is he 9 or 10?\N-奧斯卡，我。。。  -他9歲還是10歲生日？
Dialogue: 0,2:01:51.08,2:01:53.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The time passes so slowly.\N時間過得如此之慢。
Dialogue: 0,2:01:53.17,2:01:56.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oscar, I cannot allow you to see the children again.\N奧斯卡，我不能讓你再見孩子們了。
Dialogue: 0,2:02:05.23,2:02:07.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm only trying to do what I think is right.\N我只是在做我認為正確的事。
Dialogue: 0,2:02:07.36,2:02:09.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've thought and thought about it and I...\N這件事我思來想去，我。。。
Dialogue: 0,2:02:17.63,2:02:19.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive me, my dearest.\N原諒我，我親愛的。
Dialogue: 0,2:02:21.33,2:02:23.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please. Forgive me.\N請原諒我。
Dialogue: 0,2:02:31.08,2:02:32.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oscar.\N奧斯卡。
Dialogue: 0,2:02:39.61,2:02:40.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I brought you some cigarettes\N我給你帶煙來了
Dialogue: 0,2:02:42.05,2:02:43.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and some delicacies, some chicken.\N和一些好吃的，一些雞肉。
Dialogue: 0,2:02:43.92,2:02:45.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know what the food must be like.\N我知道食物應該是什麼樣的。
Dialogue: 0,2:02:53.97,2:02:54.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye, my dear.\N再見，親愛的。
Dialogue: 0,2:03:44.54,2:03:46.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will he have time to catch the boat train?\N他有時間趕上渡輪火車嗎?
Dialogue: 0,2:03:46.85,2:03:48.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we hurry.\N如果我們趕緊。
Dialogue: 0,2:03:55.07,2:03:56.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye, Mr. Wilde, sir.\N再見，王爾德先生。
Dialogue: 0,2:03:56.69,2:03:58.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye, Dick. Thank you.\N再見，迪克，謝謝你。
Dialogue: 0,2:04:16.49,2:04:17.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, my dear.\N謝謝你，我親愛的。
Dialogue: 0,2:04:20.71,2:04:22.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oscar.\N奧斯卡。
Dialogue: 0,2:04:22.15,2:04:23.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, we must hurry.\N來吧，我們得快點。
Dialogue: 0,2:04:37.16,2:04:38.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You look well, Oscar.\N奧斯卡，你看起來氣色不錯。
Dialogue: 0,2:04:44.30,2:04:45.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The children send their love.\N孩子們向你問好。
Dialogue: 0,2:04:47.52,2:04:48.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.\N謝謝你。
Dialogue: 0,2:04:50.57,2:04:53.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I told them you were very ill. I hope you understand.\N我告訴他們你病得很重。我希望你能理解。
Dialogue: 0,2:04:55.31,2:04:56.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, of course.\N是的,當然。
Dialogue: 0,2:05:00.58,2:05:02.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I suppose we're better get down to business.\N好了，我想我們最好開始談正事。
Dialogue: 0,2:05:02.36,2:05:03.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There isn't very much time.\N時間不多了。
Dialogue: 0,2:05:06.36,2:05:12.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've arranged with my lawyer to pay you 150pounds a year.\N我和我的律師約定每年付給你150英鎊。
Dialogue: 0,2:05:12.63,2:05:15.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not much, I'm afraid, but it's all I can afford.\N雖然不算多，但恐怕我也只能付得起這些了。
Dialogue: 0,2:05:16.59,2:05:18.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am very grateful to you, Constance.\N非常感謝你，康斯坦斯
Dialogue: 0,2:05:20.46,2:05:22.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only I'm sorry I had to make one condition.\N很抱歉，我必須提出一個條件。
Dialogue: 0,2:05:25.30,2:05:29.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you see or communicate with Bosie again, the payments will stop.\N如果您再見到波西或與他聯系，付款將停止。
Dialogue: 0,2:05:34.70,2:05:37.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I... I understand.\N是的，我。。。我能理解。
Dialogue: 0,2:05:37.31,2:05:38.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know that may sound harsh,\N我知道這聽起來有些刺耳，
Dialogue: 0,2:05:38.79,2:05:41.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I promise you I'm doing it to help you.\N但我向你保證，我這麼做是為了幫助你。
Dialogue: 0,2:05:43.92,2:05:44.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm.\N嗯。
Dialogue: 0,2:06:07.86,2:06:08.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Porter.\N行李員
Dialogue: 0,2:06:12.82,2:06:14.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Boat train, sir?   -Yes.\N-渡輪火車？先生。  -是的。
Dialogue: 0,2:06:26.66,2:06:27.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ada.\N艾達。
Dialogue: 0,2:06:29.05,2:06:31.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You look lovelier than ever.\N你看起來比以前更可愛了。
Dialogue: 0,2:06:31.27,2:06:33.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's good to see you, Oscar.\N噢，很高興見到你，奧斯卡。
Dialogue: 0,2:06:36.67,2:06:37.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ticket, madam?\N票,夫人?
Dialogue: 0,2:06:37.76,2:06:39.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The gentleman has them. Thank you.\N那位先生有。謝謝你。
Dialogue: 0,2:06:41.72,2:06:44.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Robbie, I can't bear to see him looking so ill.\N哦，羅比，我不忍看到他病得這麼厲害。
Dialogue: 0,2:06:44.11,2:06:46.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was talking to the prison doctor yesterday.\N我昨天和獄醫談過了。
Dialogue: 0,2:06:46.16,2:06:48.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Another six months in there and he's never come out alive.\N再在那裡待六個月，他就再也沒能活著出來。
Dialogue: 0,2:06:54.65,2:06:55.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Constance.\N康斯坦斯。
Dialogue: 0,2:06:56.78,2:06:58.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to remember this.\N我希望你們記住這一點。
Dialogue: 0,2:06:59.74,2:07:02.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have always loved you, and I always will.\N我一直愛著你，將來也永遠愛著你。
Dialogue: 0,2:07:04.52,2:07:08.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You talk as if... You're going to get well again\N你說得好像…你會好起來的
Dialogue: 0,2:07:08.35,2:07:10.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and you'll forget about these past two years.\N你會忘記過去的兩年。
Dialogue: 0,2:07:12.62,2:07:14.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll start work again.\N你會重新開始工作的。
Dialogue: 0,2:07:14.23,2:07:16.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know you too well, Oscar. Once you start writing, you...\N奧斯卡，我太了解你了。一旦你開始寫作，你……
Dialogue: 0,2:07:22.46,2:07:26.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ada, don't be so depressed on my behalf.\N艾達，別為我這麼沮喪。
Dialogue: 0,2:07:26.72,2:07:30.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What better reward for one's sins than to be exiled to Paris?\N還有什麼比流放到巴黎更好的罪過獎賞呢?
Dialogue: 0,2:07:30.81,2:07:34.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where no doubt I shall die as I have lived, beyond my means.\N毫無疑問，我將那樣死去，窮困潦倒，入不敷出。
Dialogue: 0,2:07:36.08,2:07:37.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a gorgeous hat.\N多漂亮的帽子啊。
Dialogue: 0,2:07:37.65,2:07:38.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Oscar.\N哦,奧斯卡。
Dialogue: 0,2:07:40.69,2:07:42.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye, my dear.\N再見,我親愛的
Dialogue: 0,2:07:42.35,2:07:43.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take care of the children.\N照顧好孩子。
Dialogue: 0,2:07:56.97,2:07:58.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, Oscar.\N你好,奧斯卡。
Dialogue: 0,2:08:47.63,2:08:49.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I never understood it, Ada.\N我一直不明白，艾達。
Dialogue: 0,2:08:50.50,2:08:51.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just never understood it.\N我就是不明白。\N
Dialogue: 0,2:08:55.72,2:08:59.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OSCAR: "Yet each man kills the thing he loves.\N奧斯卡:“然而每個人都殺死他所愛的東西。”\N節選自《雷丁監獄之歌》
Dialogue: 0,2:08:59.34,2:09:01.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"By each let this be heard.\N“讓每個人都聽到這句話。
Dialogue: 0,2:09:01.47,2:09:03.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Some do it with a bitter look,\N“有些人一臉苦相地去做，
Dialogue: 0,2:09:03.51,2:09:05.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"some with a flattering word.\N“有些人阿諛奉承地去做。
Dialogue: 0,2:09:06.69,2:09:09.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"A coward does it with a kiss,\N“懦夫用吻來做，
Dialogue: 0,2:09:09.04,2:09:11.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"the brave man with a sword."\N勇士拿劍來做。”

